\mt2 The second
\mt1 Sequential Account
\mt2 (2 Chronicles)
\is1 Introduction
\ip The \bk Second Chronicles\bk* account is the continuation of \bk First Chronicles\bk* account (and they're considered as just one account in the book form of the Hebrew Scripturesthe TaNaK). This document includes the account of Shelomoh (Solomon) becoming king, then the rebellion of the northern tribes against his son Rehoboam becoming king. That rebellion was led by Yeroboam (Jeroboam) and resulted in the split between the northern kingdom (called вҖҳYisrael/IsraelвҖҷ or sometimes вҖҳEfrayim/EphraimвҖҷ) and the southern king (called вҖҳYehudah/JudahвҖҷ and consisting mostly of the tribes of Yehudah and Benyamin). This document then ends with the accounts of the kingdom of Yehudah (Judah) and the defeat of Yerushalem (Jerusalem) in 586 B.C.
\iot Main components of this account
\io1 Shelomoh's reign \ior 1:1вҖ“9:31\ior*
\io2 a. The first years \ior 1:1-17\ior*
\io2 b. The temple construction \ior 2:1вҖ“7:10\ior*
\io2 c. The final years \ior 7:11вҖ“9:31\ior*
\io1 The rebellion of the southern tribes \ior 10:1-19\ior*
\io1 The kings of Yehudah \ior 11:1вҖ“36:12\ior*
\io1 The defeat of Yerushalem \ior 36:13-23\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\s1 The requesting of Solomon of wisdom
\rem /s1 The reign of Solomon; King Solomon Prays for Wisdom; Solomon Asks for Wisdom; Solomon Requests Wisdom
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (1 Kgs 3:1-15)
\p
\v 1 David'sВҰ200723 son ShelomohВҰ200720 \add (SolomonВҰ200720)\add* became establishedВҰ200719 over his kingdomВҰ200726 and his godВҰ200728, YahwehВҰ200727, was with him and \add вүҲmade him very powerful\add*.
\p
\v 2 Shelomoh spoke to all Yisrael \add (IsraelВҰ200737)\add*, to the army commandersВҰ200738 of thousandsВҰ200739 andВҰ200733 of hundredsВҰ200740, to the judgesВҰ200741, to all of Yisrael's leaders, including the clan leaders.
\v 3 \add вүҲSoВҰ200750\add* Shelomoh led all the assemblyВҰ200754 to the \add вүҲworship placeВҰ200756\add* atВҰ200758 GibeonВҰ200758 because the \add вүҲsacredВҰ200763 tent\add* was thereВҰ200761 thatВҰ200757 Yahweh's servantВҰ200769 MoshehВҰ200768 \add (MosesВҰ200768)\add* had made inВҰ200758 the wildernessВҰ200772.
\v 4 DavidВҰ200778 had broughtВҰ200777 God's box uphill from Kiryat-Yearim \add and\add* \add *he'd\add* erected a tent for it inВҰ200781 YerushalemВҰ200789 \add (Jerusalem)\add*.\x + \xo 1:4: \xt 2Sam 6:1-17; 1Ch 13:5-14; 15:25вҖ“16:1.\x*
\v 5 The bronzeВҰ200792 altarВҰ200791 made by Betsalel (son of UriВҰ200798, son of HurВҰ200801) was there \add вүҲin frontВҰ200803 of\add* Yahweh's tentВҰ200804, and Shelomoh and the assemblyВҰ200808 \add вүҲrequested Yahweh's guidance there\add*.\x + \xo 1:5: \xt Exo 38:1-7.\x*
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ200810\add* ShelomohВҰ200811 went up to the bronzeВҰ200816 altarВҰ200815 thereВҰ200812 at the \add вүҲsacredВҰ200820 tent\add*, andВҰ200810 \add вүҲin frontВҰ200817 of\add* YahwehВҰ200818, he sacrificed one thousandВҰ200825 burntВҰ200824 offeringsВҰ200824 on it.
\p
\v 7 That nightВҰ200827, GodВҰ200830 appearedВҰ200829 to Shelomoh andВҰ200832 told him, вҖңAsk for what \add you want\add* me to giveВҰ200836 you.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 вҖңYou showed outstanding loyalВҰ200849 commitment to my fatherВҰ200848 DavidВҰ200847,вҖқ Shelomoh \add вүҲreplied\add* to GodВҰ200842, вҖңandВҰ200851 you've made me kingВҰ200851 in his placeВҰ200852.
\v 9 Now, YahwehВҰ200855 GodВҰ200856, may yourВҰ200858 promiseВҰ200858 to my fatherВҰ200861 DavidВҰ200860 be confirmed, for youВҰ200863 yourself have made me kingВҰ200864 over a peopleВҰ200867 as numerousВҰ200868 as the dust on the ground.
\v 10 Give me wisdomВҰ200873 and knowledgeВҰ200874 now \add вүҲas\add* I come and go in frontВҰ200879 of these people, because who could make \add good\add* judgementsВҰ200887 for this greatВҰ200892 people of yoursВҰ200890?вҖқ
\p
\v 11 вҖңBecause that was in yourВҰ200915 heartВҰ200906,вҖқ GodВҰ200897 \add вүҲreplied\add* to Shelomoh вҖңand you didn't ask for wealthВҰ200910, richesВҰ200911, or \add вүҲfame\add*, or the life of those who hate you, and also you didn't ask \add вүҲfor a long life\add*, butВҰ200895 you've asked for wisdomВҰ200925 and knowledgeВҰ200926 for yourselfВҰ200924 \add вүҲto help you lead\add* my peopleВҰ200931 that I've made you kingВҰ200933 over,
\v 12 then I'll giveВҰ200943 you \add that\add* wisdomВҰ200936 and knowledgeВҰ200937, \add along with\add* wealth and richesВҰ200940 and fame. You'll have more than any king that preceded you or any that follows.вҖқ
\s1 Shelomoh's honour and wealth
\rem /s1 King Solomon's Power and Wealth
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (1 Kgs 10:26-29)
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ200961 ShelomohВҰ200962 left the \add вүҲsacredВҰ200969\add* tent atВҰ200966 GibeonВҰ200966 andВҰ200961 returned to YerushalemВҰ200967, where he reignedВҰ200971 over YisraelВҰ200974.
\rem /s1 Solomon's Military and Commercial Activity
\v 14 Then Shelomoh built up \add his\add* chariots and horsemen, and \add вүҲsoon had\add* 1,400 chariots and 12,000 horsemen whichВҰ200994 he stationedВҰ200994 in the chariotВҰ200996 citiesВҰ200995 and withВҰ200995 \add *him\add* in YerushalemВҰ201000.\x + \xo 1:14: \xt 1Ki 4:26.\x*
\v 15 The kingВҰ201003 made silverВҰ201006 and goldВҰ201009 in YerushalemВҰ201010 as \add common\add* as stonesВҰ201011, and he made \add imported\add* cedarВҰ201013 \add timber\add* as \add common\add* as the \add local\add* sycamoreВҰ201015 trees thatВҰ201016 were \add вүҲplentiful\add* in the lowlands.
\v 16 Shelomoh's horsesВҰ201022 \add вүҲwere importedВҰ201021\add* from EgyptВҰ201025 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add* andВҰ201026 from the tradersВҰ201027 in Kue \add (in modern southern TГјrkiye/Turkey)\add*.\x + \xo 1:16: \xt Deu 17:16.\x*
\v 17 \add вүҲEgyptian chariotsВҰ201036 cost\add* six hundred silverВҰ201039 coins and horsesВҰ201040 cost one hundred and fiftyВҰ201041. (The HittitesВҰ201047 and Aramean kings were able to get them \add вүҲfor the same price\add*.)
\c 2
\s1 Preparations for temple construction
\rem /s1 Preparations for Building the Temple
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (1 Kgs 5:1-18)
\p
\v 1 Then Shelomoh \add вүҲdecided to build a temple to honour\add* Yahweh, as well as a \add вүҲpalace for himself\add*,
\v 2 \add вүҲso he conscripted\add* seventy thousand men as porters, eighty thousand as stone-cutters in the hillside quarries, and 3,600 supervisors.
\rem /s1 Alliance with Huram of Tyre
\p
\v 3 Shelomoh \add вүҲcontacted\add* King Hiram in Tsor \add (Tyre)\add*, вҖң\add вүҲIn the time of\add* my father David, you sent cedar \add timber\add* to him so he could buildВҰ201113 himself a palace to live in.
\v 4 Listen, I am buildingВҰ201148 a \add вүҲtemple to honour\add* my godВҰ201153 Yahweh, to consecrate to him. There we'll sacrifice spiced incense to him, plus the regular \add bread\add* display, and burnt offerings in the morning and in the evening, on rest days and on the new moons, and \add вүҲother\add* appointed times of Yahweh ourВҰ201153 godВҰ201153. \add вүҲYisrael is required to do\add* this forever.
\v 5 \add вүҲWe want to build an impressive building, because our god is more powerful\add* than all \add the other\add* gods.
\v 6 \add вүҲButВҰ201187\add* who could \add вүҲstay strong enough\add* to build a house for him, since the \add вүҲsky\add* and the heavens of the heavens can't contain him? And who am I that I could build for him a house for himвҖ”\add вүҲmaybe I'm good enough to burn incense to him\add*?\x + \xo 2:6: \xt 1Ki 8:27; 2Ch 6:18.\x*
\v 7 \add вүҲSo then,\add* sendВҰ201218 me a skilled man who can work in gold, and in silver, and in bronze, and in iron, and in purple and crimson and violet, and who knows how to engrave. \add He will work\add* with the skilled \add craftsmen\add* who my father David appointed and who are with me \add here\add* in Yerushalem and across Yehudah.
\v 8 \add вүҲAlso,\add* send to me cedar, cypress, and algum timber from \add there in\add* Lebanon, because I myself know thatВҰ201248 your servants know how to cut the trees from Lebanon's \add forests\add*. And listen, my servants will \add вүҲhelp\add* your servants
\v 9 so they can supply me with plenty of timberВҰ201261, because the temple that I'mВҰ201262 building will be large and beautiful.
\v 10 I'll pay your wood-cutters three thousand tonnes of ground wheat and the same of barley, four hundred thousand litres of wine and the same of \add olive\add* oil.
\p
\v 11 King Hiram of Tsor \add (Tyre)\add* wrote back to \add King\add* Shelomoh, вҖңYahwehВҰ201308 has appointed you as kingВҰ201322 over his people because he loves them.
\v 12 Blessed be Yisrael's god Yahweh who made the heavens and the earth, who's given King David the king a wise son with insight and understandingВҰ201343, who'll build a temple for Yahweh and a palace for his kingdom.
\p
\v 13 вҖңI'll send Huram-Avi to youвҖ”he's a skilled craftsman
\v 14 \add вүҲHis mother's\add* from the \add вүҲtribe\add* of Dan, and his father a man of Tsor, knowing to work in gold and silver, in bronze and iron, in stone and in timber, in purple and in violet, in fine linen and in crimson, and \add вүҲdo any kind of\add* engraving. \add вүҲHe can follow any pattern\add* that's given to himВҰ201401 by your \add вүҲdesigners, and the designers\add* of my masterВҰ201400, David, your father.
\v 15 \add So then go ahead \add* and send the wheat, barley, \add olive\add* oil, and wine that \add *you\add* promised to send to \add *us\add*,
\v 16 then we'll cut the trees you need from Lebanon and raft them to Yafo by sea. \add вүҲThe responsibility of getting them up the hills to Yerushalem will be yours\add*.
\s1 Temple construction begins
\rem /s1 Construction of the Temple Begins
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (1 Kgs 6:1-38)
\p
\v 17 Shelomoh had all the foreign men living inВҰ201461 Yisrael countedВҰ201461 (similar to what his father David had done), and it came to 153,600.
\v 18 He conscripted seventy thousand as porters, eighty thousand as stone-cutters, and 3,600 as supervisors to keep the others working.
\c 3
\rem /s1 Solomon Builds the Temple
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ201472 Shelomoh beganВҰ201472 to buildВҰ201474 Yahweh's temple onВҰ201480 Mt. Moriyah inВҰ201480 YerushalemВҰ201480, where \add @Yahweh\add* had appearedВҰ201484 to his fatherВҰ201486 David. It was atВҰ201480 the threshingВҰ201491 floorВҰ201491 of OrnanВҰ201492 the YebusiteВҰ201493 where David \add вүҲhad planned for it\add*,\x + \xo 3:1: \xt Gen 22:22.\x*
\v 2 andВҰ201495 they beganВҰ201495 the construction in early-May of the fourth yearВҰ201500 of Shelomoh's reignВҰ201502.\f + \fr 3:2 \ft Probably in 966 B.C.\f*
\v 3 \add вүҲThe temple foundationВҰ201505 was twenty-seven metres long andВҰ201518 nine metres wide\add*,
\v 4 andВҰ201522 the nine metre longВҰ201527 front entrance porch was nine metres high.\f + \fr 3:4 \ft Most modern translations assume that the Hebrew вҖҳfifty-five metres highвҖҷ is an error.\f* \add @Shelomoh\add* overlaidВҰ201539 the insideВҰ201540 \add walls\add* with pure goldВҰ201541.
\v 5 For the \add вүҲmain building\add*, he overlaid it first with cypressВҰ201550 planking, then with pure goldВҰ201552, then \add вүҲcarved\add* palm treesВҰ201556 andВҰ201544 chainsВҰ201557 \add along the walls\add*.
\v 6 The gold \add they use\add* came from ParvaimВҰ201568.\f + \fr 3:6 \ft Probably somewhere south of Yisrael in the Arabian peninsula, but possibly to the east.\f* \add вүҲThe main building\add* was \add also\add* overlaid with valuable gemstones.
\v 7 He overlaidВҰ201570 the temple beamsВҰ201574, thresholdsВҰ201575, walls, and doorsВҰ201577 with goldВҰ201578, and he engraved winged creatures on the walls.
\p
\v 8 Then he made the \add вүҲmost sacredВҰ201591 roomВҰ201591\add* \add inside\add* the temple. It was nine metresВҰ201600 long \add (the full width of the temple)\add* and the same width. He overlaidВҰ201605 it with thirty kilograms pureВҰ201591 goldВҰ201606 \add (beaten into thin sheets)\add*.\x + \xo 3:8: \xt Exo 26:33-34.\x*
\v 9 Each gold nail weighedВҰ201612 half a kilogram, andВҰ201612 he also overlaidВҰ201618 the upperВҰ201617 roomsВҰ201617 with gold.
\p
\v 10 He cast \add molten metal\add* into twoВҰ201627 winged creatures in the \add вүҲmost sacredВҰ201624 roomВҰ201624\add* andВҰ201630 overlaidВҰ201630 them with goldВҰ201632.\x + \xo 3:10-13: \xt Exo 25:18-20.\x*
\v 11 Each of the creatures had two wings, each 2.3 metresВҰ201637 long. One of the wings reached the temple wall, andВҰ201646 the other wing was stretched out to touch the other creature's wingtip,
\v 12 andВҰ201655 \add вүҲthe same for its companion\add*,
\v 13 \add so\add* the total span of the two winged creatures was nine metresВҰ201676. They \add were made\add* standingВҰ201679 on their feetВҰ201682, and \add placed\add* with their faces towardsВҰ201684 \add the opening into\add* the main hall.
\v 14 The \add вүҲcurtainВҰ201690\add* \add separating the two rooms\add* was made from fine-linen with blue, purpleВҰ201692, and red thread, and with winged creatures \add embroidered\add* onto it.\x + \xo 3:14: \xt Exo 26:31.\x*
\s1 The two bronze pillars
\rem /s1 The Two Bronze Columns
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (1 Kgs 7:15-22)
\p
\v 15 At the frontВҰ201701 of the temple, he made two sixteen metre tall pillarsВҰ201703 whichВҰ201710 each had a вҖҳcapitalВҰ201709вҖҷ topping thatВҰ201710 was another two metresВҰ201705 high.
\v 16 \add Ornamental\add* chains were made for the innerВҰ201721 sanctuaryВҰ201721 and to go around the tops of the pillarsВҰ201726, and there were one hundredВҰ201729 pomegranateВҰ201728 \add models\add* hanging onВҰ201721 the chains.
\v 17 There was one pillarВҰ201736 on each side of the \add east-facing\add* entranceвҖ”the lefthand one was named YakinВҰ201750 andВҰ201733 the righthand one was named BoazВҰ201753.
\c 4
\s1 The temple equipment
\rem /s1 Furnishings for the Temple; Equipment for the Temple; Furnishings of the Temple; The Temple's Furnishings
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (1 Kgs 7:23-51)
\p
\v 1 Then he made a \add вүҲsquare,\add* bronzeВҰ201758 altarВҰ201757, nine metresВҰ201766 on each side and 4.5m highВҰ201767,\x + \xo 4:1: \xt Exo 27:1-2.\x*
\v 2 and he made the large, round metalВҰ201774 \add water tank\add* (\add called\add* вҖҳThe SeaвҖҷ) which was 4.5m diameter and over two metresВҰ201776 highВҰ201786.
\v 3 \add вүҲBelow the outer rim were twoВҰ201810 rows of small, ornamental bullsВҰ201795 spaced 45cm apart that were also part of the same casting\add*.
\v 4 \add вүҲSupporting вҖҳThe SeaвҖҷ were twelve large cast bullsвҖ”facing outwards with three facing each of the four compass points\add*.
\v 5 \add вүҲThe sides of the tank were eight centimeters thickВҰ201845. The tank's brim was fashionedВҰ201848 like the brim of a cup, resembling a lily blossomВҰ201852\add*. \add @The tank\add* held sixty-six thousandВҰ201857 litres of water.
\v 6 Then he made ten washbasins, placing five onВҰ201876 \add вүҲeach side for the priests to rinseВҰ201875 the burntВҰ201874 offeringsВҰ201874 in\add*. The priests used вҖҳThe SeaвҖҷ to wash in.\x + \xo 4:6: \xt Exo 30:17-21.\x*
\p
\v 7 He made the ten goldВҰ201887 lampstandsВҰ201886 as per theirВҰ201889 design, and placed them inВҰ201891 the templeВҰ201891 \add вүҲwithВҰ201891 five onВҰ201891 each side\add*.\x + \xo 4:7: \xt Exo 25:31-40.\x*
\v 8 He made ten tablesВҰ201899 and \add also\add* placedВҰ201901 them inВҰ201902 the templeВҰ201902 \add вүҲwithВҰ201902 five onВҰ201902 each side\add*, plus he made one hundredВҰ201910 goldВҰ201909 basins.\x + \xo 4:8: \xt Exo 25:23-30.\x*
\p
\v 9 He made the courtyard for the priestsВҰ201914, as well as the large courtyard with its doors overlaidВҰ201920 with bronzeВҰ201921,
\v 10 andВҰ201923 he placed вҖҳThe SeaвҖҷ in the southeast corner.
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* HuramВҰ201934 made the tubs and shovelsВҰ201940 \add (for the ashes from the altar)\add* and \add other small\add* bowlsВҰ201943.
\p \add вүҲSoВҰ201933\add* Huram finished the workВҰ201951 for God's temple thatВҰ201952 KingВҰ201954 Shelomoh had assigned to him:
\v 12 the two pillars, and the \add вүҲbowl-shaped\add* the capitals on top of each pillar, and the two \add вүҲsets of latticeworkВҰ201968\add* to coverВҰ201970 those two bowls of the capitals,
\v 13 andВҰ201982 the four hundredВҰ201986 pomegranates for the latticeworkВҰ201988вҖ”two rows of pomegranates to coverВҰ201994 each of the two bowlsВҰ201998 of the capitalsВҰ201999 thatВҰ202000 \add вүҲdecorated the tops\add* of the pillarsВҰ202004.
\v 14 He also made the washbasins andВҰ202010 their stands,
\v 15 вҖҳThe SeaвҖҷ andВҰ202022 the twelve bullsВҰ202024 that hold itВҰ202028 up,
\v 16 and the tubs and shovelsВҰ202035, the forksВҰ202038, and other utensilsВҰ202043.
\p Those were all items made of polishedВҰ202052 bronzeВҰ202051 that HuramВҰ202045-Abi made for KingВҰ202047 Shelomoh for Yahweh's temple.
\p
\v 17 The kingВҰ202057 had them cast inВҰ202058 the clay between Sukkot andВҰ202062 TseredahВҰ202063 \add down\add* by the YordanВҰ202055 River.
\v 18 ShelomohВҰ202066 had \add вүҲso many items made that they didn'tВҰ202074 even try to weighВҰ202076 all\add* the bronzeВҰ202077.
\p
\v 19 Shelomoh had all the items for God's temple made, including the goldВҰ202091 altarВҰ202090 and the tablesВҰ202094 \add вүҲfor displaying the sacred breadВҰ202096\add*,
\v 20 and the pure gold lampstands and their lamps for the innerВҰ202106 sanctuaryВҰ202106 according to their designs,
\v 21 the pure gold flowerВҰ202110 \add ornaments\add*, lampsВҰ202111, tongsВҰ202112,
\v 22 the pureВҰ202128 gold lamp trimmers, the basinsВҰ202119 and spoons, and fire pans. Also the temple entranceВҰ202124, its innerВҰ202127 doors into the very sacredВҰ202128 room, and the \add outer\add* temple doors were \add all\add* gold.
\c 5
\rem /s1 The Ark Brought to the Temple
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲAfter\add* all the workВҰ202138 whichВҰ202139 Solomon did for Yahweh's temple was completed, Solomon broughtВҰ202146 in the sacredВҰ202150 thingsВҰ202150 of his fatherВҰ202153 DavidВҰ202152: the goldВҰ202159 and silverВҰ202156, and all the items, he placed in the temple treasuriesВҰ202166.\x + \xo 5:1: \xt 2Sam 8:11; 1Ch 18:11.\x*
\s1 Bringing the sacred box into the temple
\rem /s1 The Ark Brought into the Temple; The Covenant Box Is Brought to the Temple; The Ark Brought to the Temple
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (1 Kgs 8:1-9)
\p
\v 2 Then Shelomoh assembledВҰ202172 the Israeli eldersВҰ202176, andВҰ202178 all the heads of the tribesВҰ202183, the Israeli \add вүҲclan leadersВҰ202184\add* to YerushalemВҰ202190, to bringВҰ202191 the box \add вүҲcontaining\add* Yahweh's agreement up \add the hill\add* from the cityВҰ202198 of DavidВҰ202199, that is, TsiyyonВҰ202201 \add (ZionВҰ202201)\add*.\x + \xo 5:2: \xt 2Sam 6:12-15; 1Ch 15:25-28.\x*
\v 3 \add вүҲSoВҰ202203 inВҰ202211 OctoberВҰ202210,\add* all those IsraeliВҰ202209 leaders gathered to be withВҰ202211 the kingВҰ202206 for a feast,
\v 4 andВҰ202220 once \add вүҲeveryone was there\add*, the LevitesВҰ202221 lifted up the \add sacred\add* chest
\v 5 and carried it up \add towards the temple\add*. The priestsВҰ202244 (who are also LevitesВҰ202245) carried it, along withВҰ202241 the \add sacredВҰ202239\add* tent and everything thatВҰ202240 had been inВҰ202241 it.
\v 6 ThenВҰ202247 KingВҰ202247 Shelomoh and all the assembledВҰ202253 IsraelisВҰ202251 with him, gathered in frontВҰ202255 of the box, sacrificingВҰ202257 sheepВҰ202258 and cattleВҰ202259 whichВҰ202260 were too many to countВҰ202263.
\v 7 The priestsВҰ202269 thenВҰ202268 took the box \add вүҲcontaining\add* Yahweh's agreement, in to its place in the innerВҰ202281 sanctuary of the houseВҰ202282 (the holy of holiesВҰ202286)вҖ”to underВҰ202289 the winged creatures
\v 8 whose outstretched wingsВҰ202296 would now be over the \add sacred\add* chest andВҰ202293 even over the top of itsВҰ202308 carrying polesВҰ202308.
\v 9 \add вүҲThose long poles stuck out and could be seen from the front of that innerВҰ202322 room, butВҰ202311 couldn't be seen from the main room\add*, and they're still thereВҰ202328 to this dayВҰ202330.
\v 10 ThereВҰ202333 was nothing in the box except the twoВҰ202336 \add stone\add* tabletsВҰ202337 that MoshehВҰ202341 \add (MosesВҰ202341)\add* had \add вүҲput in\add* atВҰ202334 Horev \add (Mt. Sinai)\add*, whichВҰ202338 \add represented the agreement that\add* YahwehВҰ202345 \add вүҲhad made withВҰ202334 the IsraelisВҰ202348 after\add* they'd leftВҰ202350 EgyptВҰ202351 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add*.\x + \xo 5:10: \xt Deu 10:5.\x*
\s1 Yahweh's splendour
\rem /s1 The Glory of the Lord
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲThen the priests leftВҰ202355 the holy placeВҰ202359 inВҰ202355 the temple. All the priests who were there, consecratedВҰ202365 themselvesВҰ202365 to serve the priestly duties, irrespective of which divisionВҰ202368 they were part of\add*.
\v 12 All the LevitesВҰ202370 who were singersВҰ202371 (AsafВҰ202373, Heyman, Yedutun, and their sonsВҰ202376 and their brothers) stood onВҰ202380 the east side of the altarВҰ202385. \add вүЎThey\add* were dressed inВҰ202380 fine linenВҰ202379 and had cymbalsВҰ202380, and harpsВҰ202381 and lyresВҰ202382, along withВҰ202380 120 priestsВҰ202387 playing trumpetsВҰ202390.
\v 13 The trumpeters and singersВҰ202398 performed together to praise and thankВҰ202404 Yahweh, with the trumpets and cymbalsВҰ202409 onВҰ202408 the highlights of the song to praise Yahweh:\x + \xo 5:13: \xt 1Ch 16:34; 2Ch 7:3; Ezr 3:11; Psa 100:5; 106:1; 107:1; 118:1; 136:1; Jer 33:11.\x*
\q1 вҖң\add Yahweh\add* is good to us,
\q1 because his loyal commitment continues foreverВҰ202417.вҖқ
\p ThenВҰ202394 Yahweh's temple filled with a cloudВҰ202421
\v 14 and the priestsВҰ202428 weren't able to stay on their feet and continue ministeringВҰ202430 because Yahweh's brilliance had filledВҰ202435 the temple.
\c 6
\s1 Shelomoh's blessing
\rem /s1 Solomon's Address to the People; Dedication of the Temple; Solomon Blesses the People
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (1 Kgs 8:12-21)
\p
\v 1 Then Shelomoh \add вүҲprayed\add*, вҖң\add вүҲYahwehВҰ202448, you said that you\add* would live inВҰ202451 a dark cloud,
\v 2 \add вүҲbutВҰ202453\add* I've builtВҰ202454 a \add вүҲbeautiful\add* residence for youвҖ”a placeВҰ202459 for you to live in foreverВҰ202461.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 \add вүҲThenВҰ202463 while all the people stood\add* \add there\add*, Shelomoh turnedВҰ202463 toward them andВҰ202463 \add вүҲpronounced a blessingВҰ202468 over\add* them,
\v 4 saying, вҖңBlessed be YahwehВҰ202482 the godВҰ202483 of YisraelВҰ202484 who spokeВҰ202486 \add вүҲphysically\add* to my fatherВҰ202490 DavidВҰ202489, andВҰ202491 \add вүҲthen caused it to actually happen\add*, when you saidВҰ202480 \add back then\add*,\x + \xo 6:4-9: \xt 2Sam 7:1-13; 1Ch 17:1-12.\x*
\v 5 вҖҳFrom the time that I broughtВҰ202499 my people out of EgyptВҰ202504, I hadn't choosen a cityВҰ202508 from all the tribesВҰ202510 of YisraelВҰ202511 as a place to buildВҰ202512 a houseВҰ202513 so my nameВҰ202515 could be thereВҰ202516. Nor had I chosen a manВҰ202520 to be leader over my people IsraelВҰ202511,
\v 6 \add вүҲbutВҰ202528\add* \add now\add* I've chosen YerushalemВҰ202529 \add (Jerusalem)\add* \add вүҲto be my place of residence\add* andВҰ202533 I've chosen \add you\add*, DavidВҰ202534, to be over my peopleВҰ202538 YisraelВҰ202539.вҖҷ
\p
\v 7 вҖңMy fatherВҰ202546 DavidВҰ202545 wanted to buildВҰ202547 a temple for Yisrael's godВҰ202551 YahwehВҰ202550,
\v 8 \add вүҲbutВҰ202554\add* YahwehВҰ202555 told \add *him\add*, вҖҳ\add вүҲIt'sВҰ202558 good that youВҰ202569 wanted to buildВҰ202566 a houseВҰ202567 to honour me\add*,
\v 9 \add вүҲbut\add* you won'tВҰ202578 be the one to build it. It'll be yourВҰ202584 own \add вүҲbiological\add* son who'll build the temple to honour my \add вүҲreputation\add*.вҖҷ
\p
\v 10 вҖң\add вүҲNow\add* Yahweh has fulfilledВҰ202591 what he said, and I'm here sitting on Yisrael's throneВҰ202606 instead of my fatherВҰ202601 DavidВҰ202600, just as Yahweh said, and I've had this temple builtВҰ202611 to honour Yisrael's godВҰ202615 Yahweh.
\v 11 I've placed the \add sacred\add* chest in thereвҖ”\add @the box\add* that contains the agreement that YahwehВҰ202627 made with Yisrael's descendants.вҖқ
\s1 Shelomoh's prayer
\rem /s1 Solomon's Prayer; Solomon's Prayer of Dedication
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (1 Kgs 8:22-53)
\p
\v 12 ThenВҰ202635 \add @Shelomoh\add* stoodВҰ202635 in front of the altarВҰ202637 to YahwehВҰ202638 in front of all the assembledВҰ202642 IsraelisВҰ202642, andВҰ202644 spreadВҰ202644 out his handsВҰ202645
\v 13 because \add *he'd\add* made a bronzeВҰ202652 platform and had it placed in the centre of the courtyardВҰ202655. The square platform was just over two metresВҰ202657 on each side, and stood just over a metre off the ground. \add вүҲFirstly\add* he stood on it, then he kneltВҰ202667 down onto his kneesВҰ202670 in front of all the assembledВҰ202674 IsraelisВҰ202674 and spreadВҰ202676 his handsВҰ202677 out to the \add #sky\add*
\v 14 and said, вҖңYahwehВҰ202681, GodВҰ202682 of YisraelВҰ202683, thereВҰ202684 isn'tВҰ202684 any god like you inВҰ202688 the heavensВҰ202688 or onВҰ202688 the earthВҰ202689вҖ”one who keepsВҰ202690 his agreement and \add shows\add* loyal commitment to your servantsВҰ202693 who are walking \add вүҲwithВҰ202688 totalВҰ202696 integrity as you watch them\add*.
\v 15 \add вүҲEverything you verbally told my fatherВҰ202704 DavidВҰ202703 thatВҰ202706 you'd do, you've used your power to make it all happen, including this today\add*.
\v 16 And now, YahwehВҰ202718, GodВҰ202720 of Yisrael, keepВҰ202722 \add something else\add* for your servantВҰ202723 DavidВҰ202725 my fatherВҰ202726 when you told him, вҖҳThere'll \add вүҲalways be one of your descendants sitting onВҰ202752 Yisrael's throneВҰ202741, as long as they obey my instructions just like you have\add*.вҖҷ\x + \xo 6:16: \xt 1Ki 2:4.\x*
\v 17 \add вүҲSoВҰ202757\add* now, YahwehВҰ202758, GodВҰ202759 of YisraelВҰ202760, let what youВҰ202764 said to your servantВҰ202765, to DavidВҰ202766, be confirmed.
\p
\v 18 вҖңButВҰ202780 will GodВҰ202771 really live with humansВҰ202774 \add here\add* on the earthВҰ202777? Wow, the skiesВҰ202780 and the heavens of the heavens can'tВҰ202782 containВҰ202783 youвҖ”how much less this houseВҰ202787 thatВҰ202789 I've builtВҰ202790.\x + \xo 6:18: \xt 2Ch 2:6.\x*
\v 19 \add вүҲNevertheless\add* YahwehВҰ202800 my godВҰ202801, listenВҰ202802 to yourВҰ202812 servant'sВҰ202796 prayer and request \add вүҲand take notice\add*.
\v 20 \add вүҲWatch over this building\add* whereВҰ202826 you said \add вүҲthatВҰ202835 you'd be present\add* and hear \add &my\add* prayersВҰ202834 when your servantВҰ202837 prays towards this place.\x + \xo 6:20: \xt Deu 12:11.\x*
\v 21 Listen \add вүҲto what your servantВҰ202847 and your Israeli peopleВҰ202848 are requesting\add* when they pray towards this place. Listen from where you live in the heavensВҰ202862, and hear and forgiveВҰ202864.
\p
\v 22 вҖңIf someone \add is accused of\add* wronging their neighbourВҰ202870 and is forced to make a sworn statement in frontВҰ202878 of yourВҰ202879 altarВҰ202879 in this temple,
\v 23 thenВҰ202883 \add вүҲlistenВҰ202885\add* from the heavensВҰ202888 and \add вүҲdecide who's telling the truth\add*. \add вүҲThenВҰ202883 punish the guiltyВҰ202895 party as they deserve, and do good to the other side as a rewardВҰ202901 for their innocence\add*.
\p
\v 24 вҖңAnd if your Israeli peopleВҰ202909 are \add вүҲdefeatedВҰ202908 by their enemies because they've disobeyed\add* you, butВҰ202906 they returnВҰ202917 \add to you\add* and confessВҰ202918, and pray, and inВҰ202925 this place they \add вүҲrequest your\add* favour,
\v 25 thenВҰ202928 listenВҰ202929 to them from the heavensВҰ202932 and forgiveВҰ202933 the disobedience of your IsraeliВҰ202936 peopleВҰ202935, and bringВҰ202937 them back to this land thatВҰ202941 you gaveВҰ202943 to theirВҰ202945 ancestorsВҰ202945 and to them.
\p
\v 26 вҖңWhen \add вүҲthe clouds hold back\add* and give no rain because they've \add вүҲdisobeyed\add* you, butВҰ202950 then they pray towards this placeВҰ202961 and \add вүҲacknowledge you\add* and turnВҰ202968 away from theirВҰ202967 disobedience because you've punished them,
\v 27 thenВҰ202972 listenВҰ202974 to them from the heavensВҰ202975 and forgiveВҰ202976 the \add вүҲdisobedience\add* of your servantsВҰ202978 and your Israeli people. Teach them the \add вүҲright way to live their lives\add*, and give rain to your land which you gave your people as a \add вүҲpermanent inheritanceВҰ203000\add*.
\p
\v 28 вҖңIf this land \add suffers\add* from famineВҰ203003, or if there's blightВҰ203012 or mildewВҰ203013, or locustsВҰ203014 or grasshoppers, plagueВҰ203027 or sicknessВҰ203030, or if an enemy \add army\add* surrounds them,
\v 29 then if any person or all yourВҰ203044 IsraeliВҰ203045 peopleВҰ203044 stretchВҰ203051 out their handsВҰ203052 towards this temple with their prayersВҰ203034 and requests because theyВҰ203047 each acknowledge their individual pain and suffering,
\v 30 thenВҰ203058 listenВҰ203059 to them from your where you live there in the heavensВҰ203062 andВҰ203058 forgiveВҰ203065 them. \add вүҲReward\add* each person accordingВҰ203068 to their behaviour, because you know \add вүҲpeople's motives\add*вҖ”only you know \add вүҲwhat's in people's minds\add*.
\v 31 \add Do that\add* so they'll respect you and \add вүҲliving how you want them to\add*, as they live inВҰ203089 \add вүҲthis country\add* that you gaveВҰ203102 to our ancestorsВҰ203103.
\p
\v 32 вҖңAlso, any foreignersВҰ203109 who don'tВҰ203111 belong to your Israeli peopleВҰ203112, who comeВҰ203115 to this land because they've \add вүҲheard that you're very greatВҰ203121 and powerful\add*, if they turn toward this temple and pray
\v 33 thenВҰ203133 listenВҰ203134 to them \add as well\add* from where you live there in the heavensВҰ203137. Do whatever that foreignerВҰ203146 requests from you and that all the people groups in the world will learn about your reputation, and \add вүҲhonour and obey\add* you like your Israeli people do, and to know that this temple that I've builtВҰ203170 is calledВҰ203164 by your name.
\p
\v 34 вҖңWhen you sendВҰ203182 your peopleВҰ203175 off to battleВҰ203176 theirВҰ203179 enemiesВҰ203179, and they pray towards this cityВҰ203186 that you've chosenВҰ203189 and this temple that I've had builtВҰ203194 \add to honour\add* your nameВҰ203195,
\v 35 thenВҰ203197 listenВҰ203197 from the heavensВҰ203200 to their prayerВҰ203203 and their requests, and \add вүҲupholdВҰ203207 their causeВҰ203208\add*.
\p
\v 36 вҖңWhen theyВҰ203211 disobey you (and there'sВҰ203215 no one who doesn't), and you're angryВҰ203221 withВҰ203222 them and allow an enemyВҰ203225 \add вүҲto get the upper hand\add*, and theirВҰ203227 captors takes them a distantВҰ203231 or nearby land as captivesВҰ203227,
\v 37 and thenВҰ203235 in that land whereВҰ203240 they're captivesВҰ203241, they turn and admit their wickednessВҰ203253 and their disobedience, and request your favour,
\v 38 and they turn to you with totalВҰ203257 sincerity in that other country and pray towards the land that you gaveВҰ203273 their ancestorsВҰ203274, and the cityВҰ203275 that you choseВҰ203277, and toward the temple that I'veВҰ203281 builtВҰ203281 \add to honour\add* your nameВҰ203282,
\v 39 thenВҰ203284 listenВҰ203284 from where you live in the heavensВҰ203288 to their prayerВҰ203293 and their requests, and \add вүҲupholdВҰ203297 their causeВҰ203298\add* and forgiveВҰ203299 your peopleВҰ203300 who've \add вүҲdisobeyed\add* you.
\p
\v 40 вҖңNow my godВҰ203307, pleaseВҰ203310 let your eyesВҰ203311 be open and your earsВҰ203313 attentiveВҰ203314 to prayersВҰ203315 \add offered towards\add* this placeВҰ203316.
\p
\v 41 вҖң\add вүҲSo\add* now Yahweh God, along withВҰ203335 the \add sacred\add* box of your strength, come and enter your restingВҰ203324 placeВҰ203324. Yahweh God, may your priestsВҰ203328 be dressed inВҰ203335 salvationВҰ203332, and your faithfulВҰ203333 ones enjoy \add your\add* goodnessВҰ203335.\x + \xo 6:41-42: \xt Psa 132:8-10.\x*
\v 42 YahwehВҰ203337 GodВҰ203338, don'tВҰ203339 \add вүҲignore\add* those who you've chosen. Remember the loyal commitment of your servantВҰ203347 DavidВҰ203346.вҖқ
\c 7
\s1 The temple dedication
\rem /s1 The Dedication of the Temple; Solomon Dedicates the Temple
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (1 Kgs 8:62-66)
\p
\v 1 When Shelomoh \add (SolomonВҰ203351)\add* finishedВҰ203350 praying, fireВҰ203353 cameВҰ203354 down from the skies and consumed the burntВҰ203357 offeringВҰ203357 and the sacrificesВҰ203358, and Yahweh's \add вүҲbrilliant light\add* filledВҰ203361 the temple.\x + \xo 7:1: \xt Lev 9:23-24.\x*
\v 2 The priestsВҰ203368 weren't able to goВҰ203369 into Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add* because of Yahweh's \add вүҲbrilliant light\add*,
\v 3 and when all the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ203387\add* saw the fireВҰ203391 comeВҰ203390 down and saw the \add вүҲbright light\add* above the \add вүҲtemple\add*, they fell \add to their knees withВҰ203390\add* their faces bowedВҰ203397 down low to the stone pavementВҰ203402, and worshippedВҰ203403 and thankedВҰ203404 YahwehВҰ203393 saying, вҖңHe is certainly goodВҰ203407вҖ”his loyal commitment really will \add continue\add* foreverВҰ203409.вҖқ\x + \xo 7:3: \xt 1Ch 16:34; 2Ch 5:13; Ezr 3:11; Psa 100:5; 106:1; 107:1; 118:1; 136:1; Jer 33:11.\x*
\p
\v 4 ThenВҰ203412 the kingВҰ203412 andВҰ203413 all the peopleВҰ203415 offered sacrificesВҰ203416 to YahwehВҰ203419вҖ”
\v 5 KingВҰ203423 Shelomoh sacrificedВҰ203422 twenty-two thousand cattleВҰ203428 and one hundredВҰ203433 and twenty thousand sheepВҰ203432, and \add so\add* the king and all the peopleВҰ203444 dedicatedВҰ203436 God's \add вүҲtemple\add*.
\v 6 The priests were standing in their positions, as well as the LevitesВҰ203451 withВҰ203452 the instrumentsВҰ203452 thatВҰ203456 KingВҰ203459 David had made to give thanksВҰ203460 to Yahweh. When \add вүҲthey assisted\add* David in praisingВҰ203466 \add Yahweh\add*, \add they would sing\add*, вҖң\add вүҲYes,\add* his loyal commitment \add continues\add* foreverВҰ203464,вҖқ andВҰ203446 the priests \add вүҲwould blow their trumpetsВҰ203470\add* in front of them as all the \add вүҲIsraelis\add* stood \add there\add*.
\p
\v 7 Then Shelomoh consecratedВҰ203479 the middleВҰ203483 of the courtyardВҰ203484 \add вүҲin frontВҰ203486\add* of Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple building\add* so he could offer burnt offerings and the fat of the peace offerings thereВҰ203493, because the bronzeВҰ203501 altarВҰ203500 thatВҰ203485 \add *he'd\add* made wasn't able to \add вүҲhandle\add* the \add large number of\add* burnt offerings and grainВҰ203513 offerings, and the fats.
\p
\v 8 ThenВҰ203518 Shelomoh andВҰ203527 all YisraelВҰ203529 feasted for the \add next\add* sevenВҰ203525 daysВҰ203526вҖ”the hugeВҰ203532 gathering spread from Levo-HamatВҰ203535 \add in the far north\add*, all the way to the Egyptian riverbed \add in the far south\add*.
\v 9 On the eighthВҰ203543 day, they \add вүҲhad a solemn service\add*, because they'd observedВҰ203549 seven days of celebration for the altarВҰ203548 \add ?вүҲwith seven days of feasting\add*.
\v 10 \add вүҲFinally after some threeВҰ203558 weeks,\add* \add @Shelomoh\add* sent the people \add вүҲhome\add*вҖ”they were cheery and \add вүҲencouraged\add* because of the goodnessВҰ203571 thatВҰ203572 YahwehВҰ203574 had \add вүҲdisplayed to\add* DavidВҰ203575 and Shelomoh, and for his Israeli people.
\s1 Yahweh appears to Shelomoh again
\rem /s1 The Lord Appears to Solomon; The Lord's Response to Solomon; God Appears to Solomon Again
\s4 Full kingdom
\rem /r (1 Kings 9.1-9)
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲSoВҰ203580\add* Shelomoh finished Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add* andВҰ203580 the king's \add вүҲpalaceВҰ203602\add*вҖ”he'd succeededВҰ203603 inВҰ203602 \add вүҲimplementing everythingВҰ203591 that he'd envisaged\add*.
\rem /s1 God's Second Appearance to Solomon
\v 12 \add вүҲOne\add* nightВҰ203611, YahwehВҰ203607 appearedВҰ203606 to Shelomoh inВҰ203611 a dream and told him, вҖңI've heardВҰ203614 yourВҰ203617 prayerВҰ203617, and I've chosenВҰ203618 this \add вүҲtemple to be the placeВҰ203619 where my people will offer sacrificesВҰ203623\add* \add to me\add*.
\v 13 If I restrain the skiesВҰ203627 \add вүҲso\add* there's no rain, or if I commandВҰ203634 locusts to devourВҰ203638 the land, or if I sendВҰ203642 disease among my peopleВҰ203644,
\v 14 \add вүҲthen if\add* my peopleВҰ203647 \add вүҲwho are known by my nameВҰ203651\add* humbleВҰ203646 themselves and pray, and \add вүҲrequest my help\add* and turnВҰ203656 back from their evil waysВҰ203657, then I myself will hearВҰ203660 \add >them\add* from the heavensВҰ203663, and I'll forgiveВҰ203664 their sinВҰ203665, and I will healВҰ203666 their land.
\v 15 My eyesВҰ203672 will be open andВҰ203675 my earsВҰ203675 will be attentiveВҰ203676 to prayersВҰ203677 \add вүҲoffered towards\add* this placeВҰ203678,
\v 16 as I've chosenВҰ203682 andВҰ203681 consecratedВҰ203683 this \add вүҲtemple to be associated with my nameВҰ203690 foreverвҖ”I'll be permanently present there\add*.
\v 17 \add вүҲAlso, if you'll obey\add* me like your father DavidВҰ203710 did, and do everything that I've instructedВҰ203715 you, and keep my rules and regulationsВҰ203716,
\v 18 thenВҰ203720 \add вүҲI'll ensure that your descendants rule your kingdom\add*, just as I \add вүҲpromised\add* your father DavidВҰ203726 when I said, вҖҳ\add вүҲYou won'tВҰ203729 fail to have one of your descendants\add* ruling over YisraelВҰ203735.вҖҷ
\v 19 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if you all turnВҰ203739 away, and abandonВҰ203741 my rules and instructions thatВҰ203744 I gave you all, and \add вүҲdecide to\add* serveВҰ203748 otherВҰ203750 godsВҰ203749 and worshipВҰ203751 them,
\v 20 thenВҰ203754 I'll remove \add @these peopleВҰ203775\add* from my land that I gaveВҰ203758 them. \add вүҲAlso this temple\add* that I consecratedВҰ203765 for \add вүҲmyself\add*, I'll \add вүҲthrowВҰ203767 it away where I can't see it\add*, and I'll make it \add вүҲan object of scorn and ridicule\add* among all the \add other\add* nations.
\p
\v 21 ThenВҰ203777 this \add вүҲtemple whichВҰ203779 everyoneВҰ203784 admires\add* as they pass by, will be devastated and \add @people\add* will \add вүҲask\add*, вҖҳWhy did YahwehВҰ203790 do \add вүҲsuch terrible things\add* to that \add вүҲtemple\add* and to that land?вҖҷ
\p
\v 22 вҖҳIt happened because they abandonedВҰ203800 YahwehВҰ203803, the godВҰ203805 of theirВҰ203806 ancestorsВҰ203806,вҖҷ others will reply. вҖҳHe brought them out from \add slavery inВҰ203812\add* EgyptВҰ203810, \add вүҲbutВҰ203797 thenВҰ203797\add* they obtained other godsВҰ203812 and worshippedВҰ203814 them and servedВҰ203816 themвҖ”that's why he sent them all this misery.вҖҷ вҖқ
\c 8
\s1 King Shelomoh's achievements
\rem /s1 Solomon's Many Achievements; Solomon's Achievements; Solomon's Other Activities; Various Activities of Solomon
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (1 Kgs 9:10-28)
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲAfter\add* the twentyВҰ203832 years thatВҰ203834 it took Shelomoh to build Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add* and his \add вүҲpalace\add*,
\v 2 \add *he\add* rebuiltВҰ203850 the citiesВҰ203845 thatВҰ203846 \add King\add* HuramВҰ203848 had givenВҰ203847 to \add *him\add*, andВҰ203845 he \add вүҲgot IsraelisВҰ203857 to live in them\add*.
\p
\v 3 ThenВҰ203860 Shelomoh \add вүҲattacked\add* HamatВҰ203863-Tsovah andВҰ203860 \add вүҲcapturedВҰ203864 it\add*.
\v 4 He \add вүҲrebuilt\add* TadmoreВҰ203870 in the wildernessВҰ203871, andВҰ203872 storageВҰ203876 citiesВҰ203875 in the HamatВҰ203879 \add region\add*.
\v 5 He \add вүҲrebuilt\add* the fortifiedВҰ203893 citiesВҰ203892 of Upper-Beyt-Horon and Lower-Beyt-Horon with wallsВҰ203894 and barred gates,
\v 6 as well as Baalat and all the storageВҰ203905 cities, and all the cities for Shelomoh's chariotsВҰ203913 and horsemen thatВҰ203906 he wanted to buildВҰ203925 inВҰ203926 YerushalemВҰ203926 and LebanonВҰ203927, and throughout his kingdom.
\v 7 All the peopleВҰ203934 \add вүҲwho lived in YisraelВҰ203945 butВҰ203939 who were actually\add* remnants of the HittitesВҰ203938, AmoritesВҰ203939, PerizzitesВҰ203940, HivitesВҰ203941, and Yebusites
\v 8 \add вүҲwho were descendantsВҰ203950 of groups that the IsraelisВҰ203959 hadn't completely destroyedВҰ203958, were forcedВҰ203963 to become Shelomoh's labourersВҰ203963 andВҰ203961 theyВҰ203952 continue in that role untilВҰ203964 the present time\add*.
\v 9 \add вүҲHowever,\add* Shelomoh didn'tВҰ203973 make the IsraelisВҰ203970 become labourers, because theyВҰ203981 became his \add вүҲsoldiers\add*, officers, chariotВҰ203987 commanders, andВҰ203968 horsemen.
\v 10 \add вүҲSome\add* 250 \add Israelis\add* were \add also\add* KingВҰ203998 Shelomoh's \add вүҲchief officialsВҰ203993\add* who had authorityВҰ204002 over the peopleВҰ204003.
\p
\v 11 Shelomoh broughtВҰ204010 \add his wife\add*, Far-oh's \add (Pharaoh'sВҰ204009)\add* daughterВҰ204007, up from the cityВҰ204012 of David to the house thatВҰ204015 he had builtВҰ204016 for her, because he said, вҖңMy wife mustn't live in the \add вүҲpalace\add* of Yisrael's KingВҰ204028 David, because the placesВҰ204035 whereВҰ204035 Yahweh's box has been are sacredВҰ204033.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 Then Shelomoh sacrificed burntВҰ204046 offeringsВҰ204044 to YahwehВҰ204047 on the altarВҰ204049 thatВҰ204051 had been builtВҰ204052 in frontВҰ204053 of the \add temple's\add* porch.
\v 13 He \add вүҲfollowed Mosheh'sВҰ204062 instructions about the daily\add* \add sacrifices\add* for the rest days and the new moonsВҰ204064, and for the appointed threeВҰ204066 timesВҰ204067 per year: the Celebration of Flat Bread, the Harvest Festival, and the Celebration Living inВҰ204056 Shelters.\x + \xo 8:13: a \xt Num 28:9-10; \xo b \xt Num 28:11-15; \xo c \xt Exo 23:14-17; 34:22-23; Num 28:16вҖ“29:39; Deu 16:16.\x*
\v 14 ThenВҰ204076 as his fatherВҰ204080 David had instructed, he assigned the priests into divisions for their various tasks, and the LevitesВҰ204088 who would praiseВҰ204092 and ministerВҰ204093 in front of the priests and help in their daily tasks, and gatekeepersВҰ204100 in their divisions atВҰ204101 the various gates. That was \add all\add* what David, the manВҰ204108 of God had commandedВҰ204106.
\v 15 The priestsВҰ204118 andВҰ204112 LevitesВҰ204119 followed the king's instructions concerningВҰ204123 all their duties, as well as \add their supervision of\add* the treasuriesВҰ204123.
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲSoВҰ204125 now,\add* all of Shelomoh's workВҰ204128 on Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add* was completedвҖ”from the foundationВҰ204133 through to it's completion \add andВҰ204137 operation\add*.
\p
\v 17 Then Shelomoh wentВҰ204146 to Etsyon-Gever and to Eylat on the edge of the ocean, in the EdomВҰ204159 \add вүҲregionВҰ204158\add*.
\v 18 \add King\add* HuramВҰ204164 \add (from Tsor/Tyre)\add* sent ships to him \add as his\add* servants who knew the seaВҰ204172 \add well\add*. ThenВҰ204161 Shelomoh's men \add boarded the ships\add* and sailed withВҰ204165 them to OfirВҰ204178, where they obtained fifteen tonnes of goldВҰ204186 and broughtВҰ204187 \add it back\add* to King Shelomoh.
\c 9
\s1 The queen from Sheva visits
\rem /s1 The Queen of Sheba Visits Solomon; The Queen of Sheba's Visit; The Visit of the Queen of Sheba; Visit of the Queen of Sheba
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (1 Kgs 10:1-13)
\p
\v 1 The queenВҰ204194 from the Sheva \add region\add* had heardВҰ204197 \add вүҲall about\add* Shelomoh, and she came to YerushalemВҰ204208 with some hard questionsВҰ204207. HerВҰ204232 party \add included\add* a large numberВҰ204216 of camelsВҰ204212 carryingВҰ204213 lots of spicesВҰ204214 and goldВҰ204215 and valuable gemstones. She came to Shelomoh and \add вүҲdiscussed\add* everything thatВҰ204213 was onВҰ204207 herВҰ204232 mind with him.\x + \xo 9:1-9: \xt Mat 12:42; Luk 11:31.\x*
\v 2 Shelomoh responded to all herВҰ204242 \add вүҲqueries\add*, andВҰ204243 there wasn't any subject thatВҰ204248 \add *he\add* wasn't able to speak to.
\v 3 When the queenВҰ204254 from Sheva saw Shelomoh's wisdomВҰ204258, andВҰ204260 \add вүЎsaw\add* the \add вүҲpalace\add* thatВҰ204261 he'd builtВҰ204262
\v 4 and the food at his tableВҰ204265, as well as the seatingВҰ204266 of his servantsВҰ204269, his well-dressed ministers standing by, his cup-bearers inВҰ204282 their uniforms, and the burntВҰ204273 offeringsВҰ204273 thatВҰ204274 he sacrificed at Yahweh'sВҰ204277 \add вүҲtemple\add*, it \add вүҲtook her breathВҰ204283 away\add*
\v 5 and she told the kingВҰ204288, вҖңEverything I heardВҰ204292 inВҰ204293 my \add own\add* country about you and you wisdomВҰ204299 was true.
\v 6 I didn't believeВҰ204303 \add вүҲwhat they reported to me untilВҰ204305 I sawВҰ204309 itВҰ204313 with my own eyesВҰ204310\add*, andВҰ204301 wow, the reportsВҰ204304 thatВҰ204323 I heardВҰ204324 \add вүҲdidn't even cover\add* \em half\em* of the extent of yourВҰ204318 wisdomВҰ204318!
\v 7 Your menВҰ204327 are blessed, and \add even\add* your servantsВҰ204329 are blessed to be able to continuallyВҰ204333 standВҰ204331 in front of you and listenВҰ204334 to your wisdomВҰ204337.
\v 8 Let your god YahwehВҰ204340 be blessedВҰ204342вҖ”the one who delightedВҰ204345 inВҰ204346 you to place you onВҰ204346 his throneВҰ204350 as \add *his\add* king. Your godВҰ204341 lovedВҰ204354 YisraelВҰ204358 \add and wanted\add* to establishВҰ204359 them foreverВҰ204360, \add вүҲso\add* he's placed you over them as kingвҖ”to give justiceВҰ204365 and \add вүҲdo what is rightВҰ204366\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 9 ThenВҰ204368 she gave the king four tonnes of goldВҰ204374, a very large quantity of spices, andВҰ204368 valuable gemstones. \add Nobody before had ever seen\add* such a large amount of spices as what the queenВҰ204387 from Sheva gave to KingВҰ204369 Shelomoh.
\p
\v 10 (\add вүҲAlso\add*, \add King\add* Huram'sВҰ204396 servants \add working together with\add* Shelomoh's servants brought goldВҰ204403 from OfirВҰ204404, as well as algumВҰ204407 wood andВҰ204393 valuable gemstones.
\v 11 The king made the algumВҰ204416 wood into staircases for Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add* and for the king's \add вүҲpalaceВҰ204421\add*, and into lyresВҰ204423 and harpsВҰ204424 for the singersВҰ204425. Nothing like that had been seen beforeВҰ204430 in YehudahВҰ204432.)
\p
\v 12 KingВҰ204434 ShelomohВҰ204435 gave the queenВҰ204437 from ShebaВҰ204439 \add вүҲeverything she wanted\add*вҖ”more than what she'd broughtВҰ204450 to the king. ThenВҰ204434 she \add вүҲdeparted\add* with her servantsВҰ204458 andВҰ204434 went \add back\add* to her country.
\s1 Shelomoh's wealth
\rem /s1 Solomon's Great Wealth; Solomon's Wealth and Splendour; King Solomon's Wealth; Solomon's Splendour
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (1 Kgs 10:14-25)
\p
\v 13 In one year, Shelomoh received about twenty tonnes of gold,
\v 14 as well as what the merchants and traders brought in. All the ArabianВҰ204485 kingsВҰ204484, and all the \add ?вүҲlocal\add* governorsВҰ204486 brought goldВҰ204489 and silverВҰ204490 to Shelomoh.
\v 15 KingВҰ204494 ShelomohВҰ204495 made two hundred large shields of beaten goldвҖ”six hundred gold \add coins worth\add* of beaten gold \add вүҲwent into\add* each shield.
\v 16 \add вүҲAlsoВҰ204528,\add* three hundred \add вүҲsmaller shields\add*вҖ”three hundred gold \add coins worth\add* of beatenВҰ204515 gold \add вүҲwent into\add* each shield.
\p
\v 17 Then the kingВҰ204532 made a large, ivoryВҰ204535 throneВҰ204533 and overlaidВҰ204537 it with pure goldВҰ204538.
\v 18 There were six stepsВҰ204542 \add leading up to\add* the throne, andВҰ204541 a goldВҰ204545 footstoolВҰ204544 was attachedВҰ204547 to \add *it\add*. It had armrests onВҰ204545 \add вүҲeach side\add*, withВҰ204545 a lion \add statue\add* besideВҰ204558 each armrest.
\v 19 There were twelve \add statues of\add* lionsВҰ204563 standingВҰ204564 on the sixВҰ204568 stepsВҰ204569вҖ”one at each end of each step. \add No throne\add* like that existed in any otherВҰ204571 kingdomВҰ204578.
\p
\v 20 All of KingВҰ204583 Shelomoh's \add вүҲcups\add* were made of gold, andВҰ204580 all the \add вүҲvarious dishes\add* in вҖҳThe House of the LebanonВҰ204591 ForestвҖҷ were refined gold. Nothing was made of silver, because in the \add вүҲtime\add* of Shelomoh's \add reign\add*, silver wasn't considered valuable
\v 21 because the king's ships wentВҰ204613 to TarshishВҰ204606 with Huram'sВҰ204609 servantsВҰ204608. EveryВҰ204616 threeВҰ204611 yearsВҰ204612 the fleet would \add вүҲbring back\add* goldВҰ204618, silverВҰ204619, ivory, and apes and baboons,
\v 22 \add вүҲso\add* KingВҰ204626 ShelomohВҰ204627 \add became\add* greaterВҰ204625 than all the other kingsВҰ204629 in the world, \add both\add* in wealth and in wisdomВҰ204632.
\p
\v 23 \add вүҲKings from all over the world wanted to come andВҰ204634 listenВҰ204642\add* to the wisdomВҰ204645 thatВҰ204646 God had \add вүҲgiven\add* Shelomoh.
\v 24 Each of them would bringВҰ204653 gifts: goldВҰ204659 and silverВҰ204657 items, clothes, myrrh and spicesВҰ204662, horsesВҰ204663 and mulesВҰ204664. (\add This continued\add* \add вүҲyear after year\add*.)
\p
\v 25 SolomonВҰ204672 had fourВҰ204673 thousand stallsВҰ204675 for horsesВҰ204676 and chariotsВҰ204677, and twelve thousand horsemen, and he kept \add some\add* in the chariotВҰ204685 citiesВҰ204684 and \add some\add* \add вүҲclose by\add* in YerushalemВҰ204689.\x + \xo 9:25: \xt 1Ki 4:26.\x*
\v 26 He \add ended up\add* rulingВҰ204692 over all the kingsВҰ204695 \add in the regionВҰ204701\add* from the \add Euphrates\add* River \add in the northeast\add*, \add west\add* to the area of the PhilistinesВҰ204702, andВҰ204691 \add south down\add* to the Egyptian borderВҰ204704.\x + \xo 9:26: \xt Gen 15:18; 1Ki 4:21.\x*
\v 27 TheВҰ204712 kingВҰ204708 made silverВҰ204711 \add as common\add* as stonesВҰ204713, andВҰ204714 cedarВҰ204715 \add timber as common\add* as the sycamoreВҰ204717 fig trees inВҰ204712 the lowlands.
\v 28 Horses were brought in from Egpyt \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add* for Shelomoh andВҰ204727 from \add вүҲother countriesВҰ204729 as well\add*.\x + \xo 9:28: \xt Deu 17:16.\x*
\s1 Summary of Shelomoh's reign
\rem /s1 Summary of Solomon's Reign; Death of Solomon; Solomon's Death
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (1 Kgs 11:41-43)
\p
\v 29 Everything else that Shelomoh did, from the beginning to the end, was written down by the prophet NatanВҰ204743, and the prophecy by AhiyahВҰ204748 (from Shiloh) and the prophet Iddo'sВҰ204751 visionsВҰ204750 about Nevat's son Yaraveam \add (Jeroboam)\add* \add were also written down\add*.
\v 30 ShelomohВҰ204762 reignedВҰ204761 from YerushalemВҰ204763 over all YisraelВҰ204768 for fortyВҰ204769 years,
\v 31 thenВҰ204772 he \add вүҲdied\add* and was buriedВҰ204777 withВҰ204778 his fatherВҰ204780 inВҰ204778 вҖҳThe City of DavidВҰ204779вҖҷ, and his son Rehaveam \add (RehoboamВҰ204782)\add* \add вүҲreplaced himВҰ204777 as king\add*.
\c 10
\s1 Yisrael splits in two
\rem /s1 Kings of Judah; The Revolt against Rehoboam; Israel Rebels Against Rehoboam; The Northern Tribes Revolt
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (1 Kgs 12:1-20)
\p
\v 1 Then Rehaveam \add (RehoboamВҰ204788)\add* wentВҰ204787 to Shekem where all YisraelВҰ204795 had gathered \add вүҲfor his coronation\add*.
\v 2 \add вүҲMeanwhile\add*, Nevat's son Yaraveam \add (Jeroboam)\add* had fled from KingВҰ204811 Shelomoh andВҰ204799 was \add down\add* inВҰ204806 Egypt, \add вүҲbutВҰ204799\add* when he heardВҰ204800 \add about the coming coronation\add*, \add *he\add* returnedВҰ204812 from Egypt.
\v 3 \add вүҲSoВҰ204816\add* the leaders of the northern tribes summoned \add @Yaraveam\add*, and he wentВҰ204820 with them to speak to \add Shelomoh's son\add* Rehaveam and all YisraelВҰ204824, saying,
\v 4 вҖңYour father \add вүҲmade us workВҰ204838 very hard, butВҰ204836\add* now, lightenВҰ204837 the \add вүҲdemands thatВҰ204843\add* your father \add вүҲmade on\add* us, and we'll serveВҰ204847 youВҰ204847.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 вҖңCome back to me in threeВҰ204852 daysВҰ204853.вҖқ \add @Rehaveam\add* \add вүҲanswered\add*, so the peopleВҰ204857 departed.
\p
\v 6 Then KingВҰ204861 Rehaveam consultedВҰ204860 withВҰ204873 the older men who'd advised his fatherВҰ204872 Shelomoh when he was \add still\add* aliveВҰ204874, \add вүҲasking\add* \add &them\add*, вҖңHow do you all advise me to answer the peopleВҰ204880?вҖқ
\p
\v 7 вҖңIf you are good to those peopleВҰ204892 and \add вүҲdo things that pleaseВҰ204894 them\add*, and speakВҰ204895 \add вүҲkindly\add* to them,вҖқ they \add вүҲanswered\add*, вҖңthenВҰ204885 they'll \add вүҲserve you for a long time to come\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 \add вүҲHowever,\add* \add @Rehaveam\add* \add вүҲrejectedВҰ204906 their advice\add*, andВҰ204906 consultedВҰ204913 some of the young men \add вүҲthere\add* who'd grownВҰ204918 up with him.
\v 9 вҖң\add вүҲHow would youВҰ204926 guys suggest thatВҰ204934 I answer the peopleВҰ204932 who've asked me to lightenВҰ204938 the burden on them from the days of my father\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 10 вҖң\add вүҲThoseВҰ204964 peopleВҰ204958 tell you that your father was hard on them andВҰ204948 that you should lightenВҰ204970 their load\add*,вҖқ \add вүҲhis contemporaries advised him\add*. вҖң\add вүҲButВҰ204948 you should tell that that your littleВҰ204975 fingerВҰ204975 is thickerВҰ204976 than your father's waist\add*,
\v 11 \add вүҲandВҰ204980 that whereas he required them to contribute, you'll be even more demanding. Tell them that he might\add* have whipped you with \add leather\add* whipsВҰ204994, butВҰ204980 that you'll whip them with scorpionsВҰ204996!вҖқ
\p
\v 12 \add вүҲSo\add* Yaraveam and all the peopleВҰ205003 \add вүҲreturnedВҰ205013\add* to \add KingВҰ205011\add* Rehaveam on the third day \add вүҲas he'd prearranged\add*,
\v 13 andВҰ205018 ignoring the advice of the older men, the king answeredВҰ205018 \add @the people\add* harshly.
\v 14 \add вүҲHe passed onВҰ205043 the suggestion\add* of the younger men, telling \add &the people\add*, вҖңI'll make your \add вүҲburden even heavier\add*. My fatherВҰ205040 rebuked you all with whipsВҰ205043, butВҰ205028 I'll \add вүЎdo it\add* with scorpionsВҰ205045.вҖқ
\v 15 \add вүҲSoВҰ205047\add* the kingВҰ205050 \add вүҲtook no notice of the people'sВҰ205053 request\add*, because \add вүҲitВҰ205056 was God turning events around so thatВҰ205066 what YahwehВҰ205062 had said to Yaraveam (Nevat's son) through AhiyahВҰ205069 (from Shiloh), would come to pass\add*.
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲWhen\add* all \add вүҲthe Israelis\add* saw that the king hadn't listenedВҰ205084 to them, and the peopleВҰ205088 \add from the northern tribes\add* answeredВҰ205087 the king, вҖңWhat \add вүҲdid David have to do withВҰ205098 us anyway\add*? \add вүҲWe had nothing to gain\add* from Yeshay's \add (Jesse'sВҰ205104)\add* son. \add вүҲYou might as well all head home, and thenВҰ205078 they'll see what happened to David'sВҰ205098 dynasty\add*.вҖқ
\p \add вүҲSoВҰ205078 they all went home\add*\x + \xo 10:16: \xt 2Sam 20:1.\x*
\v 17 and RehaveamВҰ205126 \add ended up\add* \add вүҲonly ruling over the IsraelisВҰ205120 livingВҰ205121 inВҰ205122 the YehudahВҰ205123 region\add*.
\p
\v 18 King Rehaveam \add (still inВҰ205150 Shekem)\add* sentВҰ205128 out HadoramВҰ205133, his supervisor of the forced labourersВҰ205137, butВҰ205128 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ205141 hurled stonesВҰ205138 atВҰ205150 him and killed him\add*. \add When he heard about that\add*, King RehoboamВҰ205130 \add вүҲforced his way into his\add* chariotВҰ205150 \add вүҲand escaped\add* to YerushalemВҰ205152,
\v 19 andВҰ205155 \add northern\add* YisraelВҰ205156 has rebelledВҰ205155 against David'sВҰ205158 \add вүҲdescendants\add* untilВҰ205159 today.
\c 11
\s1 The scolding of prophet Simayass to Rehoboam
\rem /s1 Judah and Benjamin Fortified; Shemaiah's Prophecy
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (1 Kgs 12:21-24)
\p
\v 1 When Rehaveam \add (RehoboamВҰ205165)\add* \add вүҲarrived in\add* YerushalemВҰ205166, he assembledВҰ205167 the \add вүҲwarriors\add* of YehudahВҰ205171 and BenyaminВҰ205172: 180,000 chosenВҰ205176 to fightВҰ205179 against YisraelВҰ205182 to bring the kingdomВҰ205186 back to Rehaveam.
\v 2 \add вүҲButВҰ205199\add* YahwehВҰ205193 \add вүҲspoke\add* to the prophet ShemayahВҰ205196 saying,
\v 3 вҖң\add Go and\add* tell \add вүҲthis\add* to Shelomoh's son KingВҰ205209 Rehaveam of Yehudah, and to all the IsraeliВҰ205212 people of the tribes of Yehudah and BenyaminВҰ205216:
\v 4 Yahweh says that you mustn't go and fight with your relatives. Everyone should just go homeВҰ205233 again because everythingВҰ205232 that's happened, came from me.вҖқ \add вүҲSo\add* they listened to the messageВҰ205242 from Yahweh, and \add вүҲcalled off the planned attack\add* against YeroboamВҰ205248.
\s1 Rehaveam fortifies the cities
\rem /s1 Rehoboam Fortifies Judah; Rehoboam Fortifies the Cities
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 5 \add вүҲSo\add* Rehaveam lived inВҰ205253 YerushalemВҰ205253 and fortified the citiesВҰ205255 throughout YehudahВҰ205257:
\v 6 Beyt-Lehem, Eytam, TekoaВҰ205270,
\v 7 Beyt-TsurВҰ205276, Sokoh, AdullamВҰ205282,
\v 8 GatВҰ205286, MareshahВҰ205289, ZifВҰ205292,
\v 9 Adorayim, Lakish, AzekahВҰ205302,
\v 10 ZorahВҰ205306, Ayyalon, and Hevron (all inВҰ205314 YehudahВҰ205314 and BenyaminВҰ205315).
\v 11 He strengthenedВҰ205319 the fortifications \add in those cities and towns\add*, \add вүҲappointed an army commanderВҰ205325, and stocked their storehousesВҰ205326 with\add* food and oilВҰ205328 and wine.
\v 12 He \add also\add* \add вүҲequipped each of them with\add* shieldsВҰ205335 and spearsВҰ205336, and \add вүҲmade them well-protected\add*. \add вүҲSoВҰ205331\add* YehudahВҰ205343 and BenyaminВҰ205344 \add вүҲwere under his control\add*.
\s1 Priests and Levites go down to Yehudah
\rem /s1 Priests and Levites Support Rehoboam; Priests and Levites Come to Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 13 The priestsВҰ205347 and LevitesВҰ205348 throughout all YisraelВҰ205352 \add вүҲsupported Rehaveam from every part of the country\add*.
\v 14 The LevitesВҰ205362 abandonedВҰ205361 their propertyВҰ205366 and their pasturelandВҰ205365 and moved to YerushalemВҰ205369 and across the rest of YehudahВҰ205368, because Yaraveam and his sonsВҰ205374 rejectedВҰ205372 them from servingВҰ205375 as priestsВҰ205375 to YahwehВҰ205376.
\v 15 \add вүҲInstead\add* \add @Yaraveam\add* established his own priestsВҰ205381 for his hilltop shrines and for the goat and calf \add idols\add* thatВҰ205385 he'd made.\x + \xo 11:15: \xt 1Ki 12:31.\x*
\v 16 \add вүҲAs well as\add* \add @the priests andВҰ205388 Levites\add*, people from all the IsraeliВҰ205390 tribesВҰ205390 \add вүҲwho wanted to serve\add* Yisrael's godВҰ205400 Yahweh, cameВҰ205402 to YerushalemВҰ205403 to sacrificeВҰ205404 to Yahweh, the god of their ancestorsВҰ205407.
\v 17 \add вүҲSoВҰ205409\add* they strengthened the kingdomВҰ205412 of YehudahВҰ205413, and as \add @the people\add* followed the ways of DavidВҰ205426 and Shelomoh, they strengthened Rehaveam's \add rule\add* for three years.
\s1 Rehaveam's family
\rem /s1 Rehoboam's Family; Rehoboam's Marriages
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 18 Rehaveam \add вүҲmarried\add* MahalatВҰ205438. She was the daughter of David'sВҰ205445 son Yerimot, and her mother was Avihayil, the daughter of Eliav and \add вүҲgranddaughter\add* of YishayВҰ205452 \add (JesseВҰ205452)\add*.
\v 19 \add вүҲThey had\add* \add three\add* sonsВҰ205456: YeushВҰ205459, ShemaryahВҰ205462, andВҰ205454 ZahamВҰ205465.
\v 20 After her, he \add вүҲmarried\add* Avishalom's daughterВҰ205472 Maakah, and they had \add four sons\add*: Aviyah, AttaiВҰ205482, ZizaВҰ205485, and ShelomitВҰ205488.
\v 21 Rehaveam lovedВҰ205490 Maakah \add вүҲthe most out of hisВҰ205501 eighteenВҰ205504 wives and sixty slave-wives\add*. He fatheredВҰ205510 twenty-eight sonsВҰ205513 and sixty daughtersВҰ205515,
\v 22 \add вүҲbutВҰ205517\add* he appointedВҰ205517 Maakah's son Aviyah to be the leader of his \add older andВҰ205517 younger\add* brothersВҰ205527, because \add вүҲthat would mark him as the future\add* kingВҰ205529.
\v 23 He wiselyВҰ205531 sent his \add other\add* sonsВҰ205535 to fortifiedВҰ205543 citiesВҰ205542 across all \add вүҲthe regions\add* in YehudahВҰ205539 and BenyaminВҰ205540, \add вүҲwhere he set them up generously\add* and \add вүҲasked the local peopleВҰ205549 to give them wivesВҰ205550\add*.
\c 12
\s1 Egypt attacks Yehudah
\rem /s1 Egypt Invades Judah; Shishak Attacks Jerusalem; An Egyptian Invasion of Judah; Egypt Attacks Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (1 Kgs 14:25-28)
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲHowever,\add* after Rehaveam \add (RehoboamВҰ205555)\add* \add вүҲhad become establishedВҰ205553 and in firm control of his\add* kingdomВҰ205554, he \add вүҲand all the people\add* abandonedВҰ205557 Yahweh's instructions.
\v 2 Because theyВҰ205582 were unfaithfulВҰ205582 to Yahweh, KingВҰ205571 ShishakВҰ205574 from EgyptВҰ205577 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add* cameВҰ205573 \add to attack\add* YerushalemВҰ205580 inВҰ205569 the fifthВҰ205570 yearВҰ205569 of Rehaveam's \add reign\add*
\v 3 with 1,200 chariotsВҰ205587 and sixtyВҰ205588 thousand horsemenВҰ205590, along with a huge numberВҰ205592 of troops including Egyptians, LibyansВҰ205599, SukkitesВҰ205600, and Kushites.
\v 4 He capturedВҰ205603 Yehudah'sВҰ205609 fortifiedВҰ205607 citiesВҰ205606, thenВҰ205603 moved towards YerushalemВҰ205613.
\p
\v 5 Then the prophetВҰ205617 Shemayah and the leaders of YehudahВҰ205623 who had \add вүҲfled\add* to YerushalemВҰ205629 because of Shishak'sВҰ205631 \add attacks\add* cameВҰ205618 to Rehaveam. \add @Shemayah\add* told them, вҖңYahwehВҰ205637 saysВҰ205636 that it was all of you who abandoned me, \add вүҲso\add* then I've also abandoned you all \add вүҲto be defeated by\add* Shishak.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 ThenВҰ205650 the kingВҰ205654 and the IsraeliВҰ205653 leadersВҰ205651 humbledВҰ205650 themselves and saidВҰ205655, вҖңYahwehВҰ205658 \add вүҲalways does what is rightВҰ205656 and fair\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 When YahwehВҰ205661 sawВҰ205660 that they'd humbled themselves, \add вүҲhe gave this\add* messageВҰ205665 to ShemayahВҰ205671, вҖңThey've humbled themselves \add so\add* I won't destroyВҰ205676 themвҖ”my rage won't pour out onВҰ205660 YerushalemВҰ205685 \add вүҲusing Shishak'sВҰ205688 attack\add*, andВҰ205660 I'll give them \add вүҲa way to recover\add* \add inВҰ205660 the future\add*.
\v 8 \add вүҲNevertheless,\add* they'll becomeВҰ205691 his servantsВҰ205694, and they'll \add вүҲlearn\add* \add the difference between\add* \add вүҲserving me versus serving the kings of other nations\add*.
\p
\v 9 \add вүҲWhen\add* Egypt'sВҰ205706 KingВҰ205704 ShishakВҰ205703 \add вүҲinvaded\add* YerushalemВҰ205709, he took the treasures from Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add* and the king's \add вүҲpalace\add*. He took everythingВҰ205724 \add valuable\add*, \add вүҲincluding\add* the goldВҰ205730 shieldsВҰ205729 thatВҰ205731 Shelomoh had made.\x + \xo 12:9: \xt 1Ki 10:16-17; 2Ch 9:15-16.\x*
\v 10 KingВҰ205736 RehaveamВҰ205737 \add вүҲreplaced them with\add* bronzeВҰ205740 shieldsВҰ205739, andВҰ205735 \add вүҲdistributed them to the leaders of those who guardedВҰ205746\add* the entranceВҰ205748 to the king'sВҰ205750 \add вүҲpalace\add*.
\v 11 \add вүҲAfter that, whenever the king went to Yahweh's temple, the guards went with him carryingВҰ205761 those bronze shields. ThenВҰ205752 when the king left again, they'd returnВҰ205762 them to the guardroom\add*.
\v 12 \add вүҲBecause\add* Rehaveam humbledВҰ205768 himself, YahwehВҰ205773 \add вүҲstopped being angry withВҰ205768 him\add* andВҰ205768 didn'tВҰ205774 \add вүҲeliminate\add* him, \add вүҲso\add* thingsВҰ205780 were \add reasonably\add* goodВҰ205781 inВҰ205768 YehudahВҰ205778.
\rem /s1 Death of Rehoboam; Summary of Rehoboam's Reign
\p
\v 13 KingВҰ205785 Rehaveam \add вүҲconsolidated his rule\add* in Yerushalem. He reigned \add вүҲfor a totalВҰ205813 of\add* forty-one yearsвҖ”seventeenВҰ205797 of which were from Yerushalem cityВҰ205803 whereВҰ205804 YahwehВҰ205807 had chosenВҰ205806 from all the tribesВҰ205814 in YisraelВҰ205815 to establish his \add вүҲreputation\add*. (\add @Rehaveam's\add* motherВҰ205817 was the Ammonitess, NaamahВҰ205818.)
\v 14 \add @Rehaveam\add* did evilВҰ205822 \add things\add* because he didn'tВҰ205824 \add вүҲmake it his priority to get directionВҰ205825 from\add* YahwehВҰ205830.
\p
\v 15 The \add вүҲaccount of everything that Rehaveam did while he was king, including genealogicalВҰ205846 records, was recorded inВҰ205841 the scrolls\add* writtenВҰ205840 by the prophetsВҰ205843 ShemayahВҰ205842 and IddoВҰ205844. Rehaveam and Yaraveam \add вүҲwere atВҰ205841 war withВҰ205841 each other for his entireВҰ205850 reign\add*.
\v 16 ThenВҰ205854 Rehaveam \add вүҲdied\add*, he was buriedВҰ205859 withВҰ205860 his ancestorsВҰ205858 inВҰ205860 вҖҳThe City of DavidВҰ205861вҖҷ, andВҰ205854 his son Aviyah \add вүҲreplaced\add* him as kingВҰ205862.
\c 13
\s1 Aviyah defeats Yeroboam
\rem /s1 Abijah Reigns over Judah; Abijah King of Judah; Abijah's War with Jeroboam
\s4 Both kingdoms
\r (1 Kgs 15:1-8)
\p
\v 1 In the eighteenthВҰ205869 yearВҰ205868 of \add the reign of\add* KingВҰ205871 Yaraveam \add (Jeroboam)\add*, Aviyah \add started his\add* reign over YehudahВҰ205877 \add (Judah)\add*.
\v 2 He ruled from YerushalemВҰ205882 for three yearsВҰ205880. (His motherВҰ205884 was Uriel'sВҰ205888 daughterВҰ205886 Mikayah from Giveah.)
\p \add вүҲHowever\add* war \add started\add* between Aviyah and Yaraveam.
\p
\v 3 Aviyah \add вүҲlaunched the attack\add* with four-hundred thousand \add вүҲstrong warriors\add*, andВҰ205899 Yaraveam drew up in formationВҰ205915 against him with eight-hundred thousand \add вүҲstrong warriors\add* in his army.
\p
\v 4 Aviyah \add вүҲstood onВҰ205933 the top of\add* Mt. Tsemarayim inВҰ205933 the Efrayim hill-country and \add вүҲshouted\add*, вҖңYaraveam and all YisraelВҰ205940, listenВҰ205936 to me.
\v 5 \add вүҲDon't youВҰ205943 all understand\add* that Yisrael's godВҰ205948 YahwehВҰ205946 \add вүҲmade a formal agreement\add* that the kingdom of Yisrael was givenВҰ205950 foreverВҰ205956 to DavidВҰ205952 andВҰ205958 his descendants?
\v 6 \add вүҲButВҰ205963\add* Nevat's son Yaraveam, who was a servantВҰ205968 of David'sВҰ205972 son Shelomoh, \add вүҲtook action\add* and rebelledВҰ205973 against his masterВҰ205976,
\v 7 and \add вүҲa bunch of wicked good-for-nothings\add* gatheredВҰ205978 around \add @Yaraveam\add* and \add вүҲcreated a force\add* againstВҰ205999 Shelomoh's son, Rehaveam, when Rehaveam was \add вүҲstill an inexperiencedВҰ205994, youngВҰ205993 manВҰ205993 and couldn't stand up to\add* them.
\v 8 \add вүҲSoВҰ206001\add* now you're all sayingВҰ206004 that you'll \add вүҲstand against\add* the kingdomВҰ206007 \add вүҲthat YahwehВҰ206008 established through\add* David'sВҰ206011 descendantsВҰ206010. \add вүҲThere are certainly many of you, andВҰ206001 you have\add* the goldВҰ206017 calvesВҰ206016 that Yaraveam made as godsВҰ206022 for you all.
\v 9 Didn't you all driveВҰ206025 out the LevitesВҰ206034, as well as Yahweh's priests who were Aharon's descendantsВҰ206032? Then you all \add вүҲappointed\add* for yourselves вҖҳpriestsвҖҷ like they have inВҰ206045 \add other\add* countries, so that anyoneВҰ206046 who comesВҰ206042 to consecrateВҰ206043 himself by bringing a young bullВҰ206045 from the herd and sevenВҰ206050 rams can become a вҖҳpriestвҖҷ of your non-gods.
\p
\v 10 вҖң\add вүҲButВҰ206057\add* as for us, Yahweh is ourВҰ206059 godВҰ206059 and we haven't abandonedВҰ206061 himВҰ206061. Our priestsВҰ206062 who minister to Yahweh are Aharon's descendantsВҰ206065, and the LevitesВҰ206067 \add вүҲassist them\add*.
\v 11 \add вүҲEvery morning and every evening\add*, they sacrifice burntВҰ206072 offeringsВҰ206070 to Yahweh, and spiced incenseВҰ206079. There's \add sacred\add* breadВҰ206083 onВҰ206073 the \add вүҲdisplay\add* tableВҰ206086, and the lamps inВҰ206073 the goldВҰ206089 lampstand give lightВҰ206091 every evening because weВҰ206097 are following the instructions of ourВҰ206102 godВҰ206102 Yahweh, \add вүҲbutВҰ206070\add* you all have abandonedВҰ206104 him.
\v 12 \add вүҲSoВҰ206107 listen!\add* GodВҰ206125 is \add вүҲguiding us\add* andВҰ206107 his priestsВҰ206112 will blastВҰ206114 their trumpetsВҰ206113 to soundВҰ206115 against you all. \add вүЎListen\add* you IsraelisВҰ206117: don'tВҰ206119 fight against YahwehВҰ206124, the godВҰ206125 of your ancestorsВҰ206127, because you won'tВҰ206119 succeedВҰ206131.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 \add вүҲButВҰ206133 meanwhile,\add* Yaraveam had \add вүҲsent\add* \add some men\add* around to ambush them from behind, so theyВҰ206140 were \add both\add* in frontВҰ206141 of \add the army from\add* YehudahВҰ206142 andВҰ206133 in ambush behind them.
\p
\v 14 When \add the warriors from\add* YehudahВҰ206147 turnedВҰ206146, wow, \add вүҲthey realised that they were being attacked from inВҰ206158 front andВҰ206146 from\add* behindВҰ206152. They \add вүҲcalled\add* out to YahwehВҰ206154 \add for help\add* \add вүҲwhile\add* the priestsВҰ206155 blew their trumpetsВҰ206156.
\v 15 ThenВҰ206160 the men from Yehudah \add вүҲshoutedВҰ206160 a loud battle cry\add* and GodВҰ206167 defeatedВҰ206168 Yaraveam and all YisraelВҰ206174 \add вүҲinВҰ206164 frontВҰ206175 of\add* Aviyah and Yehudah.
\v 16 Yisrael's \add вүҲsoldiers\add* fled away from Yehudah'sВҰ206184 \add army\add*, andВҰ206179 GodВҰ206186 \add вүҲenabled Yehudah to defeat them\add*.
\v 17 Aviyah and his \add вүҲmen thrashed them badly\add*, and \add some\add* five-hundred thousandВҰ206201 of their chosenВҰ206203 \add вүҲwarriors were killed\add*.
\v 18 \add вүҲSoВҰ206205\add* the IsraelisВҰ206208 were subduedВҰ206205 atВҰ206209 that time, andВҰ206205 the people from YehudahВҰ206213 were victoriousВҰ206211 because they \add вүҲtrusted inВҰ206209\add* YahwehВҰ206218, the godВҰ206219 of theirВҰ206220 ancestorsВҰ206220.
\p
\v 19 Aviyah chased afterВҰ206224 Yaraveam and they captured the citiesВҰ206228 of Beyt-El, YeshanahВҰ206239, and EfronВҰ206245 and the surrounding villages from \add @Yisrael\add*.
\v 20 Yaraveam \add вүҲnever regained military strengthВҰ206252\add* during Aviyah's \add вүҲreign\add*, and \add after a time\add* YahwehВҰ206259 struckВҰ206258 him \add withВҰ206256 sickness\add* and he diedВҰ206260.
\p
\v 21 \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* Aviyah \add вүҲbecame more powerful\add*. He tookВҰ206265 fourteen wivesВҰ206268 for himself, and had twenty-two sonsВҰ206274 and sixteen daughtersВҰ206277.
\v 22 The rest of \add вүҲwhat Aviyah did, including his sayings and his behaviour, was writtenВҰ206285 down by\add* the prophetВҰ206287 IddoВҰ206288.
\c 14
\s1 King Asa's rule over Yehudah
\rem /s1 King Asa Defeats the Ethiopians; Early Years of Asa's Reign; Asa Reigns
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 1 Then Aviyah \add вүҲdied\add* and they buried him with his ancestors in вҖҳThe city of DavidвҖҷ, and his son AsaВҰ206313, reigned in his place. \add вүҲDuring his rule,\add* the \add вүҲcountry was peaceful for\add* ten years.
\v 2 Asa did what was good and right in the eyes of his god YahwehвҖ”
\v 3 he removed the \add вүҲpagan\add* altars and the \add вүҲhilltop shrines\add*, \add вүҲsmashed\add* the sacred \add stone\add* pillars, and cut the Asherah poles down.
\v 4 He \add вүҲordered\add* \add the people in\add* YehudahВҰ206354 to \add вүҲworship\add* Yahweh, the god of their ancestors, and to obey his instructions and regulations.
\v 5 HeВҰ206383 removed all the hilltop shrines from Yehudah'sВҰ206369 citiesВҰ206367 and the incense altars, and the kingdom \add вүҲwas peacefulВҰ206372 under his rule\add*.
\v 6 He fortified Yehudah'sВҰ206388 citiesВҰ206393 as the place was quiet without war during those years, because YahwehВҰ206407 had givenВҰ206410 himВҰ206409 \add вүҲpeace\add*
\v 7 and he'd told YehudahВҰ206424, вҖңLet's build theseВҰ206439 cities and \add вүҲwith walls around them\add*, and towers, doors, and bars \add while\add* the land is quiet \add вүҲaround\add* us because we've \add вүҲasked\add* our god Yahweh \add вүҲfor guidance\add*. We've \add вүҲmade our request\add* and he's given rest to us all around.вҖқ \add вүҲSo\add* they built and they \add вүҲprospered\add*.
\v 8 \add King\add* Asa had an army of three-hundred thousandВҰ206449 men from Yehudah who carried large shields and spears, as well as 280,000 men from Benyamin who also carried shields along withВҰ206448 bows and arrows. They were all \add вүҲpowerful warriors\add*.
\s1 The Ethiopian invasion repelled
\rem /s1 Ethiopian Invasion Repulsed
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 9 \add вүҲButВҰ206460 then\add* Zerah the Kushite \add (or Ethiopian)\add* came out against them withВҰ206465 an army of a million \add soldiers\add* and three hundred chariots, and he \add вүҲadvanced\add* to MareshahВҰ206467.
\v 10 AsaВҰ206471 went out to \add вүҲoppose\add* them, and they deployed for battle inВҰ206493 the Tsefatah valley near Mareshah.
\v 11 Then \add King\add* AsaВҰ206516 called out to his god Yahweh, вҖңYahweh, it \add вүҲmakes no difference to you if there's one against you, or one million\add*. Help us, Yahweh our god, because we rely on you, and we've come against this \add вүҲmassive force trusting in your reputation\add*. Yahweh, you're our godвҖ”don't let \add вүҲmere humans\add* prevail against you.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 \add вүҲSo\add* YahwehВҰ206542 \add вүҲhelped AsaВҰ206524 and the army from Yehudah to defeat\add* the Cushites, and \add *they\add* fled.
\v 13 Asa and his army chased them \add southwest\add* as far as GerarВҰ206557. \add вүҲSo many\add* Kushites \add вүҲwere killed\add* that \add the rest\add* \add вүҲcouldn't save themselves\add*, because they had been \add вүҲdestroyedВҰ206551 inВҰ206576 front\add* of YahwehВҰ206563 and his \add вүҲarmy\add*, and the \add @men of Yehudah\add* carried away a large amount of plunderВҰ206565.
\v 14 They struck all the cities around Gerar, because \add вүҲthe Kushites there were terrified of Yahweh\add*. The \add @men from Yehudah\add* plundered all those cities, because theyВҰ206583 \add вүҲcontained a lot of valuable goods\add*.
\v 15 They also attacked the \add Kushite\add* cattle \add вүҲherdsmen\add*, as well as capturing lots of sheep and camels \add вүҲbefore returning\add* to Yerushalem.
\c 15
\s1 Azaryah's prophecy gives courage to Asa
\rem /s1 Asa's Religious Reforms; Asa's Reforms; Asa's Reform
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 1 Then God's spiritВҰ206598 came on Oded'sВҰ206595 son AzaryahВҰ206592,
\v 2 and he wentВҰ206601 out to \add King\add* Asa and told him, вҖңListen to me, Asa, and all YehudahВҰ206610 and BenyaminВҰ206611: YahwehВҰ206612 is with you all, when you're all with him. And if you all look for him, he'll be foundВҰ206619 by you all, butВҰ206601 if you abandon him, he'll \add also\add* abandon you all.
\v 3 YisraelВҰ206630 has been without the true God \add вүҲfor a long timeВҰ206628\add* as there hasn't been a priestВҰ206636 teachingВҰ206637, so \add God's\add* instructions \add have been forgotten\add*.
\v 4 \add вүҲHowever,\add* they turnedВҰ206641 to Yisrael's godВҰ206648 YahwehВҰ206647 when they were inВҰ206642 distressВҰ206642, and \add вүҲrequested his help\add* and he \add вүҲhelped\add* them.
\p
\v 5 вҖңIn those timesВҰ206654, it wasn't \add вүҲsafe to travel away\add* because thereВҰ206656 was \add вүҲwide unrest among\add* the inhabitantsВҰ206666 of the \add surrounding\add* \add вүҲregions\add*.
\v 6 Nation crushed nation, andВҰ206669 city \add вүЎcrushed\add* city, because GodВҰ206677 \add sent them\add* \add вүҲone troubleВҰ206678 after another\add*.
\v 7 ButВҰ206683 all of youВҰ206683, be strongВҰ206684 andВҰ206685 don'tВҰ206685 give up \add вүҲstriving\add*, because your \add hard\add* workВҰ206692 will be rewardedВҰ206691.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 When \add King\add* AsaВҰ206696 heardВҰ206695 those wordsВҰ206697 and the prophecy from the prophet Oded'sВҰ206700 \add son\add*, he \add вүҲtook courage\add* and removedВҰ206703 all the detestable \add idolsВҰ206704\add* from across YehudahВҰ206708 and BenyaminВҰ206709, and from the citiesВҰ206712 that he'd capturedВҰ206714 from the Efrayim hill country. \add вүҲAlso,\add* he repairedВҰ206717 the altarВҰ206720 to Yahweh that \add stood\add* in frontВҰ206723 of Yahweh's temple.
\p
\v 9 He assembled all \add the people from\add* Yehudah and BenyaminВҰ206733, as well as the many people who had joined them from \add the tribes of\add* Efrayim, Menashsheh, and Shimeon. (Many people had emmigrated from YisraelВҰ206743 \add into Yehudah\add* when they had realisedВҰ206745 that his godВҰ206749 YahwehВҰ206748 was \add вүҲhelping\add* him.)
\v 10 They gatheredВҰ206753 \add together\add* in YerushalemВҰ206754 in \add вүҲJune\add* of the fifteenth yearВҰ206757 of \add King\add* Asa'sВҰ206762 reignВҰ206761
\v 11 and sacrificedВҰ206764 seven hundredВҰ206774 bulls to YahwehВҰ206765 and seven thousandВҰ206777 sheepВҰ206775вҖ”\add all of whichВҰ206771 had come\add* from the \add recent\add* plunderВҰ206770.
\v 12 They \add solemnly\add* \add вүҲagreed to sincerely andВҰ206779 diligently devote themselves to\add* YahwehВҰ206784, the godВҰ206785 of their ancestorsВҰ206786.
\v 13 \add They decided\add* that anyone who didn'tВҰ206796 \add вүҲworship\add* Yisrael's godВҰ206800 YahwehВҰ206799 \add вүҲmust be killed, man or womanВҰ206813, andВҰ206794 whether or not they had an important position\add*.
\v 14 They \add вүҲloudly promised\add* that together to YahwehВҰ206816, thenВҰ206815 shoutedВҰ206819 and blew trumpetsВҰ206820 and hornsВҰ206821,
\v 15 and all YehudahВҰ206826 \add вүҲcelebrated that promise because they were totally sincere and committed. They asked YahwehВҰ206842 to give them guidance which he did, and he enabled them to have peace throughout their country\add*.
\p
\v 16 KingВҰ206852 Asa also removedВҰ206853 his mother Maakah from \add herВҰ206864 position as\add* queenВҰ206854 because she made a disgusting Asherah \add pole\add*. Asa cut down \add вүҲthe pole\add* and crushedВҰ206865 it, and burnt it atВҰ206867 the KidronВҰ206868 brook,
\v 17 \add вүҲalthough\add* theyВҰ206873 didn'tВҰ206871 removeВҰ206873 the hilltop shrines from YisraelВҰ206874. \add вүҲNevertheless,\add* AsaВҰ206878 \add вүҲmaintained his singular devotion\add* \add to Yahweh\add* \add вүҲall his lifetime\add*,
\v 18 and he broughtВҰ206885 his father'sВҰ206889 sacredВҰ206888 thingsВҰ206888, and his own, into God's \add вүҲtemple\add* houseВҰ206891 of GodвҖ”goldВҰ206894 and silverВҰ206893 items.
\v 19 There was no more war \add in Yehudah\add* untilВҰ206900 the thirty-fifth yearВҰ206901 of Asa'sВҰ206906 reignВҰ206905.
\c 16
\s1 Yisrael comes to invade Yehudah
\rem /s1 Troubles with Israel; Final Years of Asa's Reign; Alliance with Aram Condemned; Asa's Last Years
\s4 Both kingdoms
\r (1 Kgs 15:17-22)
\p
\v 1 In the thirty-sixth year of \add King\add* Asa'sВҰ206913 reignВҰ206912, Yisrael's king BaashaВҰ206915 \add вүҲinvaded\add* Yehudah and builtВҰ206922 RamahВҰ206925 to \add вүҲprevent anyoneВҰ206928 from leaving or entering the land of\add* Yehudah'sВҰ206921 King Asa.
\v 2 AsaВҰ206935 took goldВҰ206937 and silverВҰ206936 from the \add вүҲtemple\add* treasuriesВҰ206938 and the king's \add вүҲpalace\add*, and he sentВҰ206943 \add it\add* to KingВҰ206940 BenВҰ206946-HadadВҰ206948 of AramВҰ206950 \add (modern SyriaВҰ206950)\add*, who livedВҰ206951 inВҰ206952 DamascusВҰ206952, \add вүҲrequesting\add*,
\v 3 вҖң\add I want\add* a \add вүҲpeace treatyВҰ206969\add* between you and me, and between your \add вүҲfamily\add* and \add вүҲmine\add*. Listen, I've sent goldВҰ206966 and silverВҰ206965 to you. Go \add and\add* breakВҰ206968 your agreement with Yisrael's KingВҰ206973 BaashaВҰ206972, \add вүҲso\add* he'll \add вүҲgive up on his attack\add* againstВҰ206976 me.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 BenВҰ206979-HadadВҰ206981 \add вүҲaccepted\add* KingВҰ206984 Asa'sВҰ206985 \add вүҲsuggestion\add* and sent his army captains \add to fight\add* againstВҰ206994 Yisrael's cities. They struck Iyyon, DanВҰ207004, and HevelВҰ207006-MayimВҰ207007, and all the storehousesВҰ207011 in the NaftaliВҰ207013 cities.
\v 5 \add вүҲWhen\add* \add King\add* BaashaВҰ207017 heardВҰ207016 \add about that\add*, he stopped \add вүҲfortifying\add* RamahВҰ207022 andВҰ207015 \add вүҲabandoned the project\add*,
\v 6 \add вүҲso\add* KingВҰ207030 AsaВҰ207029 tookВҰ207031 \add men there\add* from YehudahВҰ207036. They carriedВҰ207037 away all the \add building\add* stonesВҰ207040 from RamahВҰ207041, along with the timberВҰ207044 whichВҰ207045 BaashaВҰ207047 had been using, and used \add it all\add* to build Geva and Mitspah \add (north of Yerushalem)\add*.
\s1 Hanani's prophecy about coming wars
\rem /s1 The Prophet Hanani
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 7 At that time, the prophet HananiВҰ207061 wentВҰ207060 to Yehudah'sВҰ207067 KingВҰ207066 AsaВҰ207065, and told him, вҖңBecause you reliedВҰ207070 on the king from AramВҰ207074 \add вүҲrather than\add* on your godВҰ207080 YahwehВҰ207079, therefore the Aramean king's army has escapedВҰ207084 from \add вүҲbeing defeated by you\add*.
\v 8 Weren't the Kushites and the LibyansВҰ207093 \add вүҲoverwhelming inВҰ207102 numberВҰ207097\add* withВҰ207102 chariotsВҰ207098 and horsemenВҰ207099, yet because you reliedВҰ207102 onВҰ207102 YahwehВҰ207105, he \add вүҲhelped you defeat them\add*,
\v 9 because YahwehВҰ207110 \add вүҲsees everything that's happening all over the world, and he strengthensВҰ207116 thoseВҰ207119 who trust himВҰ207111 completelyВҰ207120\add*. You've been foolishВҰ207122 \add вүҲin what you've just done\add*, so from now on, you'll \add вүҲbe facing\add* wars.вҖқ
\v 10 \add вүҲButВҰ207132\add* \add King\add* Asa was angry atВҰ207142 the prophet, very angry, and had him put inВҰ207142 \add вүҲprisonВҰ207139\add*, and \add вүҲafter that\add* Asa oppressedВҰ207147 some of \add &his\add* peopleВҰ207151.
\s1 The end of Asa's reign
\rem /s1 The End of Asa's Reign; Asa's Disease and Death; Summary of Asa's Reign
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (1 Kgs 15:23-24)
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲAll of Asa'sВҰ207157 projects from the beginning of his reign to the end\add* are writtenВҰ207161 in the scrollВҰ207164 about the kingsВҰ207165 of YehudahВҰ207166 andВҰ207155 YisraelВҰ207167.
\v 12 \add King\add* AsaВҰ207170 \add вүҲgot a diseaseВҰ207169 the started in\add* his feetВҰ207175 in the thirty-ninth yearВҰ207171 of his reignВҰ207174. \add вүҲEven as it got worse,\add* heВҰ207185 didn'tВҰ207183 \add вүҲtry to get\add* YahwehВҰ207188 \add to help him\add*, only doctors.
\v 13 ThenВҰ207192 AsaВҰ207193 \add вүҲdiedВҰ207197\add* in the forty-first yearВҰ207198 of his reignВҰ207201,
\v 14 and he was buriedВҰ207203 in the tombВҰ207204 that \add вүҲhe'd had carved out\add* in вҖҳThe City of DavidВҰ207210вҖҷ. They laid \add вүҲhis corpse onВҰ207204 a bed of prepared spicesВҰ207215 and perfumesВҰ207218 that had been mixedВҰ207217 ready\add*. ThenВҰ207203 they lit \add вүҲa large bonfire\add* \add in his honour\add*.
\c 17
\s1 Yehoshafat becomes king
\rem /s1 Jehoshaphat Rules in Judah; Jehoshaphat King of Judah; Jehoshaphat's Reign; Jehoshaphat Becomes King
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 1 Then \add @Asa's\add* son YehoshafatВҰ207231 \add (Jehoshaphat)\add* \add вүҲreplaced him as kingВҰ207230\add*, and he strengthenedВҰ207234 \add вүҲtheir defenses\add* against YisraelВҰ207237.
\v 2 He placedВҰ207239 \add вүҲtroops\add* in all of Yehudah'sВҰ207245 fortifiedВҰ207246 cities, and posted garrisonsВҰ207248 across Yehudah and in the cities in Efrayim thatВҰ207253 his fatherВҰ207256 AsaВҰ207255 had capturedВҰ207254.
\v 3 YahwehВҰ207259 \add вүҲhelped\add* YehoshafatВҰ207262 because he followed his ancestor David'sВҰ207266 waysВҰ207265 atВҰ207265 the beginning, andВҰ207258 didn'tВҰ207269 \add вүҲask the BaalsВҰ207271 for guidance\add*,
\v 4 because he \add вүҲasked\add* his father'sВҰ207275 godВҰ207274, and he \add вүҲfollowed God's instructions rather than doing the evil things done inВҰ207277\add* YisraelВҰ207281.
\v 5 \add вүҲSoВҰ207283\add* YahwehВҰ207284 \add вүҲenabled him to maintain control of his\add* kingdomВҰ207287, and the YehudahВҰ207292 broughtВҰ207289 tributeВҰ207293 to YehoshafatВҰ207294, \add вүҲcausing him to become very wealthyВҰ207298 and highly respected\add*.
\v 6 \add вүҲHe was completely devoted to doing what pleased\add* YahwehВҰ207306, even removingВҰ207308 the \add вүҲhilltop shrines\add* andВҰ207303 the Asherah \add polesВҰ207314\add* from YehudahВҰ207315.
\p
\v 7 In the third yearВҰ207318 of his reignВҰ207320 heВҰ207321 sentВҰ207321 his \add вүҲofficialsВҰ207322\add*, Ben-Hayil, Ovadyah, Zekaryah, NetanelВҰ207328, and Mikayah, to teachВҰ207330 inВҰ207331 Yehudah'sВҰ207332 citiesВҰ207331.
\v 8 They were accompanied by the LevitesВҰ207335 ShemayahВҰ207336, Netanyah, Zevadyah, AsahelВҰ207339, ShemiramotВҰ207340, Yehonatan, Adoniyah, Toviyah, and Tov-Adoniyah, along with two priestsВҰ207351 Elishama and YehoramВҰ207350.
\v 9 They \add took\add* a scroll \add вүҲwithВҰ207354 Yahweh's instructions written onВҰ207354 it\add*, andВҰ207353 wentВҰ207359 aroundВҰ207359 Yehudah'sВҰ207354 citiesВҰ207362 teaching the peopleВҰ207365.
\s1 Yehoshafat's rise
\rem /s1 Jehoshaphat's Greatness
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 10 AllВҰ207378 the \add вүҲsurrounding\add* kingdomsВҰ207374 \add вүҲwere afraid\add* of YahwehВҰ207370, \add вүҲso\add* theyВҰ207380 didn'tВҰ207379 \add вүҲattack\add* YehoshafatВҰ207383.
\v 11 \add вүҲSome\add* of the PhilistinesВҰ207387 brought tributeВҰ207390 to Yehoshafat, \add вүҲincluding lots of\add* silverВҰ207391. Also, the ArabiansВҰ207394 brought him flocksВҰ207397 \add totalling\add* 7,700 rams andВҰ207385 7,700 goatsВҰ207403.
\v 12 \add вүҲSo\add* Yehoshafat \add вүҲcontinued to become more powerfulВҰ207413\add*, and heВҰ207413 builtВҰ207417 palaces in YehudahВҰ207418 as well as storehousesВҰ207421 in the citiesВҰ207420.
\v 13 He \add вүҲaccumulated many suppliesВҰ207423\add* in Yehudah'sВҰ207428 citiesВҰ207427.
\p He \add also\add* had \add вүҲmany powerful warriorsВҰ207429\add* in YerushalemВҰ207433.
\v 14 \add вүҲThese are the leaders and numbers from each tribe\add*:
\li1 From the tribe of YehudahВҰ207439, AdnahВҰ207442 was the commanderВҰ207440 and he had three-hundred thousandВҰ207441 warriors,
\li1
\v 15 \add вүҲHis assistant\add* YehohananВҰ207455 commandedВҰ207456 280,000,
\li1
\v 16 \add вүҲNext was\add* Zikri'sВҰ207469 son AmasyahВҰ207466 who volunteeredВҰ207470 for YahwehВҰ207471 and commanded two-hundred thousandВҰ207474 \add вүҲwarriors\add*.
\li1
\v 17 From \add the tribe of\add* BenyaminВҰ207481, Elyada led two-hundred thousandВҰ207491 \add men\add* equippedВҰ207486 with bows and shieldsВҰ207489,
\li1
\v 18 \add вүҲnext to himВҰ207498 was\add* YehozavadВҰ207497 with 180,000 equippedВҰ207503 for war.
\m
\v 19 Those were the \add ones who\add* servedВҰ207508 the king, \add вүҲalong withВҰ207517\add* the \add ones\add* that the king had placed inВҰ207517 Yehudah'sВҰ207521 fortifiedВҰ207518 citiesВҰ207517.
\c 18
\s1 prophet Mikiyas and King Ahab
\rem /s1 Jehoshaphat and Ahab; Micaiah Prophesies Against Ahab; Micaiah Predicts Failure; The Prophet Micaiah Warns Ahab
\s4 Both kingdoms
\r (1 Kgs 22:1-28)
\p
\v 1 \add King\add* YehoshafatВҰ207525 \add вүҲbecame very wealthyВҰ207526 and was highly honouredВҰ207527\add*, \add вүҲbutВҰ207524 then\add* he alliedВҰ207529 himself by marriage to \add Yisrael's King\add* Ahav.
\v 2 \add вүҲSome yearsВҰ207534 later,\add* he went \add вүҲup\add* to Ahav in ShomronВҰ207538 \add (SamariaВҰ207538)\add*, and AhabВҰ207537 sacrificed lots of sheepВҰ207543 and cattleВҰ207544 for him and for the peopleВҰ207546 who were with him, and he incited him to \add вүҲattack\add* RamotВҰ207553-GileadВҰ207554вҖ”
\v 3 Yisrael's King Ahav \add вүҲsuggested to\add* Yehudah'sВҰ207565 King Yehoshafat, вҖңWill you \add вүҲjoin\add* me to \add attack\add* RamotВҰ207568-GileadВҰ207569?вҖқ
\p вҖң\add вүҲWherever you'll be, I'll be there\add*,вҖқ he \add вүҲrespondedВҰ207556\add*. вҖңYour people \add вүҲare like my own\add* people, andВҰ207556 \add we're\add* withВҰ207577 you inВҰ207577 battleВҰ207577.вҖқ
\v 4 \add вүҲThenВҰ207579 he added\add*, вҖң\add вүҲButВҰ207579 we should get Yahweh's advice first\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 \add вүҲSoВҰ207594\add* Yisrael's king gatheredВҰ207594 four hundredВҰ207602 \add of his\add* prophetsВҰ207600 and \add вүҲasked\add* them, вҖңShould we \add вүҲattack\add* RamotВҰ207609-GileadВҰ207610 or not?вҖқ
\p вҖңGo \add вүҲahead\add*,вҖқ they answered, вҖңand God will give \add вүҲvictory to\add* the king.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲButВҰ207622\add* Yehoshafat \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖңIs there no prophetВҰ207626 of YahwehВҰ207627 here that we can \add вүҲask\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 7 The king of YisraelВҰ207635 told YehoshafatВҰ207668, вҖң\add There's\add* stillВҰ207640 one man \add вүҲwho would ask\add* YahwehВҰ207647, \add вүҲbutВҰ207632\add* I myself hate him because \add вүҲhe neverВҰ207653 prophesiesВҰ207654 anything good\add* aboutВҰ207655 meвҖ”\add вүҲit's always something\add* evil. He's Yimlah's son, Mikayah.вҖқ
\p вҖң\add вүҲYou shouldn'tВҰ207669 talk like that\add*,вҖқ said Yehoshafat.
\p
\v 8 \add вүҲSoВҰ207675\add* Yisrael's kingВҰ207676 \add вүҲordered\add* an official, вҖң\add Get\add* Yimlah's son, Mikayah \add here\add* \add вүҲas quickВҰ207683 as possible\add*.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Micaiah Prophesies against Ahab
\p
\v 9 \add вүҲNow\add* the kings of YisraelВҰ207691 and YehudahВҰ207695 were \add both\add* clothedВҰ207701 in their \add royal\add* robes and sitting there on their thronesВҰ207700 near Shomron'sВҰ207707 \add (Samaria'sВҰ207707)\add* entranceВҰ207705 gateВҰ207706. They were \add up\add* on a threshingВҰ207704 floorВҰ207704, and all the prophets were prophesying \add вүҲin frontВҰ207712 of\add* them.
\v 10 Kenaanah'sВҰ207719 son TsidkiyahВҰ207716 made himself some iron hornsВҰ207720 andВҰ207723 saidВҰ207723, вҖңYahwehВҰ207727 saysВҰ207726 that you'll gore AramВҰ207732 withВҰ207728 theseВҰ207728 untilВҰ207733 they're destroyedВҰ207735.вҖқ
\v 11 All the rest of Ahav's prophetsВҰ207739 agreed, saying, вҖң\add Yes,\add* goВҰ207743 and attack RamotВҰ207744-GileadВҰ207745 and you'll succeedвҖ”YahwehВҰ207748 will give the kingВҰ207750 \add вүҲvictory\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 The messengerВҰ207752 who went to fetch Mikayah \add вүҲwarned\add* him, вҖңListen, the kingВҰ207771 \add вүҲis pleasedВҰ207774 with what the other prophetsВҰ207764 agreed on. Just sayВҰ207761 the same as them andВҰ207752 give a favourable messageВҰ207775\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 \add вүҲButВҰ207781\add* Mikayah \add вүҲrespondedВҰ207781\add*, вҖңAs sure as YahwehВҰ207785 lives, I'll only say what my godВҰ207792 tells me to say.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 \add вүҲWhen he got\add* to the king, KingВҰ207799 \add Ahav\add* \add вүҲasked\add* him, вҖңMikayah, should we \add вүҲattack\add* RamotВҰ207807-GileadВҰ207808 for battleВҰ207809, or should I \add вүҲhold back\add*?вҖқ
\p вҖңGo \add вүҲahead\add* andВҰ207796 succeed,вҖқ he \add вүҲanswered\add*. вҖң\add вүҲYou'll be givenВҰ207816 victory over them\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 \add вүҲButВҰ207819\add* the kingВҰ207821 saidВҰ207819 to him, вҖңHow many timesВҰ207825 must I keeping making you promise that you'll \add вүҲonly say what YahwehВҰ207837 saysвҖ”not just what I want to hear\add*?вҖқ
\v 16 \add вүҲSoВҰ207839\add* \add @Mikayah\add* \add вүҲrespondedВҰ207839\add*, вҖңI saw all YisraelВҰ207845 scatteredВҰ207846 onВҰ207866 the hills like sheepВҰ207850 without shepherdsВҰ207855, andВҰ207839 YahwehВҰ207857 said, вҖҳ\add вүҲThey don'tВҰ207852 have any masterВҰ207860, so they'll all just go homeВҰ207865\add* inВҰ207866 peaceВҰ207866.вҖҷ вҖқ\x + \xo 18:16: \xt Num 27:17; Eze 34:5; Mat 9:36; Mrk 6:34.\x*
\p
\v 17 \add вүҲAhav remarked\add* to YehoshafatВҰ207874, вҖңDidn't I tell you that he wouldn't prophesyВҰ207880 anything goodВҰ207882 aboutВҰ207881 meвҖ”only \add вүҲdisasterВҰ207886\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 18 \add вүҲButВҰ207889\add* \add @Mikayah\add* \add вүҲcontinuedВҰ207889\add*, вҖң\add вүҲWell, listenВҰ207891 to what Yahweh says\add*. I sawВҰ207895 Yahweh sittingВҰ207899 on his throneВҰ207902 and all the \add вүҲheavenlyВҰ207906 soldiers\add* standingВҰ207907 on \add вүҲeach side of him\add*,
\v 19 and YahwehВҰ207914 said, вҖҳWho'll entice Yisrael's KingВҰ207920 AhabВҰ207919 so he'll \add вүҲattack\add* and thenВҰ207913 he'll fall atВҰ207925 Ramot-Gilead?вҖҷ \add вүҲSome suggested one thing, and others suggested something else\add*.
\v 20 ThenВҰ207935 \add ?вүҲa\add* spiritВҰ207936 wentВҰ207935 out, and stoodВҰ207937 \add вүҲinВҰ207946 frontВҰ207938 of\add* Yahweh and said, вҖҳI myself will enticeВҰ207942 him.вҖҷ вҖҳ\add вүҲHow would you do it\add*?вҖҷ Yahweh \add вүҲasked\add* him.
\v 21 \add @The spirit\add* \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖҳI'll go and \add вүҲinspire all Ahav's prophetsВҰ207956 to tell lies\add*.вҖҷ Yahweh said, вҖҳ\add вүҲThat'll work\add*. Go and do it.вҖҷ
\p
\v 22 вҖң\add вүҲSoВҰ207967\add* now, listen. Yahweh placed a deceiving spiritВҰ207971 inВҰ207973 the mouthВҰ207973 of those prophetsВҰ207974 of yours, andВҰ207976 Yahweh \add вүҲhas decreed that you'll face\add* disaster.вҖқ
\p
\v 23 Then Kenaanah'sВҰ207986 son Tsidkiyah \add вүҲwentВҰ207982 up to\add* Mikayah \add вүҲand slapped him hard\add* on the cheekВҰ207993, saying, вҖң\add Yeah!\add* \add вүҲSince when did Yahweh's spiritВҰ207999 leave me and start speakingВҰ208003 to\add* youВҰ208004?вҖқ
\p
\v 24 вҖңWell, you'll find out \add soon\add*,вҖқ answered Mikayah, вҖңonВҰ208015 the dayВҰ208010 when you go room by room \add inВҰ208015 some house\add* to \add вүҲtry to hide\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 25 вҖң\add вүҲArrest\add* Mikayah,вҖқ \add вүҲordered KingВҰ208019 Ahav\add*, вҖңand returnВҰ208025 himВҰ208025 to AmonВҰ208028 the cityВҰ208031 \add вүҲgovernor\add*, and to \add вүҲmy\add* son YoashВҰ208034.
\v 26 \add вүҲTell them that the king's ordered that this man be put inВҰ208054 prisonВҰ208046, and be given only strictly-rationed breadВҰ208048 and waterВҰ208050 untilВҰ208052 I returnВҰ208053 safely\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 27 вҖңIf youВҰ208061 return \add вүҲsafely\add*,вҖқ Mikayah \add вүҲretorted\add*, вҖңthenВҰ208056 YahwehВҰ208066 mustn't have spokenВҰ208065 to me.вҖқ
\s1 The death of Ahab
\rem /s1 Ahab Killed at Ramoth Gilead; The Death of Ahab; Defeat and Death of Ahab
\s4 Both kingdoms
\r (1 Kgs 22:29-35)
\p
\v 28 \add вүҲSo\add* Yisrael's KingВҰ208075 \add Ahav\add* and Yehudah'sВҰ208081 king YehoshafatВҰ208078 went to RamotВҰ208084-GileadВҰ208085.
\v 29 \add вүҲAhav\add* told Yehoshafat, вҖң\add вүҲI'll get changed\add* \add so I'm not recognised\add*, and go into the battle, \add вүҲbutВҰ208087 you wear your royal robe\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ208087\add* Yisrael's king disguisedВҰ208093 himself, and they wentВҰ208102 into the battle.
\p
\v 30 \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* Aram'sВҰ208106 king had orderedВҰ208107 his chariotВҰ208111 commandersВҰ208107, вҖңOnly attack Yisrael's kingвҖ”\add вүҲdon'tВҰ208116 bother fighting anyone else\add*.вҖқ
\v 31 \add вүҲHowever,\add* when \add &those\add* chariotВҰ208136 commandersВҰ208135 sawВҰ208134 \add KingВҰ208142\add* Yehoshafat, they \add вүҲmistook him for\add* Yisrael's kingВҰ208142 and \add вүҲwheeled\add* around to fightВҰ208147 him, \add вүҲbutВҰ208133\add* Yehoshafat criedВҰ208148 out \add to YahwehВҰ208150 for help\add* and \add *he\add* helpedВҰ208151 himвҖ”GodВҰ208153 drew them away from him
\v 32 \add вүҲbecause\add* when the chariotВҰ208159 commandersВҰ208158 \add вүҲrealisedВҰ208157\add* that it wasn't the kingВҰ208164 of YisraelВҰ208165, they turnedВҰ208166 back from \add chasingВҰ208167\add* him.
\v 33 \add вүҲHowever,\add* one \add Aramean\add* \add вүҲwarrior drew his bow without knowing where Ahav was\add*, and struckВҰ208173 Yisrael's kingВҰ208176 \add вүҲatВҰ208171 a joint inВҰ208171 his\add* armour. \add @Ahav\add* \add вүҲordered\add* the charioteerВҰ208183, вҖңTurn \add вүҲaroundВҰ208184 and get me out of here\add*, because I've been seriously woundedВҰ208192.вҖқ
\v 34 The battleВҰ208195 \add вүҲcontinued\add* all that dayВҰ208196, andВҰ208194 Yisrael's kingВҰ208198 was propped up inВҰ208202 his chariotВҰ208202 \add вүҲto watch\add* the ArameansВҰ208204, \add вүҲbutВҰ208194 he diedВҰ208208 as the sunВҰ208211 was setting\add*.
\c 19
\s1 Yehoshafat gets scolded
\rem /s1 A Prophet Reprimands Jehoshaphat; Jehoshaphat Appoints Judges
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 1 Yehudah'sВҰ208217 kingВҰ208215 YehoshafatВҰ208214 returnedВҰ208213 safely to his home inВҰ208221 YerushalemВҰ208222,
\v 2 \add вүҲbutВҰ208224\add* Hanani'sВҰ208231 son, the prophet YehuВҰ208228 \add вүҲconfronted\add* him, вҖңShould you have helped the wickedВҰ208238, andВҰ208224 befriended those that Yahweh hates? Yahweh's angry withВҰ208243 you because of what you've done.
\v 3 \add вүҲHowever, you have some goodВҰ208251 points\add* because you removedВҰ208256 the Asherah \add polesВҰ208257\add* from the \add вүҲcountry\add* and \add вүҲyou've been sincere in wanting to follow\add* God.вҖқ
\s1 The neneyimu of Hihusapat
\rem /s1 The Reforms of Jehoshaphat; Jehoshaphat's Reforms; Jehoshaphat Appoints Judges
\p
\v 4 Yehoshafat lived in YerushalemВҰ208268 \add вүҲbutВҰ208266\add* one time he wentВҰ208271 out to the peopleВҰ208272 of Beer-Sheva in the Efrayim hill countryВҰ208277 andВҰ208266 \add вүҲencouraged\add* them back to YahwehВҰ208282, the godВҰ208283 of theirВҰ208284 ancestorsВҰ208284.
\v 5 He appointedВҰ208286 judgesВҰ208287 in Yehudah'sВҰ208292 fortifiedВҰ208293 citiesВҰ208291 \add вүҲto serve across the country\add*,
\v 6 andВҰ208312 he told them, вҖң\add вүҲTakeВҰ208308 care inВҰ208313 what you all do, because you're not serving men as judgesВҰ208300, butВҰ208297 serving YahwehВҰ208311 when you make judicial decisions\add*.
\v 7 \add вүҲSoВҰ208316 revere Yahweh andВҰ208316 judge cases carefully, because ourВҰ208330 godВҰ208330 Yahweh doesn't tolerate injusticeВҰ208331, partialityВҰ208332, or briberyВҰ208336\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 YehoshafatВҰ208341 also appointedВҰ208340 some LevitesВҰ208344 andВҰ208338 priestsВҰ208345 in Yerushalem, as well as \add вүҲleaders\add* from some IsraeliВҰ208348 familiesВҰ208347 to be judgesВҰ208349 \add вүҲonВҰ208339 Yahweh's behalf based in\add* Yerushalem,
\v 9 and he \add вүҲinstructedВҰ208355\add* them, вҖңYou all \add вүҲmust revere YahwehВҰ208361 and be trustworthy and sincere\add*.
\v 10 When any of your \add вүҲfellow Israelis\add* who liveВҰ208375 inВҰ208376 the citiesВҰ208376 bring any case to you \add вүҲinvolving violent crime, interpreting laws or regulationsВҰ208386, etc., you must caution them so theyВҰ208391 won't sin against YahwehВҰ208392 and induce his angerВҰ208395 to comeВҰ208371 onВҰ208376 you all or them, so do thatВҰ208369 and you won't be guilty\add*.
\v 11 And listen, the chiefВҰ208408 priestВҰ208407 AmaryahВҰ208406 is over you all in any \add вүҲreligious\add* matter, and Yishmael'sВҰ208417 son Zevady is the leader of \add вүҲYehudahВҰ208421\add* for any \add вүҲcivil\add* matter \add вүҲconcerning\add* the kingВҰ208425. \add вүҲAlso\add* you have the LeviteВҰ208427 officialsВҰ208426 to assist you all. \add вүҲAct with courage and let YahwehВҰ208413 assist those doing what's right\add*.вҖқ
\c 20
\s1 Yehoshafat handles a massive invasion
\rem /s1 War against Edom; Invasion from the East; War with Moab, Ammon, and Edom; Jehoshaphat Defeats Moab and Ammon
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲSometime afterВҰ208439 that,\add* the Moabites and Ammonites, along with some of the MeunitesВҰ208450\f + \fr 20:1 \ft Following the Septuagint for this.\f*, cameВҰ208442 to battleВҰ208454 against \add King\add* YehoshafatВҰ208453.
\v 2 \add Some men\add* cameВҰ208456 and told Yehoshafat, вҖңA \add вүҲhugeВҰ208463 army\add* is comingВҰ208460 from Aram beyondВҰ208464 the \add Dead\add* seaВҰ208465 to attack youВҰ208461, and take note: they're \add already\add* inВҰ208468 Hatstson-Tamar, also known as Eyn-Gedi.вҖқ
\v 3 YehoshafatВҰ208476 \add вүҲwas alarmed and decided to request advice from\add* YahwehВҰ208481, and he \add вүҲordered that all YehudahВҰ208489 should fast\add*.
\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ208491\add* Yehudah assembledВҰ208491 to \add вүҲrequest Yahweh's help\add*вҖ”theyВҰ208500 cameВҰ208500 to Yerushalem from all of Yehudah'sВҰ208492 citiesВҰ208498 to \add вүҲask Yahweh for help\add*.
\rem /s1 Jehoshaphat's Prayer and Victory
\p
\v 5 Yehoshafat stoodВҰ208506 in front of all the people from YerushalemВҰ208510 andВҰ208510 across YehudahВҰ208509, in front of the new temple courtyardВҰ208514
\v 6 and \add вүҲprayed\add*, вҖңYahwehВҰ208518, the god of our ancestorsВҰ208520, aren'tВҰ208521 you the god \add who lives\add* in the heavensВҰ208526? And you rule in all the kingdomsВҰ208530 \add вүҲaround the world\add*, and \add вүҲyou have full powerВҰ208533 and control\add*вҖ”no one can standВҰ208537 againstВҰ208536 you.
\v 7 Weren't you our godВҰ208542 who drove the previous inhabitantsВҰ208546 of this land out ahead of your Israeli peopleВҰ208550? Didn't you giveВҰ208552 itВҰ208552 to the descendantsВҰ208553 of AbrahamВҰ208554вҖ”the one you loved foreverВҰ208556?\x + \xo 20:7: \xt Isa 41:8; Jam 2:23.\x*
\v 8 \add @Our ancestors\add* livedВҰ208558 inВҰ208560 \add @this land\add* andВҰ208561 theyВҰ208558 builtВҰ208561 a \add вүҲtemple to honour you\add*, saying,
\v 9 вҖҳIf disaster \add like\add* \add вүҲwar\add*, judgementВҰ208575, or epidemic, or famineВҰ208577 comes onВҰ208586 us, we'll standВҰ208578 \add вүҲin front of\add* this \add вүҲtemple\add*, and \add вүҲin front of\add* you, because yourВҰ208583 nameВҰ208585 is \add вүҲhonoured here\add*. And we will cryВҰ208588 to you from our distressВҰ208590, and you will hearВҰ208591 and deliver.вҖҷ
\p
\v 10 You didn't allow our Israeli ancestors to enter the countries of AmmonВҰ208598, MoabВҰ208599, or Edom when they were travelling from EgyptВҰ208612 \add to Canaan\add*. SoВҰ208594 our ancestors turnedВҰ208614 away from those areas andВҰ208594 didn't destroyВҰ208617 them, butВҰ208594 now they \add are coming here to attack us\add*.\x + \xo 20:10: \xt Deu 2:4-19.\x*
\v 11 Look how they're repayingВҰ208622 us \add for not destroying them\add*вҖ”they come \add here\add* to driveВҰ208625 us out from the \add вүҲland\add* thatВҰ208627 you gaveВҰ208628 us as an inheritanceВҰ208628.
\v 12 \add So,\add* our godВҰ208630, \add вүҲplease punish\add* them, because \add вүҲwe're not strong enough to battle this hugeВҰ208641 army that's onВҰ208634 its way\add*. \add вүҲWe simply don'tВҰ208631 knowВҰ208647 what to do, so we're looking to you to rescue us\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 \add At that time,\add* all of YehudahВҰ208657 (men, women, andВҰ208665 childrenВҰ208665) were standingВҰ208658 \add вүҲin frontВҰ208659 of\add* YahwehВҰ208660
\v 14 and Yahweh's spiritВҰ208688 came on Yahaziel. (Yahaziel was the son of Zekaryah, son of BenayahВҰ208674, son of YeielВҰ208677, son of MattanyahВҰ208680 the LeviteВҰ208681 and a descendantВҰ208684 of AsafВҰ208685.) In the middleВҰ208690 of the assemblyВҰ208691
\v 15 he saidВҰ208693, вҖң\add вүҲPay\add* attentionВҰ208694, all YehudahВҰ208697 and inhabitantsВҰ208698 of YerushalemВҰ208699 and KingВҰ208700 YehoshafatВҰ208701. YahwehВҰ208705 has this to say to you all, вҖҳDon't be afraidВҰ208710, and don'tВҰ208708 be dismayedВҰ208713 by this \add вүҲhugeВҰ208716 force\add*, because it's not your battleВҰ208721 butВҰ208693 God's.\x + \xo 20:15-17: \xt Deu 20:1-4.\x*
\v 16 TomorrowВҰ208725, goВҰ208726 down againstВҰ208727 them. Listen, they're comingВҰ208729 uphill near the Ascent of Tsits, andВҰ208732 you'll all find them atВҰ208730 the endВҰ208734 of the valleyВҰ208735, facing the YeruelВҰ208738 wildernessВҰ208737.
\v 17 You all won'tВҰ208754 \add need\add* to fightВҰ208742 \add вүҲthem\add*вҖ”\add вүҲJust takeВҰ208744 your positions all of you from YerushalemВҰ208753 and wider YehudahВҰ208752, and watch Yahweh save you\add*. Don't \add вүҲbe afraidВҰ208756 or discouraged\add*. Go out \add вүҲthere\add* tomorrowВҰ208760 and Yahweh will be withВҰ208743 you all.вҖҷ вҖқ\x + \xo 20:17: \xt Exo 14:13-14.\x*
\p
\v 18 ThenВҰ208766 \add King\add* Yehoshafat bowedВҰ208766 with his face to the groundВҰ208769, and all \add the people from\add* YerushalemВҰ208774 and across YehudahВҰ208772 fell \add to their knees\add* in frontВҰ208776 of YahwehВҰ208777 to worshipВҰ208778 \add *him\add*.
\v 19 ThenВҰ208781 \add some of\add* the LevitesВҰ208782 who were descendants of Kohat andВҰ208787 Korah, stoodВҰ208781 up to \add вүҲloudly\add* praiseВҰ208791 Yisrael's godВҰ208793 YahwehВҰ208792.
\p
\v 20 They rose earlyВҰ208799 the \add next\add* morningВҰ208800 and went out to the TekoaВҰ208803 wildernessВҰ208802, and \add вүҲas they were leaving\add* Yehoshafat stoodВҰ208805 and \add вүҲcalled out\add*, вҖңHear me, inhabitantsВҰ208810 of YerushalemВҰ208811 and YehudahВҰ208809. Believe inВҰ208800 \add вүҲour\add* godВҰ208814 Yahweh, and be \add вүҲconfident\add*. Believe his prophetsВҰ208817 and succeedВҰ208818.вҖқ
\v 21 ThenВҰ208820 he consulted withВҰ208831 the peopleВҰ208823, and he appointedВҰ208824 some to sing to Yahweh and some to praiseВҰ208827 \add вүҲhim for his splendourВҰ208828 and sinlessness\add* as they wentВҰ208831 out before the \add enemy\add* army, and they were sayingВҰ208834, вҖңGive thanksВҰ208835 to Yahweh, because his loyal commitment \add endures\add* foreverВҰ208838.вҖқ
\p
\v 22 As they beganВҰ208842 to sing and praiseВҰ208844 YahwehВҰ208846, he sent ambushersВҰ208848 againstВҰ208858 the \add вүҲAmmonites, Moabites, and Edomites\add* who were attacking YehudahВҰ208858, and they were defeatedВҰ208859.
\v 23 ThenВҰ208861 the \add вүҲAmmonites and Moabites turned onВҰ208874 the Edomites and completely annihilatedВҰ208872 them\add*, and \add вүҲafter that\add* they \add вүҲslaughtered each other\add*.
\v 24 \add вүҲWhen the men of Yehudah arrived at the place overlooking the wildernessВҰ208887, wowВҰ208892, theyВҰ208892 saw corpsesВҰ208893 all over the ground\add*. No one had escapedВҰ208897.
\p
\v 25 ThenВҰ208899 YehoshafatВҰ208900 and his peopleВҰ208901 wentВҰ208899 to plunder the spoils, and they foundВҰ208906 lots of goodsВҰ208909 among them, as well as clothing,\f + \fr 20:25 \ft The Hebrew вҖҳbodies/corpsesвҖҷ seems wrong here.\f* and valuable items. They took that for themselves \add вүҲuntilВҰ208915 there was nothing left to\add* carryВҰ208916 awayвҖ”there was \add вүҲso much plunder that it took threeВҰ208919 daysВҰ208918 to collect it all\add*.
\v 26 On the fourthВҰ208930 day, they assembledВҰ208931 inВҰ208929 the Berakah valley andВҰ208929 they praised YahwehВҰ208940 thereВҰ208936. That's why it's calledВҰ208944 Berakah valley \add (which means вҖҳpraise/blessingВҰ208937вҖҷ)\add* to this day.
\v 27 ThenВҰ208956 all the men from Yerushalem andВҰ208956 \add across\add* YehudahВҰ208960 returnedВҰ208956 to Yerushalem withВҰ208963 \add King\add* Yehoshafat \add вүҲleading them\add*вҖ”celebrating because YahwehВҰ208972 had enabled them to defeat their enemiesВҰ208973.
\v 28 \add вүҲWhenВҰ208983\add* they arrived atВҰ208977 YerushalemВҰ208976, they wentВҰ208975 to the \add вүҲtemple\add*, \add playing\add* harpsВҰ208977, lutes, andВҰ208975 trumpetsВҰ208979.
\v 29 The nearby kingdomsВҰ208991 \add вүҲwere all very afraid of\add* GodВҰ208987 when theyВҰ208993 heardВҰ208993 that YahwehВҰ208996 had foughtВҰ208995 withВҰ208993 Yisrael's enemiesВҰ208998,
\v 30 \add вүҲso\add* Yehoshafat'sВҰ209003 kingdomВҰ209002 was untroubled andВҰ209004 his godВҰ209006 gaveВҰ209004 him \add вүҲpeaceВҰ209001 from all his neighbours\add*.
\s1 The end of Yehoshafat's kingdom
\rem /s1 The End of Jehoshaphat's Reign; Summary of Jehoshaphat's Reign
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (1 Kgs 22:41-50)
\p
\v 31 Yehoshafat was thirty-five \add вүҲyears old\add* when he becameВҰ209020 kingВҰ209020, and he reigned over YehudahВҰ209014 from YerushalemВҰ209025 for twenty-five years. His motherВҰ209027 was Shilhi'sВҰ209031 daughterВҰ209029, Azuvah.
\v 32 He \add вүҲhad similar priorities to his fatherВҰ209035 AsaВҰ209036, doingВҰ209041 what pleased\add* YahwehВҰ209044, andВҰ209033 he didn'tВҰ209037 \add вүҲdeviate\add* from that.
\v 33 \add However,\add* he never removedВҰ209050 the hilltop shrines, and the peopleВҰ209052 \add вүҲwere not really serious about obeying the godВҰ209057 of their ancestorsВҰ209058\add*.
\p
\v 34 \add вүҲEverything else thatВҰ209072 YehoshafatВҰ209062 did from the beginning to the end\add* \add of his reign\add* was writtenВҰ209066 down by Hanani'sВҰ209071 son YehuВҰ209068 inВҰ209067 the scrollВҰ209076 about Yisrael's kingsВҰ209077.
\p
\v 35 \add вүҲLater on,\add* Yehudah'sВҰ209087 King Yehoshafat \add вүҲmade an allianceВҰ209083\add* with Yisrael's King AhazyahВҰ209089 (which was a wickedВҰ209094 thing to do),
\v 36 andВҰ209097 they worked together to make ships atВҰ209105 Etsyon-Gever to sail to TarshishВҰ209102.
\v 37 ThenВҰ209108 Dodavahu'sВҰ209112 son EliezerВҰ209109 from MareshahВҰ209113 prophesiedВҰ209108 against Yehoshafat, saying, вҖңWhen you allied yourself with AhazyahВҰ209121, YahwehВҰ209123 broke through yourВҰ209126 works.вҖқ \add вүҲIn due course,\add* the shipsВҰ209128 were damaged andВҰ209108 unable to \add вүҲsail\add* to TarshishВҰ209134.
\c 21
\rem /s1 Jehoram Rules in Judah; Jehoram's Reign
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ209136 Yehoshafat \add вүҲdied and was buriedВҰ209141 withВҰ209145 his ancestorsВҰ209140\add* inВҰ209145 вҖҳThe City of DavidВҰ209146вҖҷ, and his son YehoramВҰ209148 \add (Jehoram)\add* \add вүҲreplaced him as kingВҰ209147\add*.
\s1 Yehudah's King Yehoram
\rem /s1 King Jehoram of Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Kgs 8:17-24)
\p
\v 2 \add @Yehoram's\add* \add younger\add* brothersВҰ209154 were Azaryah, Yehiel, Zekaryah, Azaryah, Mikael, andВҰ209152 Shefatyah,
\v 3 and theirВҰ209175 fatherВҰ209175 gave them many giftsВҰ209176 of goldВҰ209179 and silverВҰ209178 and precious things, along withВҰ209185 fortifiedВҰ209184 citiesВҰ209183 inВҰ209185 YehudahВҰ209185, \add вүҲhowever\add* he \add вүҲhanded\add* the kingdomВҰ209188 over to YehoramВҰ209190 because he was the oldest \add son\add*.
\rem /s1 Jehoram King of Judah
\v 4 \add вүҲAfter YehoramВҰ209198 established firm control\add* of his father'sВҰ209202 kingdomВҰ209201, he had all his brothersВҰ209209 killedВҰ209204, as well as some of Yisrael's leaders.
\p
\v 5 YehoramВҰ209220 was thirty-two \add вүҲyears old\add* when he becameВҰ209221 the kingВҰ209221, and he ruled from YerushalemВҰ209225 for eightВҰ209222 years.
\v 6 He did \add many of the evil things\add* that Yisrael's kingsВҰ209230 had done, because \add вүҲhe married one\add* of \add King\add* Ahav's daughtersВҰ209237 andВҰ209227 did things that YahwehВҰ209246 \add вүҲhad said\add* were evil.
\v 7 \add вүҲDespite thatВҰ209259,\add* YahwehВҰ209251 wouldn't \add вүҲeliminate\add* David'sВҰ209256 descendantsВҰ209267 because of the \add вүҲpromise he'd made\add* with David to вҖҳkeep his lamp burningвҖҷ forever.\x + \xo 21:7: \xt 1Ki 11:36.\x*
\rem /s1 Revolt of Edom
\p
\v 8 \add Meanwhile, EdomВҰ209274 had been\add* underВҰ209275 Yehudah'sВҰ209278 control, butВҰ209279 \add вүҲduring Yehoram's reign\add* they rebelledВҰ209273 and \add вүҲappointed theirВҰ209280 own\add* king.\x + \xo 21:8: \xt Gen 27:40.\x*
\v 9 YehoramВҰ209284 took his commanders and all his chariots, and crossedВҰ209283 \add the Yorden River\add*, thenВҰ209283 \add вүҲat nighttimeВҰ209294\add* he attacked the Edomites who had surrounded him and his chariots.\f + \fr 21:9 \ft The meaning of the second half of this sentence is confusing, so other translations might differ.\f*
\v 10 \add вүҲHowever,\add* EdomВҰ209306 \add successfully\add* rebelledВҰ209315 against \add вүҲcontrol by\add* YehudahВҰ209310, thenВҰ209305 Livnah \add вүҲalso did the same\add*, because \add @Yehoram\add* had abandonedВҰ209322 YahwehВҰ209325, the godВҰ209326 of his ancestorsВҰ209327.
\rem /s1 Elijah's Letter
\v 11 Also he built hilltop shrines around Yehudah, and he caused Yerushalem'sВҰ209341 inhabitantsВҰ209340 to prostitute themselves,\f + \fr 21:11 \ft This sentence is about worship, not physical adultery, so the reference to prostitution most likely refers to idol worship. Also see verse 13 below.\f* and he drove Yehudah away \add from Yahweh\add*.
\p
\v 12 Then \add @King Yehoram\add* received a written message from the prophetВҰ209352 EliyahВҰ209351 \add (ElijahВҰ209351)\add*: вҖңYour father David'sВҰ209359 godВҰ209358 YahwehВҰ209357 says that becauseВҰ209361 you \add decided\add* not to \add вүҲfollow\add* the ways of your father YehoshafatВҰ209367 or those of \add good\add* King AsaВҰ209370,
\v 13 butВҰ209375 rather you \add вүҲimitated the behaviour of\add* Yisrael's king, thenВҰ209375 \add вүҲyou've caused\add* Yerushalem'sВҰ209386 inhabitsВҰ209385 as well as \add wider\add* YehudahВҰ209382 to commit adultery like Ahab'sВҰ209389 \add вүҲfamily did\add*. Also, you've killedВҰ209399 \add вүҲyour own blood brothersВҰ209393\add*вҖ”people who were betterВҰ209397 than you.
\v 14 \add вүҲSo listen, now\add* YahwehВҰ209402 is going to severely strikeВҰ209403 your peopleВҰ209406 including your sonsВҰ209407 and your wivesВҰ209408, as well as all your possessionsВҰ209411,
\v 15 andВҰ209413 you yourself will \add вүҲget an intestinal disease that will get worse every day untilВҰ209418 your innids\add* fall out.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 ThenВҰ209430 YahwehВҰ209431 stirredВҰ209430 the PhilistinesВҰ209437 up against YehoramВҰ209434, as well as the ArabsВҰ209438 who \add вүҲlived beside\add* the KushitesВҰ209443,
\v 17 and they attacked YehudahВҰ209446. They \add вүҲdid a lot of damage\add* and took away everything valuable from the king's palace. They also took his wivesВҰ209460 and sonsВҰ209459, other than YehoahazВҰ209469, his youngestВҰ209470 son.
\rem /s1 Disease and Death of Jehoram
\p
\v 18 After that, YahwehВҰ209478 caused an intestinal diseaseВҰ209481 inВҰ209480 Yehoram that couldn't be cured,
\v 19 and it \add вүҲprogressed day after day until after two yearsВҰ209492, his intestines fell out and he died in great pain\add*. His peopleВҰ209506 didn'tВҰ209502 make a \add вүҲbonfire in his honour\add* like they'd done for his ancestorsВҰ209509.
\p
\v 20 \add @Yehoram\add* was thirty-two when he becameВҰ209516 kingВҰ209516, and he ruled from YerushalemВҰ209520 for eightВҰ209517 yearsВҰ209518. No one regretted it when he died, and his body was buriedВҰ209524 in вҖҳThe City of DavidВҰ209526вҖҷ, butВҰ209514 not in the \add вүҲroyal tombsВҰ209528\add*.
\c 22
\s1 Yehudah's king Ahazyah
\rem /s1 Ahaziah's Reign; Ahaziah Rules in Judah; King Ahaziah of Judah; Ahaziah King of Judah
\s4 Both kingdoms
\r (2 Kgs 8:25-29; 9:21-28)
\p
\v 1 The inhabitantsВҰ209532 of YerushalemВҰ209533 made his youngest son Ahazyah\f + \fr 22:1 \ft Called Yehoahaz in 21:17 above. (Replace вҖҳYehoвҖҷ at the front with вҖҳYahвҖҷ at the endвҖ”the meaning вҖҳYahweh has heldвҖҷ remains the same.)\f* king in his placeВҰ209539, because all \add вүҲhis olderВҰ209543 brothers had been killedВҰ209544 by the ArabВҰ209547 invaders\add*. \add вүҲSoВҰ209531\add* Yehoram'sВҰ209553 son Ahazyah reignedВҰ209549 as Yehudah'sВҰ209555 king.
\v 2 \add *He\add* was twenty-two\f + \fr 22:2 \ft The Hebrew has forty-two here, but we've corrected it from 2 Kgs 8:26.\f* when he becameВҰ209564 kingВҰ209564, and he reignedВҰ209567 from YerushalemВҰ209568 for one yearВҰ209565. His motherВҰ209570 was Atalyah, a \add вүҲgranddaughter\add* of Yisrael's \add KingВҰ209564\add* OmriВҰ209574.
\v 3 \add @King Ahazyah\add* \add вүҲbehaved just like\add* \add King\add* Ahav's family had done because his motherВҰ209584 \add вүҲgave him evil advice\add*,
\v 4 \add вүҲso\add* he did \add вүҲwhat YahwehВҰ209592 had said was evilВҰ209590\add* just like Ahav'sВҰ209594 family, because afterВҰ209602 his father'sВҰ209604 deathВҰ209603, they had become \add @Ahazyah's\add* advisors, \add вүҲgiving destructiveВҰ209605 suggestions\add*.
\v 5 He \add вүҲfollowed theirВҰ209609 advice and joined\add* \add King\add* Yehoram (son of Yisrael's King Ahav) to fight against Aram'sВҰ209626 King HazaelВҰ209623 atВҰ209609 Ramot-Gilead, where Yehoram was woundedВҰ209629 by the ArameansВҰ209626.
\v 6 YehoramВҰ209652 returnedВҰ209635 to Yizreel to recover because he'd been woundedВҰ209639 atВҰ209637 RamahВҰ209642 inВҰ209637 the battle against Aram'sВҰ209648 King HazaelВҰ209646. SoВҰ209635 Yehudah'sВҰ209654 King AhazyahВҰ209649 wentВҰ209655 \add вүҲup\add* to Yizreel to seeВҰ209656 Yehoram.
\p
\v 7 GodВҰ209669 \add вүҲcaused Ahazyah'sВҰ209672 downfallВҰ209671 through\add* his visit to Yehoram. When \add @Ahaziah\add* arrived, he wentВҰ209677 withВҰ209677 Yehoram to meet Nimshi'sВҰ209687 son YehuВҰ209684, who YahwehВҰ209690 had appointed to killВҰ209691 all of Ahav's descendants.
\v 8 \add вүҲWhile YehuВҰ209699 was executingВҰ209698 judgementВҰ209698 on Ahav's descendants\add*, he discovered Yehudah'sВҰ209708 officialsВҰ209707 there, including Ahazyah'sВҰ209711 nephews who'd been servingВҰ209712 him, andВҰ209697 he killedВҰ209714 them \add all as well\add*.
\v 9 ThenВҰ209716 Yehu went searching for Ahazyah and found him hidingВҰ209722 inВҰ209723 ShomronВҰ209723 \add (SamariaВҰ209723) city\add*. They capturedВҰ209720 him and took him to Yehu, and killed him. They did bury him, because they saidВҰ209731, вҖңHe was \add вүҲthe grandson\add* of \add King\add* YehoshafatВҰ209734 who \add вүҲtried hard to please\add* YahwehВҰ209741.вҖқ \add вүҲAfter that,\add* there were no \add вүҲdescendants of Ahazyah who were powerful enough to become Yehudah's king\add*.
\s1
\rem /s1 Athaliah Rules in Judah; Athaliah Seizes the Throne; Queen Athaliah of Judah; Athaliah and Joash
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Kgs 11:1-3)
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲWhen\add* Ahazyah'sВҰ209754 motherВҰ209753 Atalyah found out that herВҰ209758 son had died, sheВҰ209755 \add вүҲtook action\add* andВҰ209752 destroyedВҰ209760 all the \add вүҲhis family members who could become king\add* of YehudahВҰ209768.
\v 11 \add вүҲHowever, a princess named\add* Yehoshaveat took Ahazyah's son YoashВҰ209777, and she \add вүҲsneaked him away from amongВҰ209783\add* the king's sons who were about to be killed, and she hid him and his nurseВҰ209792 inВҰ209793 a bedroom. Yehoshaveat was the daughter of \add the late\add* KingВҰ209774 YehoramВҰ209800, the wife of Yehoyada the priestВҰ209803 (she was Ahazyah's sisterВҰ209807), \add and she\add* hid him from Atalyah \add вүҲso she couldn't\add* kill him.
\v 12 He \add вүҲstayed in hidingВҰ209818 with them in the temple\add* for sixВҰ209819 yearsВҰ209820 \add вүҲwhile\add* Atalyah ruled over \add вүҲYehudah\add*.
\c 23
\s1 The making of Hihuyada to Huwas King of Yehudah
\rem /s1 Revolt against Athaliah; The Revolt against Athaliah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Kgs 11:4-16)
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲThe following yearВҰ209828\add*, \add the priest\add* Yehoyada \add вүҲtookВҰ209832 courage\add* and made an agreement withВҰ209828 the commandersВҰ209835 of units of one hundredВҰ209836 \add soldiers\add*: Azaryah (Yehoram's son), YishmaelВҰ209841 (Yehohanan'sВҰ209844 son), \add another\add* Azaryah (Oved's son), MaaseyahВҰ209851 (Adayah'sВҰ209854 son), and ElishafatВҰ209857 (Zikri'sВҰ209860 son).
\v 2 They wentВҰ209864 throughout YehudahВҰ209865 and gatheredВҰ209866 all the LevitesВҰ209869 and the \add вүҲclan leaders\add* from all the citiesВҰ209872. \add вүҲWhen\add* theyВҰ209877 cameВҰ209877 to YerushalemВҰ209880,
\v 3 all the assemblyВҰ209885 \add вүҲmade an agreement\add* with the \add young\add* king in the \add вүҲtemple\add*, andВҰ209882 \add @Yehoyada\add* told them, вҖңListenВҰ209888, the \add late\add* king's son will reignВҰ209898, just as YahwehВҰ209901 said concerning David'sВҰ209905 descendants.\x + \xo 23:3: \xt 2Sam 7:12.\x*
\v 4 \add Now\add* this is what all of you need to do: one thirdВҰ209911 of you priestsВҰ209915 andВҰ209916 LevitesВҰ209916 who are on duty on the Rest Day, must guard the \add temple\add* \add вүҲentrances\add*.
\v 5 Another third of you \add вүЎmust guard\add* the king's \add вүҲpalace\add*, and the \add final\add* third \add вүЎguard\add* the Foundation Gate and all the peopleВҰ209928 inВҰ209924 the \add вүҲtemple\add* courtyardВҰ209929.
\v 6 Don't let anyoneВҰ209935 enter Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add* other than the priestsВҰ209942 andВҰ209933 the LevitesВҰ209944 who are on duty, because they're consecrated. \add вүҲEvery one else must respect Yahweh's instructions\add* \add not to enter\add*.
\v 7 \add вүҲYou\add* LevitesВҰ209959 must \add вүҲbe armed\add* andВҰ209958 surroundВҰ209958 the \add young\add* king. \add вүҲYou must kill anyone else who tries to enterВҰ209967 the temple, butВҰ209958 stay close to the king wherever he goes\add*.
\rem /s1 Joash Crowned King
\p
\v 8 \add вүҲSoВҰ209979\add* the LevitesВҰ209980 andВҰ209979 the other people did \add вүҲeverything\add* that Yehoyada the priest had instructedВҰ209987. Each \add leader\add* tookВҰ209990 his menВҰ209994, both those starting duty on the Rest Day, as well as the others \add вүҲfinishing their duties that day\add*, because Yehoyada \add вүҲdidn'tВҰ210001 dismiss any of the groups\add*.
\v 9 ThenВҰ210009 Yehoyada the priestВҰ210011 gaveВҰ210009 each of those commandersВҰ210012 the spearsВҰ210016, and the large and smallВҰ210022 shields which \add вүҲhad been put in the temple by\add* KingВҰ210024 DavidВҰ210025.
\v 10 He stationedВҰ210030 all the peopleВҰ210035, each one holding his weaponВҰ210038, \add вүҲright across the end of the temple\add* around the altarВҰ210048 and the \add вүҲtemple\add*, and all around the kingВҰ210052.
\v 11 Then they broughtВҰ210055 out \add вүҲyoung Yoash\add* and put a crownВҰ210065 on \add вүҲhis head\add* and gave him \add вүҲa scroll with the agreement on it\add*, and proclaimed him as king. Then Yehoyada and his sons anointedВҰ210071 him \add with olive oil\add* and shouted, вҖң\add Long\add* live the king!вҖқ
\rem /s1 The Death of Athaliah; Athaliah Murdered
\p
\v 12 \add вүҲWhen\add* Atalyah heardВҰ210079 the soundВҰ210083 of people runningВҰ210085, and \add вүЎpeople\add* praisingВҰ210086 the kingВҰ210089, she went to the \add вүҲtemple\add*
\v 13 to look, and wow, the \add young\add* king was standingВҰ210100 \add where previous kings had stood\add* by the pillarВҰ210103 atВҰ210104 the \add temple\add* entranceВҰ210104, with the commanders and trumpeters beside him. The peopleВҰ210112 were all \add вүҲcheering\add* and blowingВҰ210115 trumpets, and singersВҰ210117 with instrumentsВҰ210118 were leadingВҰ210120 the praisingВҰ210121. ThenВҰ210097 Atalyah tore herВҰ210126 robe and \add вүҲshouted out\add*, вҖңTreason! Treason!вҖқ
\p
\v 14 The Yehoyada the priest instructed the commandersВҰ210137, вҖң\add Kill her,\add* butВҰ210132 not \add here\add* atВҰ210152 Yahweh's temple. \add вүҲMarch her outsideВҰ210147 and kill anyone who sticks up for\add* her.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 They \add вүҲseized\add* her as she reached the Horse Gate \add вүҲin front of the palace\add* andВҰ210161 \add вүҲkilled\add* her thereВҰ210174.
\s1 Yehoyada leads back to Yahweh
\rem /s1 Jehoiada's Reforms; Jehoiada's Religious Reforms
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Kgs 11:17-20)
\p
\v 16 Then Yehoyada \add the priest\add* \add вүҲgot the people to formally agree that they and the kingВҰ210186 would be loyal to\add* YahwehВҰ210189,
\v 17 \add вүҲso\add* all the peopleВҰ210194 wentВҰ210191 to Baal's \add вүҲtemple\add* and tore itВҰ210198 down. They smashed its altars and idols, and killedВҰ210210 Baal's priestВҰ210208 MattanВҰ210207 in frontВҰ210211 of the altars.
\v 18 ThenВҰ210214 Yehoyada \add вүҲcreated the roster\add* for the temple \add duties of\add* the priestsВҰ210220 andВҰ210236 LevitesВҰ210221 that \add King\add* DavidВҰ210224 had \add previously\add* assigned, \add including\add* offering burntВҰ210230 offerings to YahwehВҰ210218 withВҰ210219 happiness and singingВҰ210236, \add вүҲfollowing\add* Mosheh'sВҰ210234 writtenВҰ210232 instructions.
\v 19 HeВҰ210247 \add вүҲalso\add* stationedВҰ210241 guards at the \add вүҲtemple\add* gatesВҰ210245 so that no one could enter if they were \add вүҲceremonially вҖҳuncleanВҰ210251вҖҷ\add*.
\p
\v 20 ThenВҰ210256 \add @Yehoyada\add* took those commandersВҰ210259 and the noblesВҰ210263 and leaders and all the people, and \add #they\add* broughtВҰ210274 the king \add вүҲout of the temple\add* and down into the palace through the Upper Gate, and sat him onВҰ210267 the royalВҰ210293 throneВҰ210292.
\v 21 ThenВҰ210295 all of Yehudah's peopleВҰ210298 \add вүҲcelebrated\add* and thenВҰ210295 the cityВҰ210301 was \add вүҲpeacefulВҰ210302 and quiet\add* as Atalyah had been put to deathВҰ210306 withВҰ210307 the swordВҰ210307.
\c 24
\s1 Yehudah's king Yoash
\rem /s1 King Joash of Judah; Joash Repairs the Temple
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Kgs 12:1-16)
\p
\v 1 YoashВҰ210314 was sevenВҰ210312 \add вүҲyears old\add* when he becameВҰ210315 \add Yehudah's\add* kingВҰ210315, and he reignedВҰ210318 from YerushalemВҰ210319 for fortyВҰ210316 years. His motherВҰ210321 was Tsivyah from Beer-Sheva.
\v 2 YoashВҰ210327 did \add вүҲwhat pleased\add* YahwehВҰ210330 \add вүҲthroughout the lifetime\add* of YehoyadaВҰ210334 the priestВҰ210335.
\v 3 YehoyadaВҰ210340 \add вүҲprocured\add* twoВҰ210342 wivesВҰ210341 for him, and \add вүҲthey bore him\add* sonsВҰ210344 and daughtersВҰ210345.
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲSometime later,\add* Yoah \add вүҲdecided it would be good\add* to repair Yahweh's residence,
\v 5 and he gatheredВҰ210362 the priestsВҰ210365 and Levites, and told them, вҖңGo out to Yehudah'sВҰ210371 citiesВҰ210370 and collectВҰ210372 enough moneyВҰ210376 \add вүҲacross the country\add* to \add вүҲrenovate\add* God's houseВҰ210381 \add вүҲinВҰ210385 the next few years\add*. \add вүҲMake this a priority\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲButВҰ210362\add* the Levites didn'tВҰ210389 \add вүҲget onВҰ210385 to it\add*,
\v 6 \add вүҲso\add* \add @the kingВҰ210394\add* he summoned Yehoyada and \add вүҲdemanded\add*, вҖңWhy haven't you \add вүҲfollowed up on sending\add* the LevitesВҰ210405 throughout YerushalemВҰ210408 and \add across\add* YehudahВҰ210407 \add вүҲto collect the annual taxВҰ210411 instituted\add* by Yahweh's servantВҰ210413 MoshehВҰ210412 \add (MosesВҰ210412)\add* \add вүҲfor the people to contribute to the costs of the sacred tent\add*?вҖқ\x + \xo 24:6: \xt Exo 30:11-16.\x*
\p
\v 7 (The wickedВҰ210423 Atalyah had \add previously\add* brokenВҰ210425 into Yahweh's residence andВҰ210430 \add taken\add* some of the sacredВҰ210433 items from Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add* to be used for BaalВҰ210438 \add worship\add*.)
\p
\v 8 TheВҰ210449 kingВҰ210441 ordered that a chestВҰ210443 be made andВҰ210440 placed outsideВҰ210450 the \add main\add* \add вүҲtemple\add* entrance.
\v 9 They made an announcement in YerushalemВҰ210456 andВҰ210456 \add throughout\add* YehudahВҰ210455 to bringВҰ210457 to YahwehВҰ210458 the \add вүҲtaxВҰ210459 instituted\add* by God's servantВҰ210461 MoshehВҰ210460 \add вүҲwhen they were still\add* in the wildernessВҰ210467.
\v 10 All the officials and the peopleВҰ210475 agreed \add with this policy, so\add* they broughtВҰ210476 \add >their contributions\add* and droppedВҰ210477 them into the chestВҰ210478 untilВҰ210479 it filled up.
\v 11 Every day when the LevitesВҰ210494 who'd been given oversightВҰ210491 over the chest by the king, saw that it was full, they'd \add вүҲfetch\add* one of the king's secretaries along withВҰ210484 one of the head priest'sВҰ210504 officialsВҰ210503, and they'd emptyВҰ210506 the box and returnВҰ210511 it to its placeВҰ210514, so they amassed \add вүҲa large sum of\add* money.
\p
\v 12 The kingВҰ210526 and Yehoyada \add the priest\add* gaveВҰ210525 \add @the collected funds\add* to those who workedВҰ210544 on the \add вүҲtemple renovations\add*. They \add used them\add* to hire stone-workers and \add вүҲcarpentersВҰ210539\add* to restoreВҰ210540 the \add вүҲtemple building\add*, as well as for iron and bronzeВҰ210546 craftsmen.
\v 13 \add вүҲSoВҰ210553\add* they \add вүҲstarted onВҰ210559 the work\add* and the \add вүҲtemple restorationВҰ210560 went ahead\add*. TheyВҰ210564 rebuilt the \add вүҲtemple following\add* it's \add original\add* specificationsВҰ210567, and strengthenedВҰ210568 it.
\v 14 Whey they'd finishedВҰ210570, they broughtВҰ210571 the remainderВҰ210577 of the funds \add back\add* to the kingВҰ210573 and Yehoyada, and they made items for \add вүҲthe temple\add*, items \add вүҲused in\add* ministry and for burnt offerings, and dishesВҰ210587 and goldВҰ210589 and silverВҰ210590 items. During Yehoyada's \add вүҲtime\add*, they were offering regular burnt sacrifices in Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add*.
\rem /s1 Apostasy of Joash; Jehoiada's Policies Are Reversed
\p
\v 15 \add вүҲBy then,\add* Yehoyada \add вүҲwas getting old\add*, and he diedВҰ210607 \add вүҲatВҰ210613 the age of\add* 130,
\v 16 and they buriedВҰ210615 himВҰ210615 withВҰ210616 the kingsВҰ210621 inВҰ210616 вҖҳThe City of DavidВҰ210618вҖҷ, because he'd done \add so much\add* goodВҰ210625 for YisraelВҰ210626, and for God and his \add вүҲtemple\add*.
\rem /s1 Jehoiada's Reforms Reversed; The Wickedness of Joash
\p
\v 17 After Yehoyada's deathВҰ210633, Yehudah'sВҰ210637 leadersВҰ210636 wentВҰ210635 to \add young KingВҰ210639\add* Yoash and \add вүҲdeclared their loyalty\add* to \add *him\add*, and \add *he\add* listenedВҰ210641 to them.
\v 18 ThenВҰ210645 they abandonedВҰ210645 the \add вүҲtemple\add* of their ancestors' godВҰ210650 YahwehВҰ210649, and they \add вүҲworshipped\add* the Asherah \add polesВҰ210655\add* and idolsВҰ210658, and \add GodВҰ210650\add* was angry atВҰ210666 YerushalemВҰ210665 and YehudahВҰ210664 because of their \add вүҲdisobedience\add*.
\v 19 HeВҰ210675 sentВҰ210669 prophetsВҰ210671 to \add tell them\add* to return back to \add *him\add*, andВҰ210669 \add вүҲalthough they warned the people, they didn'tВҰ210678 take any notice\add*.
\p
\v 20 Then God's spiritВҰ210682 \add вүҲenveloped\add* Zekaryah, the son of Yehoyada the priestВҰ210691, and he stoodВҰ210692 \add вүҲup\add* and told the peopleВҰ210694, вҖңGod \add вүҲasks\add* why you're all \add вүҲviolating\add* \add *his\add* commandsВҰ210706? Because you abandoned YahwehВҰ210707, then he's abandoned all of you.вҖқ\x + \xo 24:20-21: \xt Mat 23:35; Luk 11:51.\x*
\v 21 \add вүҲHoweverВҰ210727,\add* \add @the people\add* conspiredВҰ210719 against \add @Zekaryah\add*, andВҰ210719 the kingВҰ210724 ordered him to be \add вүҲexecuted by\add* stoning him inВҰ210723 the \add вүҲtemple\add* courtyardВҰ210725.
\v 22 KingВҰ210733 YoashВҰ210732 \add вүҲdisregarded\add* the loyal commitment thatВҰ210735 Yehoyada had shown to his fatherВҰ210738, and had killedВҰ210740 his son. As he was dyingВҰ210744, he saidВҰ210745, вҖңLet YahwehВҰ210747 seeВҰ210746 \add >this\add* and \add find a way to\add* avengeВҰ210748.вҖқ
\rem /s1 The End of Joash's Reign; Death of Joash
\p
\v 23 \add вүҲAround\add* the end of the yearВҰ210754, the Aramean army \add вүҲattacked\add* YehudahВҰ210762 and YerushalemВҰ210763, and \add вүҲkilled\add* all the people's leadersВҰ210769. They sentВҰ210775 all their plunderВҰ210774 \add back to their\add* kingВҰ210776 in DamascusВҰ210777.
\v 24 \add вүҲActually, the ArameansВҰ210785 only had a smallish army, butВҰ210786 Yahweh allowed them to defeat the much larger\add* army \add from Yehudah\add* and \add вүҲbring punishment to\add* \add King\add* YoashВҰ210801, because they had abandonedВҰ210793 Yahweh, the godВҰ210797 of their fathers.
\v 25 When they \add вүҲwithdrew\add*, they left \add @Yoash\add* with severe woundsВҰ210811, and thenВҰ210805 his servantsВҰ210816 conspiredВҰ210814 against him because he'd killed the \add #son\add* of the priestВҰ210820 Yehoyada. \add вүҲSoВҰ210805\add* they killed him in his bed, and \add although\add* they buried him in вҖҳThe City of DavidВҰ210828вҖҷ, he wasn't buried \add вүҲwith the other\add* kingsВҰ210832.
\v 26 The ones who had conspiredВҰ210836 to kill him were: Zavad (a son of the AmmoniteВҰ210842 woman ShimeatВҰ210841) and Yhezavad (a son of the Moabite woman ShimritВҰ210846).
\p
\v 27 \add вүҲThe list of\add* \add @King Yoash's\add* sonsВҰ210849, the many prophecies concerning him, andВҰ210849 \add &his\add* renovations of \add вүҲthe temple\add*, are all writtenВҰ210858 on вҖҳThe Scroll of the KingsвҖҷ. His son Amatsyah replaced him as kingВҰ210864.
\c 25
\s1 Yehudah's King Amatsyah
\rem /s1 King Amaziah of Judah; Reign of Amaziah; Amaziah Rules in Judah; Amaziah King of Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Kgs 14:2-6)
\p
\v 1 Amatsyah was twenty-five when he becameВҰ210875 \add Yehudah's\add* kingВҰ210875, and he reignedВҰ210880 from Yerushalem for twenty-nine years. His motherВҰ210883 was Yehoaddin from Yerushalem.
\v 2 He \add вүҲmostly followed Yahweh's instructions, butВҰ210887 not whole-heartedly\add*.
\p
\v 3 \add вүҲOnce his rule was established\add*, he killed \add those of\add* his servantsВҰ210904 who had \add вүҲassassinated\add* his fatherВҰ210909 \add Yoash\add*.
\v 4 \add вүҲHowever,\add* he didn'tВҰ210914 order their sons to be executed because he obeyed Yahweh's instructionsВҰ210923 thatВҰ210921 had been writtenВҰ210917 down by MoshehВҰ210920 \add (MosesВҰ210920)\add*, вҖңFathers mustn't die \add вүҲbecause of what their sons did\add*, andВҰ210911 sons mustn't die \add вүҲbecause of what their parents did\add*, butВҰ210911 each \add вүҲindividual should be punished for their own disobedience\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 25:4: \xt Deu 24:16.\x*
\rem /s1 Slaughter of the Edomites; War against Edom
\rem /r (2 Kings 14.7)
\p
\v 5 Then Amatsyah \add вүҲsummoned\add* Yehudah'sВҰ210950 \add men\add* and appointed some by \add вүҲtheir clans\add* to be leaders of hundreds and of thousands, for all of Yehudah and BenyaminВҰ210962. \add вүҲThey counted\add* three-hundred thousand men who were twentyВҰ210965 and over, and \add вүҲsuitable for fighting\add* with a spearВҰ210977 and shieldВҰ210978.
\v 6 He \add вүҲalso\add* hiredВҰ210980 one-hundred thousandВҰ210983 \add вүҲpowerful warriors\add* from YisraelВҰ210981 for three tonnes of silverВҰ210989.
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲHowever,\add* a manВҰ210991 of God came and told him, вҖң\add вүҲYour majesty\add*, don'tВҰ210997 let Yisrael's \add вүҲsoldiers\add* goВҰ210999 with youВҰ211000, because YahwehВҰ211005 isn'tВҰ210997 with YisraelвҖ”those Efrayimites.\f + \fr 25:7 \ft The northern kingdom of Yisrael also came to be known as вҖҳEfrayimвҖҷ (similar how the area of the tribes of Yehudah and Benyamin (plus others who moved inвҖ”see 11:16) became known as вҖҳYehudahвҖҷ).\f*
\v 8 \add вүҲEven if\add* you goВҰ211016 \add and\add* \add вүҲfight courageously inВҰ211029\add* battleВҰ211020, God will cause you \add вүҲto be defeated\add* by the enemyВҰ211024, because God has the power to helpВҰ211030 and \add вүЎthe power to\add* overthrowВҰ211031.вҖқ
\p
\v 9 вҖң\add вүҲSoВҰ211033\add* what should I do aboutВҰ211040 \add вүҲall the silver\add* that I've \add already\add* paid to the troopsВҰ211044 from YisraelВҰ211045?вҖқ Amatsyah \add вүҲasked\add*.
\p вҖңYahwehВҰ211050 \add вүҲcan do much more for\add* you than that,вҖқ God's man \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲSoВҰ211056\add* \add King\add* Amatsyah dismissedВҰ211056 the troopsВҰ211058 from \add вүҲYisrael\add* to go home \add again\add*, \add вүҲbutВҰ211056\add* they were \add вүҲextremely angry\add* withВҰ211069 YehudahВҰ211069, andВҰ211056 they got home \add still\add* \add вүҲfeeling furious\add*.
\p
\v 11 Then Amatsyah \add вүҲtook courage\add* and led his \add вүҲarmy\add* out to the Salt ValleyВҰ211084 \add вүҲwhere\add* \add #they\add* \add вүҲslaughtered\add* tenВҰ211092 thousandВҰ211093 \add вүҲEdomite\add* \add soldiers\add*.
\v 12 YehudahВҰ211100 \add вүҲrounded up another tenВҰ211095 thousandВҰ211096\add* andВҰ211095 \add вүҲherded\add* them to the top of a cliffВҰ211103 \add вүҲwhere they drove them over to kill them\add*.
\p
\v 13 \add вүҲHowever,\add* \add during that time\add*, the \add вүҲwarriors\add* that Amatsyah had sent back \add to Yisrael\add*, raidedВҰ211120 Yehudah'sВҰ211122 citiesВҰ211121 \add all the way\add* from ShomronВҰ211123 \add (SamariaВҰ211123)\add* to Beyt-HoronВҰ211127. They'd \add вүҲkilled\add* threeВҰ211130 thousandВҰ211131 \add people\add* and taken \add back\add* a large amount of plunderВҰ211133.
\s1 Amatsyah worships false gods
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 14 After \add King\add* Amatsyah returned from \add вүҲfighting\add* the Edomites, he broughtВҰ211145 \add back\add* their \add idols\add* and set them up to be \add his\add* godsвҖ”bowing down to them and offering sacrifices.
\v 15 \add вүҲThat made\add* YahwehВҰ211162 \add вүҲvery\add* angry atВҰ211163 Amatsyah, andВҰ211159 he sentВҰ211164 a prophetВҰ211166 to tell him, вҖңWhy \add вүҲdid you want those\add* godsВҰ211173 who weren't \add вүҲeven able to save theirВҰ211181 own peopleВҰ211181 from your army\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 16 While he was still speakingВҰ211186, \add @the king\add* \add вүҲsnapped atВҰ211186\add* him, вҖң\add вүҲWho asked you to be my\add* counsellorВҰ211190? \add вүҲStop right this minute or\add* they'll strike you down?вҖқ
\p \add вүҲSoВҰ211184\add* the prophetВҰ211199 stoppedВҰ211198 \add talkingВҰ211186\add*, \add вүҲbutВҰ211184 thenВҰ211184 he added\add*, вҖңI know that GodВҰ211205 has \add вүҲdecided\add* to destroyВҰ211206 you because you've done that, andВҰ211184 \add вүЎbecause\add* you didn'tВҰ211211 listenВҰ211212 to my adviceВҰ211213.вҖқ
\s1 Yehudah brings trouble on itself
\rem /s1 War against Israel; Israel Defeats Judah
\s4 Both kingdoms
\rem /r (2 Kings 14.8-20)
\p
\v 17 \add вүҲSome time later,\add* Yehudah'sВҰ211219 King Amatsyah \add вүҲconsulted his advisors\add*, then sentВҰ211220 \add a challenge\add* to Yisrael's King YoashВҰ211223 (son of YehoahazВҰ211226, son of YehuВҰ211229), вҖңLet's face each other \add on the battlefield\add*.вҖқ
\v 18 \add вүҲButВҰ211238\add* Yisrael's KingВҰ211240 Yosash \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңA thistle that was in Lebanon sent to a cedarВҰ211256 that was in Lebanon, saying, вҖҳGive your daughterВҰ211264 to my son for a wife,вҖҷ butВҰ211238 some \add random\add* animalВҰ211268 passedВҰ211267 through the Lebanese countrysideВҰ211269 andВҰ211238 trampledВҰ211272 the thistle.
\v 19 You \add вүҲdefeatedВҰ211279\add* EdomВҰ211282 and \add вүҲnow it's gone to your head\add*. \add вүҲSo stayВҰ211287 inВҰ211288 your chair atВҰ211288 homeВҰ211288 and don't get over-excited, otherwise both you and Yehudah will be toppled\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲButВҰ211297\add* \add King\add* Amatsyah \add вүҲtook no notice\add*, because GodВҰ211302 \add вүҲwas planning for him to be defeated for worshipping\add* Edom'sВҰ211311 godsВҰ211310.
\v 21 \add вүҲSoВҰ211313\add* Yisrael's KingВҰ211315 YoashВҰ211314 \add вүҲadvanced\add*, andВҰ211313 \add вүҲthe two armies faced each other\add* at Beyt-Shemesh in YehudahВҰ211324,
\v 22 and YehudahВҰ211331 was \add вүҲbadly defeatedВҰ211330\add* by YisraelВҰ211333, and \add вүҲall their warriors fled back home\add*.
\v 23 Yisrael's King Yoash captured King Amatsyah (son of Yoash, son of YehoahazВҰ211348) atВҰ211359 Beyt-Shemesh andВҰ211338 took him to Yerushalem. ThenВҰ211338 he tore down Yerushalem'sВҰ211357 wall from the EfrayimВҰ211362 Gate to the Corner GateвҖ”a section about 180m long.
\v 24 He took all the goldВҰ211373 and silverВҰ211374 and \add вүҲother valuable items that Oved-EdomВҰ211386 had been guarding in the temple\add* back to ShomronВҰ211396 \add (SamariaВҰ211396)\add*, along with any valuables from the \add вүҲpalace\add* and some hostagesВҰ211394.
\rem /s1 Death of Amaziah
\p
\v 25 After the deathВҰ211407 of Yisrael's King YoashВҰ211403 (son of YehoahazВҰ211411), Yehudah'sВҰ211405 King Amatsyah livedВҰ211399 for a further fifteen years.
\v 26 \add The account\add* of everything else done by Amatsyah \add вүҲwas writtenВҰ211425\add* in the scrollВҰ211428 of вҖҳThe Kings of YehudahВҰ211431 andВҰ211418 YisraelВҰ211432вҖҷ.
\v 27 From the timeВҰ211434 that Amatsyah had turnedВҰ211437 from followingВҰ211439 YahwehВҰ211440, \add вүҲthere was a conspiracyВҰ211443 to assassinate him\add* inВҰ211444 YerushalemВҰ211444, \add вүҲbutВҰ211434\add* heВҰ211437 fled to Lakish. \add вүҲHowever,\add* they \add вүҲtraced him\add* to Lakish andВҰ211434 killedВҰ211450 him there.
\v 28 They used horsesВҰ211456 to carry his body back \add to Yerushalem\add*, andВҰ211457 he was buriedВҰ211457 withВҰ211462 his ancestorsВҰ211461 inВҰ211462 вҖҳThe City of DavidвҖҷ.\f + \fr 25:28 \ft The Hebrew actually has the unusual вҖҳThe City of YehudahвҖҷ here.\f*
\c 26
\s1 Yehudah's King Uzziyah
\rem /s1 King Uzziah of Judah; Uzziah Rules in Judah; Reign of Uzziah; Uzziah King of Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Kgs 14:21-22; 15:1-7)
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ211465 all the peopleВҰ211468 tookВҰ211465 sixteen year old Uzziyah andВҰ211465 made him kingВҰ211479 to replace his fatherВҰ211482 Amatsyah.
\v 2 \add @Uzziyah\add* restoredВҰ211490 Eylat City to YehudahВҰ211491 andВҰ211490 rebuilt itВҰ211490 afterВҰ211492 \add вүҲthe death of his fatherВҰ211498\add*.
\p
\v 3 Uzziyah was sixteen when he becameВҰ211507 kingВҰ211507, and he reignedВҰ211511 from Yerushalem for fifty-two years. His motherВҰ211514 was Yekolyah from Yerushalem.
\v 4 \add He\add* did \add вүҲthe things that YahwehВҰ211524 said were good, like\add* his fatherВҰ211530 Amatsyah had done.
\v 5 He \add вүҲstrived to follow\add* God \add вүҲduring the lifetime of\add* Zekaryah who instructedВҰ211537 him. During the timeВҰ211540 that he \add вүҲobeyed\add* YahwehВҰ211544, God \add вүҲmade him successfulВҰ211545\add*.
\p
\v 6 \add @Uzziyah\add* wentВҰ211549 to attack the PhilistinesВҰ211551, and \add successfully\add* brokeВҰ211552 through the walls atВҰ211551 Gat, Yavneh, and Ashdod. He \add вүҲrebuilt\add* Ashdod \add вүҲand other\add* citiesВҰ211564 inВҰ211551 the Philistia \add region\add*.
\v 7 God helpedВҰ211568 himВҰ211568 against the PhilistinesВҰ211572, against the ArabiansВҰ211575 who living inВҰ211578 Gurbaal, andВҰ211568 \add вүЎagainst\add* the MeunitesВҰ211581.
\v 8 The AmmonitesВҰ211584 paid tributeВҰ211585 to Uzziyah, andВҰ211583 his \add вүҲfame spread\add* as far as the Egyptian border because he was becoming more powerful.
\p
\v 9 \add King\add* Uzziyah builtВҰ211600 \add вүҲfortifiedВҰ211615\add* towersВҰ211602 in YerushalemВҰ211603 at the Corner Gate, the Valley Gate, andВҰ211600 at the angleВҰ211614 in the wall.
\v 10 He \add вүҲalso\add* builtВҰ211617 towersВҰ211618 in the wildernessВҰ211619 and dug many wellsВҰ211621 because he had a lot of cattleвҖ”both in the lowlands and in the plainsВҰ211630. He was \add вүҲalso interested in horticulture so\add* he had workers stationed in his vineyards and in his fertileВҰ211634 fields.
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲUzziyah'sВҰ211643 army was trained for fighting\add* battles and organised into divisionsВҰ211649 set up by YeielВҰ211653 the scribe and the commanderВҰ211662 MaaseyahВҰ211656, under the supervision of HananyahВҰ211661, one of the king'sВҰ211663 officialsВҰ211657.
\v 12 There were 2,600 \add вүҲclan leaders\add* who led the \add вүҲpowerful warriorsВҰ211669\add*,
\v 13 andВҰ211675 \add the full force of\add* 37,500 \add вүҲwas underВҰ211675 them\add* to support the kingВҰ211692 against his \add #enemies\add*.
\v 14 UzziyahВҰ211699 \add вүҲsupplied\add* \add #shields, spearsВҰ211704, helmetsВҰ211705, armoured vests, bows, andВҰ211697 slingshotsВҰ211709\add* for the entire army.
\v 15 \add вүҲUsing a local\add* inventionВҰ211715, he made war machines inВҰ211713 YerushalemВҰ211713 to be placed onВҰ211713 the towersВҰ211720 and cornersВҰ211723 \add of the walls\add* to fire arrowsВҰ211725 and largeВҰ211727 stonesВҰ211726. His fame \add now\add* \add вүҲspread widely\add* because he'd received a lot of help that had made him very powerful.
\rem /s1 Uzziah Is Punished for His Pride; Uzziah's Sin and Punishment; Pride and Apostasy
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲHowever,\add* \add atВҰ211749 the peak of\add* his strength he \add вүҲbecame very arrogant and that led to his\add* destructionВҰ211747. He \add вүҲdisobeyed\add* his godВҰ211750 YahwehВҰ211755 and went into the \add вүҲtempleВҰ211754\add* to burnВҰ211756 incense onВҰ211749 the incense altarВҰ211759.
\v 17 TheВҰ211769 high priest AzaryahВҰ211764 andВҰ211762 eightyВҰ211770 other \add вүҲbrave\add* priestsВҰ211767 wentВҰ211762 in afterВҰ211763 him.
\v 18 They \add вүҲconfronted\add* KingВҰ211779 Uzziyah andВҰ211775 \add вүҲchallenged\add* him, вҖңIt's not \add permitted\add* for you, Uzziyah, to sacrifice to Yahweh, only for Aharon's descendantsВҰ211790 the priestsВҰ211789вҖ”the ones consecratedВҰ211793 to sacrifice. Leave the sanctuaryВҰ211798, because you've \add вүҲdisobeyed\add* Yahweh GodВҰ211806 \add вүҲso now\add* he won'tВҰ211782 honourВҰ211804 you.вҖқ\x + \xo 26:18: \xt Exo 30:7-8; Num 3:10.\x*
\p
\v 19 ThenВҰ211808 Uzziyah who was holding an incense pan, becameВҰ211813 very angry, \add вүҲbutВҰ211808\add* when he \add started\add* raging atВҰ211810 the priests, spots of leprosyВҰ211817 \add suddenly\add* appeared onВҰ211810 his foreheadВҰ211819 while he was still there beside the incense altarВҰ211825 inВҰ211810 frontВҰ211820 of the priests.
\v 20 The high priestВҰ211831 AzaryahВҰ211830 lookedВҰ211828 \add more closely\add*, andВҰ211828 \add вүҲconfirming that it was indeed\add* leprosy onВҰ211840 his foreheadВҰ211840, hurried him outside. \add @The king\add* was \add now also\add* inВҰ211840 a hurry because YahwehВҰ211850 had afflictedВҰ211849 him.
\p
\v 21 KingВҰ211854 Uzziyah had leprosy untilВҰ211857 he died, \add вүҲso\add* he had to live in an isolated residence and wasn't allowed to \add вүҲapproach the temple\add*. His son Yotam \add (Jotham)\add* \add вүҲstood in for him\add*вҖ”supervising the \add вүҲpalace\add* and \add вүҲruling Yehudah\add*.
\p
\v 22 The record of all the other things done by Uzziyah \add вүҲwhile he was king\add* was writtenВҰ211888 by the prophetВҰ211893 Yeshayah \add (IsaiahВҰ211889)\add* (son of Amots).
\v 23 \add вүҲWhen Uzziyah died\add*, because of his leprosy theyВҰ211910 buriedВҰ211900 him withВҰ211905 his ancestorsВҰ211899 in a grave in the countrysideВҰ211905 for kingsВҰ211908, andВҰ211895 his son Yotam replaced him as kingВҰ211913.\x + \xo 26:23: \xt Isa 6:1.\x*
\c 27
\s1 Yehudah's King Yotam
\rem /s1 Jotham Rules in Judah; Reign of Jotham; King Jotham of Judah; Jotham King of Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Kgs 15:32-38)
\p
\v 1 Yotam \add (Jotham)\add* was twenty-five when he becameВҰ211925 kingВҰ211925, and he reignedВҰ211930 from YerushalemВҰ211931 for sixteen years. His motherВҰ211933 was YerushaВҰ211934, daughterВҰ211935 of \add the priest\add* TsadokВҰ211937.
\v 2 He did \add вүҲthe things that Yahweh said were good\add* like his fatherВҰ211948 Uzziyah had done (except that he didn'tВҰ211950 \add вүҲtrespass\add* in Yahweh's templeВҰ211955), \add вүҲHowever,\add* the peopleВҰ211958 were stillВҰ211957 behavingВҰ211959 corruptlyВҰ211959.
\p
\v 3 He rebuilt the Upper Gate of the \add вүҲtemple\add*, andВҰ211970 \add вүҲextended\add* the Ofel wall.
\v 4 He built citiesВҰ211975 in the YehudahВҰ211979 hill countryВҰ211977, and built fortressesВҰ211982 and towersВҰ211983 in the forests.
\v 5 He \add вүҲattacked\add* the Ammonite kingВҰ211989 and \add вүҲdominated\add* them. \add вүҲThenВҰ211985 for the next three yearsВҰ212020\add*, the Ammonites broughtВҰ212015 him three tonnes of silverВҰ212006, and 2,000 tonnes each of wheatВҰ212010 and barleyВҰ212011 each yearВҰ212001.
\v 6 YothamВҰ212025 became more powerful because he'd established \add вүҲa pattern of obeying\add* his godВҰ212031 YahwehВҰ212030.
\v 7 The record of all the other things done by Yotam \add вүҲwhile he was king\add*, including all his battles, was writtenВҰ212041 on the scrollВҰ212044 вҖҳThe kingsВҰ212045 of YisraelВҰ212047 andВҰ212033 YehudahвҖҷ.
\v 8 He was twenty-five when he becameВҰ212056 kingВҰ212056, and he reignedВҰ212061 from YerushalemВҰ212062 for sixteen years.
\v 9 ThenВҰ212064 \add (atВҰ212071 forty-one years old)\add*, Yotam \add вүҲdied\add* and was buriedВҰ212069 inВҰ212071 вҖҳThe City of DavidВҰ212072вҖҷ, and his son AhazВҰ212074 replaced him as kingВҰ212073.
\c 28
\s1 Yehudah's King Ahaz
\rem /s1 Reign of Ahaz; King Ahaz of Judah; Ahaz Rules in Judah; Ahaz King of Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Kgs 16:1-4)
\p
\v 1 AhazВҰ212083 was twenty-five when he becameВҰ212084 kingВҰ212084, and he reignedВҰ212089 from YerushalemВҰ212090 for sixteen years, \add вүҲbutВҰ212085\add* he didn'tВҰ212091 do what YahwehВҰ212096 \add вүҲwanted\add*, like his ancestor DavidВҰ212097 had.
\v 2 \add вүҲInstead,\add* he followed the waysВҰ212101 fo Yisrael's kingsВҰ212102, \add вүҲincluding\add* casting metal idols for the BaalВҰ212107.
\v 3 He offered incense inВҰ212111 the Ben-HinnomВҰ212114 valleyВҰ212111 andВҰ212109 he burnt his children withВҰ212111 fireВҰ212119\f + \fr 28:3 \ft Probably, but not definitely, referring to the practice of child sacrifice.\f* like the detestableВҰ212120 customs of the nationsВҰ212121 thatВҰ212122 YahwehВҰ212124 had driven away \add вүҲas the IsraelisВҰ212126 had entered the region\add*,
\v 4 plus he \add offered\add* sacrificesВҰ212129 and burnt incenseВҰ212130 atВҰ212131 the hilltop shrines, and onВҰ212131 the hillsВҰ212134, and underВҰ212135 everyВҰ212136 large, green treeВҰ212138.
\s1 War between Syria and Yisrael
\rem /s1 War with Syria and Israel; Aram and Israel Defeat Judah
\s4 Both kingdoms
\r (2 Kgs 16:5)
\p
\v 5 \add вүҲSoВҰ212141\add* his godВҰ212143 Yahweh \add вүҲallowed\add* \add @King Ahaz\add* \add вүҲto be defeatedВҰ212165 by\add* the king of AramВҰ212146вҖ”they attacked and took many prisoners \add back\add* to DamascusВҰ212155. \add вүҲIn addition,\add* \add @Yahweh\add* \add вүҲallowed the king of YisraelВҰ212160 to be victorious and they slaughtered many fighters\add*.\x + \xo 28:5-6: \xt 2Ki 16:5; Isa 7:1.\x*
\v 6 Yisrael's King PekahВҰ212170 (Remalyah'sВҰ212173 son) killedВҰ212169 120,000 \add вүҲpowerful warriors\add* in YehudahВҰ212174 in one dayВҰ212178, after they'd abandonedВҰ212184 the godВҰ212188 of theirВҰ212189 ancestorsВҰ212189.
\v 7 A warriorВҰ212194 from Efrayim \add named\add* ZikriВҰ212192 killedВҰ212191 KingВҰ212201 Ahaz's son MaaseyahВҰ212198, AzrikamВҰ212204 the \add вүҲpalaceВҰ212206 supervisor\add*, andВҰ212191 ElkanahВҰ212209 the king's second-in-command.
\rem /s1 Intervention of Oded
\v 8 Yisrael's soldiers captured two-hundred thousandВҰ212220 of their relatives, including their wives and \add вүҲchildren\add*. They also tookВҰ212214 a lot of plunderВҰ212228 back to ShomronВҰ212234 \add (SamariaВҰ212234)\add* with them.
\s2 The prophet Oded
\rem /s1 The Prophet Oded
\p
\v 9 \add вүҲNow\add* thereВҰ212237 was a prophetВҰ212239 of Yahweh \add вүҲnamed\add* OdedВҰ212241, and he wentВҰ212243 out to the army \add of Yisrael\add* as it was returning to ShomronВҰ212247, and told them, вҖңListen, Yahweh, the godВҰ212253 of your ancestorsВҰ212255 was angryВҰ212251 withВҰ212251 YehudahВҰ212258, so he \add вүҲhelped you all defeat them\add*. \add вүҲHowever,\add* you all killedВҰ212261 them inВҰ212251 rageВҰ212264 \add and\add* \add вүҲGodВҰ212253 has taken notice\add*.
\v 10 Now you want to \add вүҲkeep the peopleВҰ212270 of YerushalemВҰ212273 and YehudahВҰ212272 as your own male and femaleВҰ212278 slavesВҰ212277\add*, \add вүҲbutВҰ212269 that would certainlyВҰ212281 make you all guiltyВҰ212285 before\add* your godВҰ212287 YahwehВҰ212286.
\v 11 \add вүҲSoВҰ212289 thenВҰ212289,\add* listenВҰ212290 to me andВҰ212291 returnВҰ212291 those captivesВҰ212292 \add because\add* \add вүҲthey're your own relatives\add*, as YahwehВҰ212300 \add вүҲis extremely angry at\add* you all.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 Then \add вүҲsome of the leadersВҰ212306 of the Efrayim tribe took action\add* and \add confronted\add* \add вүҲthose returning from battleВҰ212331\add*: AzaryahВҰ212310 (Yehohanan'sВҰ212313 son), BerekyahВҰ212314 (Meshillemot'sВҰ212317 son), Yehizkiyah (Shallum'sВҰ212321 son), and AmasaВҰ212322 (Hadlai'sВҰ212325 son)
\v 13 told \add @the ones returning\add*, вҖңDon't bringВҰ212337 those captivesВҰ212340 here, because \add вүҲthat would be disobedience and adding to the rest of our disobedience and wrongs\add*, as \add Yahweh's already\add* angry at \add us here in\add* YisraelВҰ212364.вҖқ
\v 14 \add вүҲSo\add* the \add returning\add* \add вүҲsoldiersВҰ212368\add* released the captivesВҰ212371 in frontВҰ212375 of the leaders and all the assembledВҰ212379 \add people\add*, and \add вүҲdropped all the plunderВҰ212374\add* \add there as well\add*.
\v 15 Then some men \add from Yisrael\add* \add вүҲwere called out by name to come and search the plunderВҰ212395 to find clothes and\add* dress the nakedВҰ212391 captivesВҰ212388 \add from Yehudah\add* and give them sandalsВҰ212397. Then they \add вүҲgave them food and drinkВҰ212399, as well as oil\add* \add to rub onВҰ212386 their wounds\add*. They gave donkeysВҰ212402 to those who \add вүҲcouldn't easily walk\add*, and took them to Yeriho (The City of Palms) which was nearer their relatives, thenВҰ212381 those men returnedВҰ212413 to ShomronВҰ212414 \add (SamariaВҰ212414)\add*.
\rem /s1 Ahaz Closes the Temple; Assyria Refuses to Help Judah; Ahaz Asks Assyria for Help
\rem /r (2 Kings 16.7-9)
\p
\v 16 Around that timeВҰ212417, KingВҰ212420 AhazВҰ212421 \add вүҲrequested helpВҰ212426 from\add* the Assyrian kingsВҰ212424
\v 17 as the EdomitesВҰ212430 had been and attackedВҰ212432 YehudahВҰ212433 and taken captivesВҰ212436.
\v 18 \add вүҲAlso\add* the Philistines had raided the lowland citiesВҰ212440 and the NegevВҰ212442, and they'd capturedВҰ212444 Beyt-ShemeshВҰ212449, Ayyalon, GederothВҰ212455, as well as Sokoh, TimnahВҰ212462, and GimzoВҰ212466 withВҰ212440 their surrounding villagesВҰ212469
\v 19 because Yahweh was humblingВҰ212475 KingВҰ212482 AhazВҰ212481 as he'd \add вүҲthrown off\add* restraintВҰ212486 inВҰ212487 YehudahВҰ212479 andВҰ212488 been very unfaithfulВҰ212488 to Yahweh.
\v 20 \add вүҲSoВҰ212492\add* the Assyrian KingВҰ212496 TiglatВҰ212494-Pileser cameВҰ212492, \add вүҲexcept\add* he \add ended up\add* \add вүҲadding to his troubles rather than helping\add*.
\v 21 AhazВҰ212506 gave the Assyrian king \add вүҲvaluables from the temple and the palace and from other leaders\add*, \add вүҲbutВҰ212511 that didn'tВҰ212519\add* help.
\s1 Ahaz's disobedience
\rem /s1 Apostasy and Death of Ahaz; The Sins of Ahaz
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 22 \add вүҲWhile KingВҰ212530 AhazВҰ212531 was experiencing those troubles, he disobeyed Yahweh even more\add*
\v 23 and sacrificed to the gods of DamascusВҰ212535 (\add вүҲbecause AramВҰ212543 had defeatedВҰ212536 him\add*). He \add вүҲreasoned\add*, вҖңSince the gods of the Aramean kingsВҰ212541 helped them, I'll sacrifice to them, and thenВҰ212533 they'll help me.вҖқ \add вүҲHowever,\add* that led to Ahaz's fall, and \add вүЎto the fall of\add* all Yehudah.\f + \fr 28:23 \ft Sometimes in 2 Chronicles, Yehudah is referred to as Yisrael, but as that can be confusing for readers, we've made adjustments.\f*
\v 24 Then AhazВҰ212560 gatheredВҰ212559 all the furnishings \add that were used\add* inВҰ212587 the \add вүҲtemple\add*, and broke them into piecesВҰ212567 and locked the \add вүҲtemple\add* doorsВҰ212577. Then he set up \add вүҲpagan\add* altarsВҰ212583 atВҰ212587 every YerushalemВҰ212587 \add вүҲintersection\add*
\v 25 andВҰ212589 in every YehudahВҰ212593 cityВҰ212591 he set up hilltop shrines to make sacrifices to otherВҰ212598 godsВҰ212597, \add вүҲthus\add* angeringВҰ212599 YahwehВҰ212602, the godВҰ212603 of his ancestorsВҰ212604.
\p
\v 26 The record of all the other things done by Ahaz \add вүҲwhile he was king\add* was writtenВҰ212614 on the scrollВҰ212617 вҖҳThe kingsВҰ212618 of YehudahВҰ212620 andВҰ212606 YisraelВҰ212621вҖҷ.
\v 27 Then AhazВҰ212624 died andВҰ212623 was buriedВҰ212628 in вҖҳThe City of DavidвҖҷ, butВҰ212623 not in the tombsВҰ212634 of the \add other\add* kingsВҰ212635 of YisraelВҰ212636. Then his son Hizkiyah \add вүҲreplaced him as kingВҰ212637\add*.\x + \xo 28:27: \xt Isa 14:28.\x*
\c 29
\s1 Purifying the temple
\rem /s1 Hezekiah and his successors; Hezekiah Rules in Judah; Hezekiah Purifies the Temple; Reign of Hezekiah; King Hezekiah of Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Kgs 18:1-3)
\p
\v 1 Hizkiyah was twenty-five when he becameВҰ212644 kingВҰ212644, and he reignedВҰ212653 from YerushalemВҰ212654 for twenty-nine years. His motherВҰ212656 was Zekaryah's daughterВҰ212658 Aviyah.
\v 2 He did what \add вүҲpleased\add* YahwehВҰ212665, like his ancestor \add King\add* DavidВҰ212670 had done.
\rem /s1 The Purification of the Temple; Hezekiah Reopens the Temple; The Temple Cleansed
\p
\v 3 InВҰ212685 the \add very\add* first monthВҰ212677 of his reignВҰ212676, he \add вүҲunlocked\add* the \add вүҲtemple\add* doorsВҰ212682 and repairedВҰ212686 them.
\v 4 ThenВҰ212688 he \add вүҲsummoned\add* the priestsВҰ212691 and the LevitesВҰ212694, and assembled them in \add вүҲthe easternВҰ212697 temple courtyard\add*
\v 5 and told them, вҖң\add Now you\add* LevitesВҰ212702, listenВҰ212701 to me. \add You need to\add* consecrate yourselvesВҰ212704 now, and consecrate the residence of YahwehВҰ212709, the godВҰ212710 of your ancestorsВҰ212711, and removeВҰ212712 \add вүҲany\add* defilementВҰ212715 from the sacredВҰ212718 placeВҰ212718,
\v 6 because our fathersВҰ212723 were unfaithfulВҰ212722 and \add вүҲdisobeyed\add* our godВҰ212729 YahwehВҰ212727. ThenВҰ212734 they abandonedВҰ212730 him and \add вүҲhad no more interest in this temple\add* and turned \add вүҲtheirВҰ212732 back\add* \add on it all\add*.
\v 7 They had extinguished the lampsВҰ212746 and \add вүҲlocked the temple up\add*. \add After that\add*, they didn'tВҰ212748 burn any incenseВҰ212747 or offerВҰ212750 any burntВҰ212750 sacrifices inВҰ212754 the sacredВҰ212754 placeВҰ212754 of Yisrael's godВҰ212755.
\v 8 \add That's why\add* YahwehВҰ212760 \add вүҲwas angry atВҰ212773\add* YerushalemВҰ212764 and \add all\add* YehudahВҰ212763, and \add вүҲallowed us to become a place of terror and horrorВҰ212768 and scorn\add* as you've all seen withВҰ212773 your \add own\add* eyesВҰ212773.
\v 9 \add вүҲAs a result,\add* our fathersВҰ212777 fell \add вүҲinВҰ212778 battle\add*, and our wivesВҰ212781 and \add вүҲchildren\add* have been \add вүҲcaptured and taken to other countries\add*.
\p
\v 10 Now \add вүҲI sincerely want to make an agreement\add* with Yisrael's godВҰ212794 YahwehВҰ212793, \add вүҲso that his fierce angerВҰ212799\add* will turnВҰ212796 away from us.
\v 11 \add вүҲSo lads,\add* don'tВҰ212803 \add вүҲmess around\add* because YahwehВҰ212810 has chosenВҰ212809 you all to standВҰ212811 inВҰ212808 hisВҰ212812 presenceВҰ212812 to serveВҰ212813 him, and to be ministering and burning incenseВҰ212817.
\p
\v 12 Then \add these\add* LevitesВҰ212821 \add вүҲtook action\add*:
\li1 from the Kohatites: MahatВҰ212822 (Amasai's son) and YoelВҰ212826 (Azaryah'sВҰ212829 son),
\li1 from the descendants of MerariВҰ212837: KishВҰ212838 (Avdi's son) and Azaryah (Yehallelel'sВҰ212845 son),
\li1 from the Gereshonites: Yoah (Zimmah'sВҰ212852 son) and EdenВҰ212853 (Yoah'sВҰ212849 son),
\li1
\v 13 from Elitsafan's descendants: ShimriВҰ212862 and YeielВҰ212863,
\li1 from Asaf'sВҰ212868 descendants: Zekaryah and MattanyahВҰ212870,
\li1
\v 14 from Heyman's descendants: Yehiel and ShimeiВҰ212879, and
\li1 from Yedutun's descendants: ShemayahВҰ212885 and UzzielВҰ212886.
\p
\v 15 They assembled theirВҰ212891 relatives andВҰ212888 consecratedВҰ212892 themselves, thenВҰ212888 theyВҰ212893 entered the \add вүҲtemple\add* to purify it as the kingВҰ212896 had ordered as a result of Yahweh's messageВҰ212897.
\v 16 The priestsВҰ212904 entered the innerВҰ212905 part of the \add вүҲtemple\add* to purify it, and they broughtВҰ212910 out everything they foundВҰ212916 \add вүҲthatВҰ212915 shouldn't be\add* in \add *there\add* to the \add вүҲtemple\add* courtyardВҰ212919, and thenВҰ212903 the LevitesВҰ212923 tookВҰ212922 it \add all\add* out \add to be burnt down in\add* the KidronВҰ212927 \add вүҲvalleyВҰ212925\add*.
\p
\v 17 They beganВҰ212930 \add вүҲthe purification\add* atВҰ212931 the beginning of March and \add вүҲworked outwards to the porch by\add* the eighth, and thenВҰ212930 eight more daysВҰ212947 \add for the courtyard\add*, \add вүҲso\add* they finishedВҰ212954 onВҰ212931 the sixteenth.
\rem /s1 The Temple Rededication; The Temple Is Rededicated
\p
\v 18 Then they \add вүҲreported\add* to KingВҰ212962 Hizkiyah, вҖңWe've purified all of Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add*, \add including\add* the altarВҰ212973 for burntВҰ212974 offeringsВҰ212974 and all its utensils, and the \add вүҲbread display\add* tableВҰ212982 and all its utensils.
\v 19 We've preparedВҰ213000 and consecratedВҰ213001 all the \add вүҲitems\add* whichВҰ212994 KingВҰ212996 AhazВҰ212997 had rejectedВҰ212995 in his reignВҰ212998 of unfaithfulnessВҰ212999, and they're \add back\add* in frontВҰ213003 of Yahweh's altarВҰ213004.вҖқ
\s2 Temple sacrifices restored
\rem /s1 Temple Worship Restored
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲEarly the next\add* morning, KingВҰ213010 Hizkiyah assembled the cityВҰ213014 officialsВҰ213013, and went to Yahweh's \add вүҲresidence\add*,
\v 21 \add вүҲtaking\add* seven bullsВҰ213020, seven rams, seven male lambsВҰ213025, and seven male goats to be a sin offeringВҰ213030 for the kingdomВҰ213033, and for the sanctuaryВҰ213036, and for YehudahВҰ213039. He \add вүҲinstructed\add* the priestsВҰ213043 (Aharon's descendantsВҰ213041) to \add вүҲsacrifice the animals to YahwehВҰ213048 on\add* the altarВҰ213047.
\v 22 SoВҰ213050 they slaughtered the bullsВҰ213051 and took the blood and sprinkled it on the altar. ThenВҰ213050 they \add вүҲdid the same for the rams, and thenВҰ213050\add* the lambsВҰ213065.
\v 23 \add вүҲFinally,\add* they broughtВҰ213070 the goatsВҰ213073 for the sinВҰ213074 offeringВҰ213074 \add вүҲto the frontВҰ213075\add*, and the kingВҰ213076 and the people placed theirВҰ213079 handsВҰ213079 on them
\v 24 \add вүҲbefore\add* the priestsВҰ213083 slaughteredВҰ213082 them and splashed theirВҰ213087 bloodВҰ213087 on the altarВҰ213088 \add вүҲso Yahweh would forgive the disobedience\add* of all Yisrael. (The kingВҰ213100 had ordered the burntВҰ213101 offerings and the sin offering be for all Yisrael.)
\p
\v 25 ThenВҰ213104 he \add вүҲtold\add* the LevitesВҰ213107 \add to stand\add* inВҰ213110 the \add вүҲtemple\add* withВҰ213110 cymbalsВҰ213110, harpsВҰ213111, and lyresВҰ213112вҖ”\add вүҲobeying what DavidВҰ213114 and his prophets GadВҰ213115 and NatanВҰ213119 had commanded\add*. (YahwehВҰ213109 had \add actually\add* \add вүҲgiven those orders through\add* his prophets.)
\v 26 The LevitesВҰ213132 stoodВҰ213131 with David'sВҰ213134 instrumentsВҰ213133, and the priestsВҰ213135 with their trumpetsВҰ213136,
\v 27 then Hizkiyah said to offer the burnt offering onВҰ213144 the altarВҰ213143. \add вүҲWhen they started to slaughter the animals,\add* \add the people\add* \add вүҲsang and praised YahwehВҰ213150 as the trumpetsВҰ213151 were blown and the other instrumentsВҰ213155 played\add*.
\v 28 The entireВҰ213161 assemblyВҰ213163 were bowingВҰ213164 down \add and worshipping\add* as the singersВҰ213165 sang and the trumpetersВҰ213167 \add вүҲplayed\add*, untilВҰ213172 the burntВҰ213174 offeringВҰ213174 was completed,
\v 29 thenВҰ213176 the kingВҰ213179 and everyone with him bowedВҰ213178 down and worshippedВҰ213184.
\v 30 ThenВҰ213186 KingВҰ213188 HizkiyahВҰ213187 and his officialsВҰ213189 \add вүҲordered\add* the LevitesВҰ213190 to sing praises to YahwehВҰ213192 \add вүҲusing compositions\add* of DavidВҰ213194 and the prophet AsafВҰ213195, \add вүҲso\add* they cheerfully sang praises and bowedВҰ213201 down and worshippedВҰ213202.
\p
\v 31 Then Hizkiyah \add вүҲrespondedВҰ213205\add*, вҖңYou've all \add вүҲconsecrated yourselvesВҰ213210\add* to Yahweh, \add so\add* come near and bringВҰ213213 \add your\add* sacrifices and thanksgivings in to the houseВҰ213216 of Yahweh.вҖқ \add вүҲSo\add* the assemblyВҰ213219 brought in \add their\add* sacrifices and thanksgiving \add gifts\add*, \add вүҲplus those who wanted to\add*, \add вүЎbrought\add* \add вүҲtheir sacrifices to be burntВҰ213226\add*.
\p
\v 32 \add вүҲAltogetherВҰ213241\add* \add *they\add* broughtВҰ213232 seventyВҰ213235 bulls, one hundred rams, andВҰ213228 two hundred lambsВҰ213238 \add вүҲto be completed burnt on the altar\add*,
\v 33 as well as sixВҰ213248 hundredВҰ213249 bulls andВҰ213250 threeВҰ213251 thousandВҰ213252 sheepВҰ213250 \add вүҲas dedicated offeringsВҰ213246\add*.
\v 34 \add вүҲThere weren't enough priests\add* to skin all the burntВҰ213265 offeringsВҰ213265, so theirВҰ213267 relatives the Levites \add вүҲhelpedВҰ213266 them\add* until the work was finished and \add вүЎuntil\add* all the priests had consecrated themselves, because the Levites \add вүҲhard worked quicker\add* to consecrate themselves than the priests had.
\v 35 \add вүҲIn addition to the\add* burnt offerings, there was the fat from the peaceВҰ213288 offerings, andВҰ213283 there were drinkВҰ213289 offerings.
\p \add вүҲSoВҰ213283\add* the serviceВҰ213292 of Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple was reinstituted\add*
\v 36 and Hizkiyah and all the people celebrated about what God had preparedВҰ213303 for the people, because it had all happenedВҰ213308 fairly quicklyВҰ213307.
\c 30
\s1 Hizkiyah orders a pass-over celebration
\rem /s1 Hezekiah Celebrates the Passover; Preparations for Passover; The Great Passover
\s4 Both kingdoms
\p
\v 1 Then \add King\add* Hizkiyah sentВҰ213312 \add invitations\add* to all YisraelВҰ213318 and Yehudah (including Efrayim and Menashsheh) to comeВҰ213328 to Yahweh's \add temple\add*
\v 2 \add вүҲbecause\add* the kingВҰ213340 had consulted withВҰ213345 his officialsВҰ213341 and all the assemblyВҰ213344 in YerushalemВҰ213345 \add and decidedВҰ213339\add* to \add have a late\add* celebration of the Passover in \add вүҲApril\add*.\x + \xo 30:2-3: \xt Num 9:9-11.\x*
\v 3 (They couldn't have done itВҰ213354 atВҰ213355 the \add proper\add* timeВҰ213355 because the priestsВҰ213358 hadn't consecratedВҰ213361 themselvesВҰ213361 sufficientlyВҰ213363 then, andВҰ213365 so the peopleВҰ213365 hadn't gatheredВҰ213368 inВҰ213355 YerushalemВҰ213370.)
\v 4 The plan \add вүҲpleased\add* the kingВҰ213375 andВҰ213376 all the people,
\v 5 so theyВҰ213405 \add вүҲsent messagesВҰ213382 across\add* all Yisrael \add andВҰ213391 Yehudah\add* from Beer-Sheva \add in the south\add* to DanВҰ213393 \add in the far north\add* for \add the people\add* to comeВҰ213394 to YerushalemВҰ213401 to \add вүҲcelebrate\add* the Passover \add to honour\add* Yisrael's godВҰ213398 YahwehВҰ213397. (They hadn't previously been observing the written instructions.)
\v 6 Runners took the lettersВҰ213410 from the king and his officialsВҰ213413, \add going\add* to all Yisrael and YehudahВҰ213417 withВҰ213410 the king's commandВҰ213418: вҖңDescendants of Yisrael, return to YahwehВҰ213427, the godВҰ213428 of Avraham, Yitshak, and Yisrael, and he will return to you allвҖ”the \add вүҲgroup that\add* escapedВҰ213435 from the \add вүҲcontrol\add* of the Assyrian kingsВҰ213439.
\v 7 Don't be like your fathersВҰ213445 andВҰ213442 brothersВҰ213446 who weren't faithful to Yahweh, the godВҰ213450 of theirВҰ213451 ancestorsВҰ213451, \add provoking him\add* \add вүҲto leave them decimated as you can see\add*.
\v 8 \add вүҲSo don'tВҰ213459 be stubborn\add* like your ancestorsВҰ213463 were. \add вүҲObey\add* Yahweh and comeВҰ213468 to the sanctuaryВҰ213469 thatВҰ213470 he's consecratedВҰ213471 foreverВҰ213472, and serveВҰ213473 your godВҰ213477 Yahweh \add вүҲso he will\add* turnВҰ213478 his angerВҰ213481 away from you.
\v 9 If you all return to Yahweh, your brothersВҰ213488 and sons \add вүҲwill be shown mercy\add* by theirВҰ213492 captorsВҰ213492 and \add be able to\add* return to this land, because your godВҰ213501 Yahweh is graciousВҰ213498 and compassionateВҰ213490, and he won'tВҰ213502 \add вүҲignore\add* you if you all will turn back to him.
\rem /s1 Celebration of Passover
\p
\v 10 The messengers went from city to city inВҰ213530 the Efrayim and Menashsheh \add regionsВҰ213519\add*, as far \add north\add* as Zevulun, \add вүҲbutВҰ213513\add* \add @many people there\add* laughedВҰ213527 atВҰ213530 them and mockedВҰ213529 them.
\v 11 \add вүҲHowever, some of the people\add* from AsherВҰ213535, Menashsheh, and Zevulun humbledВҰ213538 themselvesВҰ213538 and wentВҰ213539 to YerushalemВҰ213540.
\v 12 Also inВҰ213543 YehudahВҰ213543, God moved the people to want to obey the kingВҰ213553 and his officialsВҰ213554 \add ?вүҲand Yahweh's instructions\add*.
\s1 The pass-over celebration
\rem /s1 Passover Is Celebrated
\s4 Both kingdoms
\p
\v 13 \add вүҲThe next\add* monthВҰ213568, a huge crowd gatheredВҰ213558 inВҰ213568 YerushalemВҰ213559 to celebrate the Festival of Flat Bread.
\v 14 They \add вүҲtook action\add* and removed the altars \add to Baal\add* inВҰ213580 YerushalemВҰ213580, and all the incenseВҰ213584 altars, and threwВҰ213586 them down into the KidronВҰ213588 valleyВҰ213587 \add to be burnt there\add*.
\v 15 \add вүҲIn the middle of the monthВҰ213594,\add* they slaughteredВҰ213590 the Passover lambs. The priestsВҰ213596 andВҰ213590 LevitesВҰ213597 had been ashamedВҰ213598, so they'd consecratedВҰ213599 themselves, them they broughtВҰ213600 the burntВҰ213601 offeringsВҰ213601 into the \add вүҲtemple\add*.
\v 16 TheyВҰ213614 theyВҰ213605 stoodВҰ213605 at their stations \add вүҲas per the instructions written by\add* MoshehВҰ213611 \add (MosesВҰ213611)\add*, thenВҰ213605 the LevitesВҰ213621 handed the \add bowls of\add* bloodВҰ213619 to the priestsВҰ213615 to sprinkleВҰ213616 \add on the altar\add*.
\v 17 Because many \add >people\add* inВҰ213626 the assemblyВҰ213626 hadn't consecrated themselvesВҰ213630, the LevitesВҰ213631 \add assisted them\add* by slaughteringВҰ213634 the lambsВҰ213635 andВҰ213631 consecrating them to YahwehВҰ213640.
\v 18 \add вүҲAlthough most\add* of the peopleВҰ213644 \add who'd travelled down\add* from Efrayim, Menashsheh, Yissakar, and Zevulun hadn't purifiedВҰ213651 themselvesВҰ213651, they ateВҰ213654 the Passover \add food\add* anyway \add вүҲdespite the written\add* \add instructions\add*, because Hizkiyah had prayedВҰ213661 to Yahweh for them, вҖңMay Yahweh who is goodВҰ213666, \add вүҲdeclare as innocent\add*
\v 19 everyone who \add вүҲsincerely wants to honour andВҰ213680 obey\add* YahwehВҰ213677, the godВҰ213678 of their ancestorsВҰ213679, \add вүҲeven if they haven't completed the formal purification ceremonies for the temple\add*.вҖқ
\v 20 YahwehВҰ213686 \add вүҲtook notice\add* of Hizkiyah'sВҰ213689 \add request\add*, and \add вүҲforgave\add* the peopleВҰ213693,
\v 21 \add вүҲso\add* the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ213699 who'd come\add* to YerushalemВҰ213701 celebratedВҰ213700 the Feast of Flat Bred for sevenВҰ213706 daysВҰ213707 withВҰ213701 greatВҰ213709 \add вүҲexcitement\add*. The LevitesВҰ213715 and priestsВҰ213716 praised \add вүҲenthusiastically\add* praised YahwehВҰ213711 every day using \add &their\add* musical instrumentsВҰ213717.
\v 22 Hizkiyah \add вүҲsincerely thankedВҰ213745\add* all the LevitesВҰ213730 who \add вүҲwere very insightful about worshipping\add* Yahweh. Then \add everyone\add* ateВҰ213736 for the prescribed sevenВҰ213740 daysВҰ213741вҖ”sacrificingВҰ213742 peaceВҰ213744 offeringsВҰ213744 and confessing to Yahweh, the godВҰ213747 of theirВҰ213748 ancestorsВҰ213748.
\s1 The pass-over celebration gets extended
\rem /s1 A Second Celebration
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 23 Then the \add вүҲwhole group decidedВҰ213751 to celebrate\add* for seven \add more\add* days, \add вүҲso\add* they \add вүҲenthusiastically\add* celebrated for \add вүҲanotherВҰ213758 whole week\add*
\v 24 because Yehudah'sВҰ213769 KingВҰ213767 Hizkiyah had provided a thousand bulls and sevenВҰ213774 thousand sheep for the people, and the officialsВҰ213778 had also contributed another thousand bulls and ten thousand sheep. Many \add more\add* priestsВҰ213787 \add also\add* consecratedВҰ213786 themselves.
\v 25 All the people from Yehudah celebrated, including the priestsВҰ213796 and LevitesВҰ213797, and all those people who'd come \add down\add* from YisraelВҰ213802 to stay in Yehudah (whether just for the occasion, or to live permanently), plus \add others\add* livingВҰ213807 in Yehudah.
\v 26 Everyone in Yerushalem was very happy, because nothing like that had happened in Yerushalem sinceВҰ213816 the time when David'sВҰ213820 son Shelomoh \add (SolomonВҰ213817)\add* was kingВҰ213821.
\v 27 \add вүҲFinally,\add*, the priestsВҰ213829 and LevitesВҰ213830 stood up and \add вүҲprayed a blessingВҰ213831 onВҰ213836\add* the peopleВҰ213834, and their voiceВҰ213836 was heardВҰ213835 because their prayerВҰ213838 reached \add @God's\add* holy residence inВҰ213836 the heavensВҰ213841.
\c 31
\s1 Hizkiyah's religious reforms
\rem /s1 Pagan Shrines Destroyed; Hezekiah's Religious Reforms; Hezekiah Reforms Religious Life
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 1 When that was all over, all \add those\add* IsraelisВҰ213879 went out to Yehudah'sВҰ213855 cities and shattered the pillarsВҰ213857 and cut down the Asherah polesВҰ213859, and they tore down the hilltop shrines and altarsВҰ213866 from the entireВҰ213845 Yehudah-BenyaminВҰ213870 \add region\add* and also up inВҰ213871 the Efrayim-Menashsheh \add region\add*. Once they'd finishedВҰ213844 that, they all returnedВҰ213876 to theirВҰ213883 ownВҰ213882 land and cities.
\rem /s1 Contributions for Worship
\p
\v 2 \add King\add* Hizkiyah allocated the priests and LevitesВҰ213892 \add into\add* divisions for the various different types of duties: for doing burntВҰ213902 offerings and peaceВҰ213903 offerings, for other servicesВҰ213899, and for thanksgivingВҰ213905 and praiseВҰ213906 atВҰ213907 the \add вүҲtemple\add* gatesВҰ213907.
\v 3 The kingВҰ213913 \add вүҲcontributedВҰ213912 some of his own funds\add* for burnt offerings \add to be sacrificed\add* each morningВҰ213919 and eveningВҰ213920, as well as for the Rest Days and the New Moon celebrations, and onВҰ213926 the other special days as per the writtenВҰ213925 instructions \add вүҲthat had come from\add* YahwehВҰ213927.\x + \xo 31:3: \xt Num 28:1вҖ“29:39.\x*
\p
\v 4 He told that peopleВҰ213930 \add вүҲliving inВҰ213939\add* YerushalemВҰ213932 to giveВҰ213933 the \add prescribed\add* \add #portions\add* to the priestsВҰ213935 andВҰ213936 LevitesВҰ213936, so that theyВҰ213938 could \add вүҲfocus onВҰ213939 serving\add* YahwehВҰ213940,\x + \xo 31:4-5: \xt Num 18:12-13,21.\x*
\v 5 and as soon as the messageВҰ213943 reached them, the IsraelisВҰ213947 \add started\add* giving the firstВҰ213948 portions of \add their harvests of\add* grainВҰ213949 and new wine, oilВҰ213951 and honeyВҰ213952, and all the produceВҰ213954 from the countrysideВҰ213955, so they broughtВҰ213959 a tenth of \add the harvests of\add* all their crops.
\v 6 The men of YisraelВҰ213962 and Yehudah \add вүҲwho were living inВҰ213965\add* Yehudah'sВҰ213966 citiesВҰ213965 also \add вүҲbroughtВҰ213978 a tenth\add* of their cattle and sheepВҰ213972, as well as a tenth of sacredВҰ213974 thingsВҰ213974 consecratedВҰ213975 to their godВҰ213977 YahwehВҰ213976, and it was all placed into large piles.
\v 7 That all beganВҰ213986 inВҰ213984 \add вүҲMay\add* andВҰ213989 was finishedВҰ213991 by \add вүҲSeptember\add*,
\v 8 and \add when King\add* Hizkiyah and \add &his\add* officialsВҰ213996 cameВҰ213994 and sawВҰ213997 the piles, they \add вүҲpraised\add* YahwehВҰ214004 and his \add вүҲIsraeli\add* peopleВҰ214006.
\v 9 \add вүҲWhen\add* Hizkiyah asked the priestsВҰ214014 and LevitesВҰ214015 about the piles,
\v 10 and AzaryahВҰ214022 the chiefВҰ214024 priestВҰ214023 (a descendant of TsadokВҰ214026) told him, вҖң\add вүҲSinceВҰ214041 the people started brining their contributionsВҰ214029\add* to the \add вүҲtemple\add*, we've been eating well and even had left-overs because YahwehВҰ214033 has blessedВҰ214042 his people, and \add вүҲall this is the remainder\add*.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Reorganization of Priests and Levites
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲSo then\add* Hizkiyah \add вүҲordered\add* \add >them\add* to prepareВҰ214055 the \add вүҲtemple\add* storerooms, which they did,
\v 12 and they broughtВҰ214061 inВҰ214067 the contributionsВҰ214064 and the tenths \add that had been given\add* and the \add вүҲthingsВҰ214066 faithfullyВҰ214067 dedicatedВҰ214066\add* \add to Yahweh\add*. The LeviteВҰ214073, KonanyahВҰ214070 \add вүҲwas appointed as supervisor\add* withВҰ214067 his brotherВҰ214075 ShimeiВҰ214074 \add вүҲas deputy\add*.
\v 13 \add вүҲThose two supervised\add* Yehiel, AzazyahВҰ214079, NahatВҰ214080, AsahelВҰ214081, Yerimot, Yozavad, ElielВҰ214084, Ismakyah, MahatВҰ214086, and BenayahВҰ214087, by the arrangement of KingВҰ214096 Hizkiyah and AzaryahВҰ214097 the \add вүҲtemple supervisor\add*.
\p
\v 14 The LeviteВҰ214107 Imnah'sВҰ214106 son, Kore \add вүҲwho guarded the temple's\add* easternВҰ214109 gateВҰ214108 was \add вүҲput in charge\add* of the free-will offering to GodвҖ”to \add вүҲdistribute those offerings\add* to YahwehВҰ214115, as well as any consecrated items.
\v 15 EdenВҰ214122, Minyamin, YeshuaВҰ214124, ShemayahВҰ214125, AmaryahВҰ214126, andВҰ214119 Shekanyah \add вүҲfaithfullyВҰ214130 assisted\add* him inВҰ214128 the priests' citiesВҰ214128 to \add вүҲdistributeВҰ214131 those things\add* to the \add different\add* divisionsВҰ214133 of priests, \add вүҲregardless of theirВҰ214132 status or size\add*.
\v 16 EveryВҰ214149 male who was atВҰ214155 least threeВҰ214141 yearsВҰ214142 old \add вүҲwho was listed in the genealogicalВҰ214138 records, received a portion\add* for their serviceВҰ214154 in the \add вүҲtemple as each divisionВҰ214156 performed their assigned duties\add*.
\v 17 \add вүҲEach priestlyВҰ214160 clan kept genealogicalВҰ214159 records\add* \add and received a portion\add*, plus the LevitesВҰ214163 \add вүҲwho were atВҰ214168 least twentyВҰ214165 years old\add* and accordingВҰ214161 to their divisionsВҰ214169,
\v 18 as well as their wivesВҰ214175 and young childrenВҰ214174, and sonsВҰ214176 and daughtersВҰ214177 whose names were onВҰ214182 the genealogies, because they had also faithfullyВҰ214182 consecratedВҰ214183 themselvesВҰ214183 for the \add вүҲsacredВҰ214185 work\add*.
\v 19 Also, Aharon's descendantsВҰ214187 the priests who had pastureВҰ214191 land around theirВҰ214192 citiesВҰ214192 andВҰ214187 who were named, were given a portionВҰ214202 for each male, as well as each Levite included onВҰ214190 the genealogicalВҰ214209 records.
\p
\v 20 SoВҰ214212 \add King\add* Hizkiyah did that throughout YehudahВҰ214217, andВҰ214212 he continued to faithfullyВҰ214221 \add вүҲfollow the instructions\add* of his godВҰ214224 YahwehВҰ214223.
\v 21 \add вүҲWhatever he did\add* for the \add вүҲtemple operation\add* as he followed God's rules and commandsВҰ214238, he \add вүҲtried hard to be diligent and sincere\add*, and he prosperedВҰ214245.
\c 32
\s1 The Assyrians threaten Yerushalem
\rem /s1 Sennacherib Threatens Jerusalem; Sennacherib's Invasion; Assyria Invades Judah; The Assyrians Threaten Jerusalem
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Kgs 18:13-37; 19:14-19,35-37; Isa 36:1-22; 37:8-38)
\p
\v 1 After all \add вүҲthose acts of faithfulnessВҰ214250\add*, the Assyrian KingВҰ214254 SennacheribВҰ214253 \add (Heb. Sanheriv)\add* \add вүҲinvadedВҰ214257\add* YehudahВҰ214258. He \add вүҲbesieged\add* the fortifiedВҰ214263 citiesВҰ214262 and prepared to capture them for himself.
\v 2 \add вүҲWhen\add* \add King\add* Hizkiyah sawВҰ214268 the SennacheribВҰ214273 had \add вүҲentered\add* \add the country\add* andВҰ214274 \add clearly\add* \add вүҲintended to attack\add* YerushalemВҰ214278,
\v 3 he consultedВҰ214280 with his officialsВҰ214283 and \add вүҲarmy leaders\add* about blocking up the springsВҰ214289 outsideВҰ214291 the cityВҰ214292, and they helpedВҰ214293 him.
\v 4 Many peopleВҰ214296 gatheredВҰ214295 and blocked the springsВҰ214304 from feeding the streamВҰ214307 that flowedВҰ214308 through the area, saying, вҖңWhy should the Assyrian kingsВҰ214315 comeВҰ214314 and find \add вүҲplenty of waterВҰ214318\add*?вҖқ
\v 5 ThenВҰ214321 he strengthened \add вүҲhis fortifications\add*, repairing brokenВҰ214328 \add sections of the\add* wall, and builtВҰ214322 towersВҰ214332 and an outer wall. He strengthened the \add вүҲsupporting wall\add* \add on the east side of\add* вҖҳThe City of DavidВҰ214341вҖҷ. He \add also\add* manufactured many weaponsВҰ214343 and shieldsВҰ214345,
\v 6 and he \add вүҲappointed army commandersВҰ214348\add* and assembled them at the plaza by the cityВҰ214359 gateВҰ214358, and \add вүҲencouraged them with these words\add*,
\v 7 вҖңBe strongВҰ214366 and be courageousВҰ214367. Don't be scared or discouraged because of the Assyrian kingВҰ214375, or by his massive army, because we have someone on our side who's \add вүҲmore powerful\add* than himВҰ214388.
\v 8 \add вүҲThey can only rely on human strength, butВҰ214393 we have\add* our godВҰ214395 YahwehВҰ214394 to helpВҰ214396 us and fightВҰ214397 our battlesВҰ214398 \add for us\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲSo\add* the peopleВҰ214400 \add вүҲtook strength\add* from KingВҰ214405 Hizkiyah's \add вүҲencouragement\add*.
\rem /s1 Sennacherib Threatens Jerusalem
\p
\v 9 \add вүҲLater, when\add* Assyrian King SennacheribВҰ214413 withВҰ214438 his army was \add вүҲsurrounding\add* Lakish city, he sentВҰ214412 some servantsВҰ214417 to YerushalemВҰ214418 to Yehudah'sВҰ214431 King Hizkiyah and \add вүҲall the residents\add*, saying,
\v 10 вҖң\add вүҲI \add* SennacheribВҰ214443, the kingВҰ214444 of AssyriaВҰ214445 \add вүҲam asking\add* what you're all trusting in as you're remainingВҰ214451 there in YerushalemВҰ214453 while it's besieged?
\v 11 Hizkiyah tells you, вҖҳOur godВҰ214466 YahwehВҰ214465 will rescue us from the Assyrian kingВҰ214469,вҖҷ butВҰ214463 he's misleadingВҰ214457 you and you'll all dieВҰ214461 of hunger and thirstВҰ214463!
\v 12 Wasn't it Hizkiyah who removedВҰ214476 his hilltop shrines and his altars, and told \add the people of\add* YerushalemВҰ214485 and \add all\add* YehudahВҰ214484, telling you all to only bow down at one altar and offer sacrifices on it.
\v 13 Don't you people knowВҰ214495 what my ancestorsВҰ214499 and I have done to the peoples from other countriesВҰ214506? Were any of theirВҰ214511 godsВҰ214505 able to save them from me?
\v 14 Which one out of the godsВҰ214517 of those nationsВҰ214518 which my ancestorsВҰ214522 destroyedВҰ214521 shows a precedent thatВҰ214520 your godВҰ214532 can rescue anyoneВҰ214523 from me?
\v 15 \add вүҲSo\add* don'tВҰ214543 let Hizkiyah deceiveВҰ214540 you or misleadВҰ214545 you like this. Don't believeВҰ214550 him because no god of any nationВҰ214561 or kingdomВҰ214562 has been able to save his peopleВҰ214564 from my ancestorsВҰ214567 or from me. \add вүҲSo your god certainly won'tВҰ214538 be able to protect you from my army\add*.
\p
\v 16 ThenВҰ214577 Sennacherib's servantsВҰ214579 said \add even\add* more against the god YahwehВҰ214582, andВҰ214584 against his servantВҰ214586 Hizkiyah,
\v 17 plus he wroteВҰ214589 lettersВҰ214588 \add вүҲinsulting\add* Yisrael's god YahwehВҰ214591 andВҰ214588 speakingВҰ214594 against him, writing, вҖңJust like the godsВҰ214597 of the \add other\add* nationsВҰ214598 couldn't save theirВҰ214604 people from me, so too Hizkiyah's god won'tВҰ214601 be able to \add вүҲprotect\add* his people from my \add вүҲstrength\add*.вҖқ
\v 18 ThenВҰ214615 \add @the Assyrians\add* \add вүҲshouted loud\add* \add threats\add* \add вүҲinВҰ214616 Hebrew\add* to the peopleВҰ214622 of YerushalemВҰ214623 who were onВҰ214616 the wall to \add try to\add* frightenВҰ214628 andВҰ214629 terrifyВҰ214629 them so theyВҰ214631 could captureВҰ214631 the cityВҰ214634вҖ”
\v 19 \add вүҲtelling them Yerushalem'sВҰ214640 god was just another god made by peopleВҰ214643 andВҰ214636 just as useless as the godsВҰ214642 of other countries\add*.
\rem /s1 Sennacherib's Defeat and Death
\p
\v 20 Then KingВҰ214652 Hizkiyah and Yeshayah (son of the prophetВҰ214657 Amots) called out to the heavensВҰ214662 \add requesting God's help\add*,
\v 21 and YahwehВҰ214666 sentВҰ214665 a messengerВҰ214667 who destroyed the powerful warriors, and the leaders and chiefs in the Assyrian \add вүҲarmy\add*, and then their kingВҰ214676 had to \add вүҲreturnВҰ214678 home in\add* shameВҰ214679. When he wentВҰ214682 into the temple of his godВҰ214684, some of \add вүҲhis sons ran him through withВҰ214675 a\add* swordВҰ214690.
\p
\v 22 \add вүҲSoВҰ214692 that's how\add* YahwehВҰ214693 savedВҰ214692 Hizkiyah and Yerushalem'sВҰ214700 inhabitantsВҰ214699 from the Assyrian KingВҰ214703 SennacheribВҰ214702, and from \add вүҲthe power of other nations\add*, and he gaveВҰ214709 them peace on all sides.
\v 23 Many \add >people\add* came to YerushalemВҰ214716 to bringВҰ214713 offeringsВҰ214714 for YahwehВҰ214715 and valuable gifts for Yehudah'sВҰ214720 KingВҰ214719 Hizkiyah, and afterВҰ214726 all that, he \add вүҲwas highly respected\add* by the other nationsВҰ214725.
\s1 Hizkiyah's illness
\rem /s1 Hezekiah's Sickness; Hezekiah's Sickness and Recovery; Hezekiah's Illness and Pride; Hezekiah's Pride, Success and Death
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Kgs 20:1-3,12-19; Isa. 38:1-3; 39:1-8)
\p
\v 24 \add вүҲSome time afterwards,\add* \add King\add* Hizkiyah becameВҰ214733 very sickВҰ214733 \add вүҲand was expected to die, butВҰ214738\add* he prayedВҰ214738 to Yahweh and \add @Yahweh\add* \add вүҲanswered him with a miracle\add*.
\v 25 \add вүҲHowever,\add* Hizkiyah was \add вүҲvery proud\add* and didn'tВҰ214748 \add вүҲthank\add* \add >Yahweh\add*, \add вүҲso his angerВҰ214759 fell on\add* YerushalemВҰ214763 and YehudahВҰ214762.
\v 26 ThenВҰ214765 HezekiahВҰ214766 and Yerushalem'sВҰ214771 inhabitantsВҰ214770 humbledВҰ214765 themselves, and so Yahweh's angerВҰ214776 didn'tВҰ214772 \add вүҲaffect them during Hizkiyah's lifetime\add*.
\s1 Hizkiyah's wealth
\rem /s1 Hezekiah's Wealth and Splendour; Hezekiah's Prosperity and Achievements
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 27 \add King\add* Hizkiyah \add вүҲhad become very wealthyВҰ214783, and heВҰ214788 was highly respected\add*. \add He established\add* treasuriesВҰ214787 for goldВҰ214792 and silverВҰ214791, for gemstones and spicesВҰ214795, and for shieldsВҰ214796 and other valuable things,
\v 28 as well as storehousesВҰ214801 for grainВҰ214803, wine, and \add olive\add* oilВҰ214805, and stallsВҰ214806 for \add вүҲall kinds of livestockВҰ214809\add* and \add &his\add* flocksВҰ214811.
\v 29 He built citiesВҰ214814 for himself, and acquiredВҰ214817 large numbersВҰ214821 of \add вүҲsheep and goats, and also cattle\add*, because GodВҰ214826 had \add вүҲmade him very prosperous\add*.
\p
\v 30 Hizkiyah \add вүҲblocked off\add* the upperВҰ214839 outletВҰ214836 at the GihonВҰ214838 spring andВҰ214831 directedВҰ214840 \add @the waterВҰ214837\add* down the western side of вҖҳThe City of DavidВҰ214845вҖҷ. All his projects were successful,
\v 31 and so when the Babylonian leaders sentВҰ214857 messengers to \add вүҲask aboutВҰ214859 the miracle thatВҰ214861 had been done inВҰ214853 the country\add*, God left him \add alone\add* to test him and \add вүҲsee what he really believed\add*.
\s1 Hizkiyah's reign ends
\rem /s1 The End of Hezekiah's Reign; Summary of Hezekiah's Reign
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Kgs 20:20-21)
\p
\v 32 The record of all the other things done by Hizkiyah \add вүҲwhile he was king\add*, including his loyal commitment, was writtenВҰ214877 onВҰ214878 the scrollВҰ214886 вҖҳThe kingsВҰ214887 of YehudahВҰ214889 andВҰ214872 YisraelВҰ214890вҖҷ.
\v 33 Then Hizkiyah died and was buriedВҰ214897 in the \add вүҲupper tombs\add* withВҰ214898 David'sВҰ214902 other descendantsВҰ214900, and everyone in YerushalemВҰ214912 and across YehudahВҰ214910 honouredВҰ214903 him. Then his son Menashsheh replaced him as kingВҰ214913.
\c 33
\s1 Yehudah's king Menashsheh
\rem /s1 Manasseh Rules in Judah; Reign of Manasseh; King Manasseh of Judah; Manasseh King of Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Kgs 21:1-9)
\p
\v 1 Menashsheh \add (ManassehВҰ214924)\add* was twelve when he becameВҰ214925 kingВҰ214925, and he reignedВҰ214929 from YerushalemВҰ214930 for fifty-five years.
\v 2 He did was what Yahweh \add вүҲhad said was\add* evilВҰ214933, like the disgusting things of the \add вүҲpeopleВҰ214942 groups\add* thatВҰ214938 Yahweh had driven out \add вүҲahead of the IsraelisВҰ214942\add*.\x + \xo 33:2: \xt Jer 15:4.\x*
\v 3 The hilltop shrines thatВҰ214950 his fatherВҰ214953 Hizkiyah had torn down, he turned around and rebuilt them and erectedВҰ214954 altarsВҰ214955 to the BaalsВҰ214956, and he made Asherot \add polesВҰ214958\add*, and he bowed down to all the stars in the sky and servedВҰ214964 them.
\v 4 He builtВҰ214967 altarsВҰ214968 in Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add* in YerushalemВҰ214974 that Yahweh had previously saidВҰ214972 that his nameВҰ214977 would \add вүҲalways be associated withВҰ214974\add*.\x + \xo 33:4: \xt 2Ch 6:6.\x*
\v 5 HeВҰ214990 builtВҰ214980 altarsВҰ214981 for all the stars in the sky in both of the temple courtyardsВҰ214987,
\v 6 and he made his sonsВҰ214996 passВҰ214993 through the fireВҰ214997 in the Ben-HinnomВҰ215001 valleyВҰ214998, and he practicedВҰ215002 fortune-telling and sorceryВҰ215004 and magic, and \add вүҲconnected\add* withВҰ214997 mediums and spiritsВҰ215007. He did so much evilВҰ215010 in Yahweh's eyesВҰ215011 that it provokedВҰ215013 him into getting angry.
\p
\v 7 He made an idolatrous imageВҰ215018 and put it in the \add вүҲtemple\add*, \add yes,\add* where GodВҰ215026 had told DavidВҰ215029 and his son Shelomoh, вҖңMy nameВҰ215045 \add вүҲwill be associated\add* withВҰ215034 thatВҰ215020 building foreverВҰ215046, there in YerushalemВҰ215036 which was chosenВҰ215038 from all the tribesВҰ215040 of YisraelВҰ215041.\x + \xo 33:7-8: \xt 1Ki 9:3-5; 2Ch 7:12-18.\x*
\v 8 If YisraelВҰ215054 will be careful to do everything that I've instructedВҰ215070 them and follow all the regulationsВҰ215074 and statutes that were given to them through MoshehВҰ215078, thenВҰ215048 I won'tВҰ215048 force them to leave the land again that I gave to their ancestorsВҰ215059.вҖқ
\v 9 \add вүҲSoВҰ215080\add* Menashsheh led Yehudah'sВҰ215084 inhabitantsВҰ215085 astray, andВҰ215085 \add all\add* YehudahвҖ”doingВҰ215087 more evilВҰ215088 than the nationsВҰ215091 thatВҰ215092 YahwehВҰ215094 had destroyedВҰ215093 ahead of the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ215096\add*.
\rem /s1 Manasseh Restored after Repentance; Manasseh Repents
\p
\v 10 Then YahwehВҰ215101 spokeВҰ215100 to \add King\add* Menashsheh and his peopleВҰ215107, \add вүҲbutВҰ215100\add* theyВҰ215109 paid no attentionВҰ215109,
\v 11 \add вүҲso\add* YahwehВҰ215112 broughtВҰ215111 in the army leaders from the Assyrian kingВҰ215119 and they capturedВҰ215121 Menashsheh. They put a hook \add in his nose\add* and put bronzeВҰ215127 chains around his feet, and tookВҰ215128 him away to BabylonВҰ215129.
\v 12 When he was there suffering, he humbledВҰ215139 himself in the presence of his ancestors' god YahwehВҰ215137, andВҰ215131 pleaded with him \add for help\add*.
\v 13 \add вүҲWhen\add* he prayedВҰ215145, \add @Yahweh\add* listenedВҰ215149 to him and answered his request and broughtВҰ215151 him back to YerushalemВҰ215152 to his kingdomВҰ215153, thenВҰ215145 Menashsheh \add вүҲrealised\add* that Yahweh is \add really\add* God.
\p
\v 14 After that, he rebuiltВҰ215164 the outerВҰ215166 wall for вҖҳThe City of DavidВҰ215170вҖҷ onВҰ215173 the west of GihonВҰ215172 to the Fish Gate andВҰ215161 around the hillвҖ”also making it higher. ThenВҰ215161 he stationed army commandersВҰ215182 inВҰ215173 all of Yehudah'sВҰ215189 fortifiedВҰ215188 citiesВҰ215187.
\v 15 He removedВҰ215191 the foreignВҰ215195 godsВҰ215194 and idols from the \add вүҲtemple\add*, as well as all the altarsВҰ215203 thatВҰ215204 he'd builtВҰ215205 onВҰ215206 the \add вүҲtemple mountВҰ215206\add* and throughout YerushalemВҰ215210, and he \add вүҲdumped\add* them \add all\add* outsideВҰ215212 the cityВҰ215213.
\v 16 ThenВҰ215215 he rebuilt Yahweh's altarВҰ215219 and sacrificedВҰ215221 peaceВҰ215224 offering and thankВҰ215225 offerings on it, and he told YehudahВҰ215227 to serveВҰ215228 Yisrael's godВҰ215232 Yahweh.
\v 17 However, the peopleВҰ215237 continued to offer sacrificesВҰ215238 atВҰ215239 the hilltop shrines, butВҰ215235 \add now\add* only to theirВҰ215242 godВҰ215242 YahwehВҰ215241.
\rem /s1 The End of Manasseh's Reign; Death of Manasseh
\rem /r (2 Kings 21.17-18)
\p
\v 18 The record of all the other things done by Menashsheh \add вүҲwhile he was king\add*, including his prayerВҰ215247 to his godВҰ215250 andВҰ215244 the messagesВҰ215251 spokenВҰ215253 to him by the prophets, was written on the scroll вҖҳThe kingsВҰ215263 of YisraelВҰ215258вҖҷ.
\v 19 It's writtenВҰ215285 in вҖҳThe Words of HozayвҖҷ about his disobedience and unfaithfulВҰ215273 activities, and how he'd builtВҰ215276 the hilltop shrines and Asherah \add polesВҰ215280\add* and idolsВҰ215281 before he'd humbledВҰ215283 himself, as well as \add вүҲthe response to his pleading in his prayerВҰ215266\add*.
\v 20 ThenВҰ215290 MenashshehВҰ215291 \add вүҲdied\add* and was buriedВҰ215295 at his \add вүҲpalace\add*, and his son AmonВҰ215298 \add вүҲreplaced himВҰ215295 as kingВҰ215297\add*.
\s1 Yehudah's King Amon
\rem /s1 Amon's Reign and Death; King Amon of Judah; Amon Rules in Judah; Amon King of Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Kgs 21:19-26)
\p
\v 21 AmonВҰ215308 was twenty-two when he becameВҰ215309 kingВҰ215309, and he ruled from YerushalemВҰ215313 for two yearsВҰ215311.
\v 22 He did what YahwehВҰ215318 \add вүҲhad said was\add* evil, just like his father Menashsheh had done, and \add *he\add* sacrificedВҰ215330 to all the idolsВҰ215325 thatВҰ215326 his father had made, and servedВҰ215332 them.
\v 23 HeВҰ215339 didn'tВҰ215334 humble himselfВҰ215335 \add вүҲandВҰ215334 turn to YahwehВҰ215337 like his fatherВҰ215340 had\add*, \add вүҲso Amon'sВҰ215343 guiltВҰ215345 was even worse\add*.
\p
\v 24 ThenВҰ215347 \add @Amon's\add* servantsВҰ215349 conspiredВҰ215347 against him, andВҰ215347 assassinated him inВҰ215351 his \add вүҲpalace\add*,
\v 25 \add вүҲbutВҰ215353 the local\add* people executed all those who'd conspiredВҰ215360 against KingВҰ215363 AmonВҰ215364, andВҰ215353 made his son YoshiyahВҰ215371 king in his placeВҰ215373.
\c 34
\s1 Yehudah's King Yoshiyah
\rem /s1 Reign of Josiah; Josiah's reforms; Josiah's Reforms; King Josiah of Judah; Josiah Rules in Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Kgs 22:1-2)
\p
\v 1 YoshiyahВҰ215380 was eightВҰ215378 when he becameВҰ215381 kingВҰ215381, and he reignedВҰ215385 from YerushalemВҰ215386 for thirty-one yearsВҰ215379.\x + \xo 34:1: \xt Jer 3:6.\x*
\v 2 He did what YahwehВҰ215391 \add вүҲhad said was\add* right, andВҰ215388 \add вүҲmade similar decisions to his ancestor DavidВҰ215394\add*вҖ”not deviating to the right or the left.
\rem /s1 Josiah Attacks Pagan Worship
\p
\v 3 In the eighthВҰ215402 year of his reignВҰ215404 while he was stillВҰ215406 a \add вүҲteenager\add*, he began to \add вүҲlearn more\add* about the godВҰ215410 of his ancestor DavidВҰ215411, and inВҰ215402 the twelfth year, he began to remove the hilltop shrines from YerushalemВҰ215421 and \add across\add* YehudahВҰ215420, as well as the Asherah polesВҰ215425, and the idols and metal images.
\v 4 \add вүҲHe watched while\add* they tore down the altars for the BaalsВҰ215433 and cut down the incenseВҰ215434 altars thatВҰ215435 were aboveВҰ215437 them. He shattered the Asherah polesВҰ215440 and the idolsВҰ215441 and metal imagesВҰ215442, thenВҰ215429 crushed them \add to powder\add* whichВҰ215435 he scatteredВҰ215445 over the gravesВҰ215449 of those who'd sacrificedВҰ215450 to them.\x + \xo 34:4: \xt 2Ki 21:3; 2Ch 33:3.\x*
\v 5 He burnt the bonesВҰ215453 of \add those\add* priestsВҰ215454 on their altars, and \add so\add* heВҰ215455 purified YerushalemВҰ215466 and \add all\add* YehudahВҰ215463,\x + \xo 34:5: \xt 1Ki 13:2.\x*
\v 6 as well as in the citiesВҰ215468 in \add the tribes of\add* Menashsheh, Efrayim, Shimeon, andВҰ215468 \add as far north as\add* NaftaliВҰ215474, including in the ruinsВҰ215476 aroundВҰ215478 them.
\v 7 He tore down the altars and the Asherah polesВҰ215486, ground the idolsВҰ215487 into pieces, and cut down the incenseВҰ215492 altars in all YisraelВҰ215497 \add вүҲbefore returningВҰ215498\add* to YerushalemВҰ215499.
\rem /s1 The Book of the Law Is Discovered; Discovery of the Book of the Law
\rem /r (2 Kings 22.3-20)
\p
\v 8 In his eighteenthВҰ215503 yearВҰ215502 \add вүҲas king\add*, in orderВҰ215506 to purify the land and the \add вүҲtemple\add*, he sentВҰ215509 Atsalyah's son ShafanВҰ215512, MaaseyahВҰ215518 the cityВҰ215521 officialВҰ215519, and Yoahaz's son YoahВҰ215523 the secretary, to repairВҰ215528 the residence of his godВҰ215533 YahwehВҰ215532.
\v 9 They wentВҰ215535 to Hilkiyah the highВҰ215541 priestВҰ215540 and \add вүҲhanded over the funds thatВҰ215550 had been donated\add* for God's houseВҰ215547, whichВҰ215550 had been collected by the LevitesВҰ215553 as doorkeepersвҖ”\add the moneyВҰ215545\add* was from \add the tribes of\add* Menashsheh, Efrayim, and other places in \add the northern kingdom of\add* YisraelВҰ215561, as well as from Yerushalem'sВҰ215568 inhabitants and \add across\add* all of YehudahВҰ215564 and BenyaminВҰ215565.
\v 10 \add @The priests\add* thenВҰ215570 \add вүҲpaid the workers\add* who'd been assigned to \add work in\add* Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add* to repairВҰ215587 andВҰ215570 strengthen it.
\v 11 They also \add вүҲpaid the carpentersВҰ215592\add* and buildersВҰ215593 to buy cut stoneВҰ215595 and timberВҰ215597 for the beamsВҰ215599 and braces whichВҰ215603 Yehudah'sВҰ215606 kingsВҰ215605 \add вүҲhad allowed to deteriorate\add*,
\v 12 and the \add вүҲworkers\add* did their workВҰ215611 faithfully. \add вүҲTheir supervisorsВҰ215628\add* were Yahat and Ovadyah (Levites descended from MerariВҰ215621), as well as Zekaryah and MeshullamВҰ215623 (descendants of \add Levi's son\add* Kohat), and all the Levites who \add вүҲwere good onВҰ215610 their\add* musical instrumentsВҰ215633.
\v 13 They \add also\add* supervisedВҰ215639 the portersВҰ215638 and those working on various \add other\add* tasks. Some of the LevitesВҰ215645 were secretaries, officialsВҰ215647, and guards.
\p
\rem /s1 The Book of the Law Found; Hilkiah Discovers God's Law
\v 14 When theyВҰ215650 were bringingВҰ215650 the moneyВҰ215653 out of the \add вүҲtemple\add*, Hilkiyah the \add high\add* priestВҰ215659 foundВҰ215657 a scrollВҰ215662 containing Yahweh's instructions that had \add вүҲbeen given via\add* MoshehВҰ215668 \add (MosesВҰ215668)\add*.
\v 15 Hilkiyah \add вүҲinformed\add* the scribe ShafanВҰ215675 that he had foundВҰ215679 a Torah scroll in the \add вүҲtemple\add*, andВҰ215670 \add *he\add* gave \add *him\add* the scroll.
\v 16 ShafanВҰ215692 took the scroll \add withВҰ215710 him\add* to the king andВҰ215691 \add вүҲreportedВҰ215699\add* to him, вҖңYour servantsВҰ215712 are doingВҰ215714 everything they were assigned to do.
\v 17 They've taken the cash that was in Yahweh's residence, andВҰ215716 \add вүҲpassed itВҰ215724 on\add* to the supervisors \add вүҲof the workers\add*.вҖқ
\v 18 ThenВҰ215735 ShafanВҰ215736 told the king, вҖң\add I'veВҰ215748 brought\add* a scrollВҰ215740 that the priestВҰ215744 HilkiyahВҰ215743 gaveВҰ215741 me,вҖқ andВҰ215735 thenВҰ215735 \add *he\add* started reading it out to the king.
\p
\v 19 \add вүҲWhen\add* the kingВҰ215754 heardВҰ215753 the wordsВҰ215756 \add вүҲwith God's instructions\add*, he tore his clothesВҰ215761 \add in grief\add*.
\v 20 ThenВҰ215763 \add *he\add* commandedВҰ215763 Hilkiyah, Shafan'sВҰ215773 son AhikamВҰ215770, Mikah's son Avdon, Shafan \add himself\add*, andВҰ215763 the king's special advisor AsayahВҰ215785,
\v 21 вҖңGo \add and\add* \add вүҲask\add* Yahweh on my behalf and on behalf of those inВҰ215799 YisraelВҰ215799 and YehudahВҰ215800, \add вүҲwhat he wants us to do\add* withВҰ215799 respect to the instructions on the scroll that has \add just\add* been foundВҰ215806, because \add it seems that\add* Yahweh \add вүҲwill be very angry atВҰ215799 us\add* because our ancestorsВҰ215821 haven't \add вүҲfollowed all of Yahweh's instructions as they're\add* writtenВҰ215829 on that scroll.вҖқ
\rem /s1 The Prophet Huldah Consulted
\p
\v 22 \add вүҲSo\add* Hilkiyah and \add вүҲthe others\add* wentВҰ215836 to Yerushalem'sВҰ215858 Second District to the prophetessВҰ215843 HuldahВҰ215842 (wifeВҰ215844 of ShallumВҰ215846, son of Tokahat, son of HasrahВҰ215853 who \add вүҲtook care of the temple robes\add*). They \add вүҲpassed onВҰ215858 the king's question\add*
\v 23 andВҰ215865 she \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңYisrael'sВҰ215872 godВҰ215871 YahwehВҰ215870 saysВҰ215869 to tell \add вүҲthe king\add*:
\v 24 YahwehВҰ215884 saysВҰ215883, вҖҳListen, I'm going to bringВҰ215886 disaster on this placeВҰ215890 andВҰ215892 itsВҰ215894 inhabitantsВҰ215894 as per all the cursesВҰ215898 writtenВҰ215899 on that scroll that was read to Yehudah'sВҰ215907 kingВҰ215906
\v 25 because they've abandonedВҰ215912 me and offered incenseВҰ215913 to otherВҰ215917 godsВҰ215916. \add That's\add* made me angry and \add so\add* my rage will be pouredВҰ215923 out onВҰ215920 this placeВҰ215925, and itВҰ215928 \add вүҲcan'tВҰ215927 be prevented\add*.вҖҷ
\v 26 \add вүҲHowever,\add* Yehudah'sВҰ215933 kingВҰ215932 sentВҰ215934 youВҰ215950 all to \add вүҲask for Yahweh's direction\add*, so tell him, вҖҳYisrael's godВҰ215946 Yahweh saysВҰ215944 thatВҰ215949 \add after\add* \add вүҲhearing the wordsВҰ215948\add* \add of the scroll\add*,
\v 27 because \add вүҲyou were sincere\add* and you humbled yourself before GodВҰ215959 when you heard his wordsВҰ215963 about this placeВҰ215966 and its inhabitantsВҰ215970. \add Yes,\add* YahwehВҰ215985 declares that you've humbled yourself before me and torn your clothesВҰ215976, and wept \add вүҲinВҰ215960 front of\add* me, and I've \add вүҲpersonally\add* heard you.
\v 28 \add вүҲSo listenВҰ215987,\add* I will \add вүҲallow youВҰ215988 to die and be buried inВҰ215996 peaceВҰ215996\add* and \add so\add* yourВҰ215988 eyesВҰ216000 won'tВҰ215997 see the disasterВҰ216002 that I'll \add вүҲsend\add* to this placeВҰ216008 and itsВҰ216012 inhabitantsВҰ216012.вҖҷ вҖқ
\m \add вүҲSo\add* theyВҰ215999 \add вүҲtook that response\add* back to the kingВҰ216016.
\rem /s1 Josiah Makes a Covenant to Obey the Lord; The Covenant Renewed; Josiah's Religious Reforms
\rem /r (2 Kings 23.1-20)
\p
\v 29 Then the kingВҰ216021 summoned all the eldersВҰ216027 from YerushalemВҰ216029 and \add вүҲfrom across\add* YehudahВҰ216028
\v 30 and they all \add вүҲwalked\add* up to the \add вүҲtemple\add* withВҰ216052 the inhabitantsВҰ216040 of YerushalemВҰ216041 and \add all\add* YehudahВҰ216039, and the priestsВҰ216042 and the LevitesВҰ216043, and all the peopleВҰ216046 \add вүҲirrespective of theirВҰ216052 standing in the community\add*. ThenВҰ216031 \add @the kingВҰ216032\add* read everything out to them that was onВҰ216052 the Torah scrollВҰ216058 that had been foundВҰ216060 in the \add вүҲtemple\add*.
\v 31 ThenВҰ216064 the kingВҰ216065 stoodВҰ216064 at his \add normal\add* placeВҰ216068 and \add вүҲmade an agreement\add* with Yahweh: to obey Yahweh and follow his instructions and his regulationsВҰ216083 and statutes, \add вүҲsincerely and with all his energy\add*вҖ”doingВҰ216090 what was in the \add вүҲjoint understanding\add* that had been writtenВҰ216095 on the scroll.
\v 32 ThenВҰ216101 he had everyoneВҰ216103 from Yerushalem and BenyaminВҰ216107 take a stand \add inВҰ216106 agreement to it\add*, and \add so\add* Yerushalem'sВҰ216106 inhabitantsВҰ216109 \add вүҲrenewed\add* their agreement withВҰ216106 the god of their ancestorsВҰ216114.
\v 33 \add вүҲSoВҰ216116\add* \add King\add* Yoshiyah removedВҰ216116 all the disgusting \add idols\add* from \add вүҲall the Yisraeli regions\add*, andВҰ216116 he \add вүҲmade\add* everyoneВҰ216131 inВҰ216134 YisraelВҰ216128 serveВҰ216135 their god YahwehвҖ”\add вүҲduring his lifetime\add* they never turnedВҰ216144 away from Yahweh, the god of their ancestorsВҰ216148.
\c 35
\s1 Celebrating the messenger's вҖҳpassing-overвҖҷ
\rem /s1 Josiah Celebrates Passover; Josiah Celebrates the Passover; Celebration of the Passover
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Kgs 23:21-23)
\p
\v 1 Then \add King\add* Yoshiyah \add вүҲprepared\add* a вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ celebration inВҰ216153 YerushalemВҰ216153, and they slaughteredВҰ216156 the \add вүҲlambs atВҰ216153 the end of March\add* .
\v 2 \add *He\add* assigned the priestsВҰ216164 to \add вүҲthe various tasks that needed to be done\add*, andВҰ216168 \add вүҲencouragedВҰ216168 them to do theirВҰ216167 workВҰ216169 well\add*.
\v 3 He told the LevitesВҰ216174 (they had been \add вүҲseparated\add* \add from the other tribes\add* in order to serve Yahweh) who were teaching all Yisrael, вҖңPlace the sacredВҰ216180 box in the houseВҰ216188 thatВҰ216189 David'sВҰ216194 son, Yisrael's KingВҰ216195 Shelomoh \add (SolomonВҰ216191)\add* had builtВҰ216190вҖ”it won'tВҰ216197 be a burdenВҰ216200 any more for your shouldersВҰ216201. Now serve your godВҰ216207 Yahweh andВҰ216173 his \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ216195\add* peopleВҰ216209
\v 4 and prepareВҰ216212 yourselves inВҰ216219 your clan divisionsВҰ216218 as per the instructions written by Yisrael's KingВҰ216221 DavidВҰ216220 and his son Shelomoh.\x + \xo 35:4: \xt 2Ch 8:14.\x*
\v 5 ThenВҰ216227 standВҰ216227 inВҰ216228 the \add вүҲtemple area\add*, \add вүҲgroupedВҰ216229 by your clans\add* \add вүҲandВҰ216227 ready to help the other tribes\add*.
\v 6 Consecrate yourselves andВҰ216241 slaughterВҰ216241 the вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ \add lambs\add* for \add вүҲthe people\add* \add вүҲas per the instructions\add* \add given\add* through MoshehВҰ216252 \add (MosesВҰ216252)\add* by YahwehВҰ216249.
\p
\v 7 \add King\add* Yoshiyah \add вүҲprovided\add* thirtyВҰ216270 thousand lambsВҰ216260 and young goatsВҰ216263 for the вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ \add sacrifices\add* from his own flocksВҰ216259 and threeВҰ216273 thousand bullsВҰ216272 \add вүҲfrom his own herds\add*.
\v 8 His officials \add вүҲalso\add* contributedВҰ216285 to the peopleВҰ216282, priests and LevitesВҰ216284. The chief temple officials Hilkiyah, Zekaryah, and Yehiel donated 2,600 lambs and threeВҰ216299 hundred cattle to the priests.
\v 9 The LeviteВҰ216311 leadersВҰ216310 Konanyah and his younger brothersВҰ216306 ShemayahВҰ216304, NetanelВҰ216305, along with Hashavyah, YeielВҰ216308, and Yozavad \add together\add* contributedВҰ216312 five thousandВҰ216316 lambs and three hundredВҰ216319 bullsВҰ216317.
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲSoВҰ216321 everything\add* was preparedВҰ216321 as the king had commandedВҰ216332, and the priestsВҰ216324 stoodВҰ216323 at their placesВҰ216327, and the LevitesВҰ216328 were there in their \add various\add* divisionsВҰ216331
\v 11 andВҰ216335 they slaughteredВҰ216335 the вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ \add lambs\add*, thenВҰ216335 the priestsВҰ216338 sprinkledВҰ216337 the blood while the LevitesВҰ216340 skinnedВҰ216341 \add >the animals\add*.
\v 12 They set asideВҰ216343 \add the animals\add* to be burntВҰ216344 \add onВҰ216355 the altar\add*, \add вүҲinВҰ216355 order to giveВҰ216345 them to the various family groupsВҰ216346 to offerВҰ216344\add* to YahwehВҰ216353, followingВҰ216357 the instructions MoshehВҰ216356 had writtenВҰ216354 down. They did the same thing withВҰ216355 the cattle.
\v 13 They roastedВҰ216360 the вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ \add meal\add* over the fireВҰ216362 as per the instructions, and theyВҰ216365 boiledВҰ216365 the meat of the sacredВҰ216364 offeringsВҰ216364 inВҰ216362 pots and kettlesВҰ216367 and pans, and \add вүҲserved the meat immediately to all the peopleВҰ216373 who were there\add*.\x + \xo 35:13: \xt Exo 12:8-9.\x*
\v 14 Afterwards, \add @the LevitesВҰ216389\add* prepared the meal for themselves and for the priests (Aharon's descendants), because the priests had been busy sacrificing the burntВҰ216384 offeringsВҰ216383 and the fat portions right through to the evening.
\v 15 The singersВҰ216396 (Asaf'sВҰ216399 descendantsВҰ216397) were at their posts as had been commandedВҰ216403 by \add KingВҰ216409\add* DavidВҰ216404, Asaf, Heyman, andВҰ216396 the king's prophet Yedutun. The \add вүҲmen guarding the gates didn'tВҰ216414 have to leave their posts\add* because their fellow LevitesВҰ216422 preparedВҰ216423 \add >food\add* for them.\x + \xo 35:15: \xt 1Ch 25:1.\x*
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲSoВҰ216426 on that dayВҰ216431, everything that needed to done for worshipping YahwehВҰ216430 was done\add*. They celebrated the вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ festival, andВҰ216426 they sacrificed burntВҰ216436 offeringsВҰ216436 as KingВҰ216441 Yoshiyah had commandedВҰ216440.
\v 17 The \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ216445 who were there celebrated\add* the вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ that \add вүҲday\add*, thenВҰ216444 theyВҰ216444 celebrated the вҖҳFestival of Flat BreadвҖҷ for sevenВҰ216458 daysВҰ216459.\x + \xo 35:17: \xt Exo 12:1-20.\x*
\v 18 There hadn't been a вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ celebration done like thatВҰ216479 is Yisrael sinceВҰ216467 the \add вүҲtime\add* of the prophetВҰ216469 Shemuel \add (SamuelВҰ216468)\add*, and all of Yisrael's kingsВҰ216472 had never done it like Yoshiyah did, along withВҰ216466 the priestsВҰ216483 and LevitesВҰ216484 and the inhabitantsВҰ216490 of YerushalemВҰ216491 and \add across\add* all YehudahВҰ216487 and Yisrael.
\v 19 They celebrated that \add вүҲfestival\add* inВҰ216494 the eighteenthВҰ216494 yearВҰ216496 of Yoshiyah's reignВҰ216497.
\s1 The death of Yehudah's King Yoshiyah
\rem /s1 Defeat by Pharaoh Neco and Death of Josiah; Josiah Dies in Battle; The Death of Josiah; The End of Josiah's Reign
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Kgs 23:28-30)
\p
\v 20 AfterВҰ216503 all of Yoshiyah's \add вүҲwork on temple restoration\add*, Egypt'sВҰ216517 KingВҰ216515 Neko went to attack Karkemish \add city\add* on the EuphratesВҰ216522 river, and Yoshiyah went out to \add вүҲconfront\add* him.
\v 21 \add @Neko\add* sentВҰ216527 messengersВҰ216529 to tell \add @Yoshiyah\add*, вҖңWhat's \add вүҲthis got to do with\add* you, KingВҰ216537 of Judah? \add вүҲWe're not attacking you at present\add*, \add вүҲbecause we're in a different fight\add*, and God told me to hurryВҰ216551. \add вүҲDon't opposeВҰ216555\add* God who's with me, and don'tВҰ216539 \add make\add* him destroyВҰ216561 you.вҖқ
\v 22 \add вүҲHowever,\add* Yoshiyah \add вүҲwouldn't listen\add*, butВҰ216563 disguisedВҰ216573 himselfВҰ216573 \add вүҲbefore going into battle\add*. He didn'tВҰ216563 listen to Neko \add вүҲeven though he was speaking for\add* GodВҰ216581, so he wentВҰ216582 to fight onВҰ216584 the Megiddon plainВҰ216584.
\p
\v 23 KingВҰ216589 Yoshiyah was hit by the archersВҰ216588, andВҰ216587 he told his servantsВҰ216593, вҖң\add вүҲGet me away from here\add* because I'm badly woundedВҰ216596.вҖқ
\v 24 \add вүҲSoВҰ216599\add* his servantsВҰ216600 \add вүҲlifted him off his\add* chariot, and took him \add вүҲonВҰ216615 his reserve\add* chariot back to Yerushalem \add where he died\add*. He was buriedВҰ216614 inВҰ216615 his ancestors' tombsВҰ216615, and all Yerushalem and YehudahВҰ216619 mournedВҰ216621 over \add *him\add*.
\p
\v 25 \add The prophet\add* Yermeyah \add (Jeremiah)\add* wroteВҰ216651 a \add вүҲfuneral song\add* for him, which the male and female singers still use \add вүҲatВҰ216638 funerals\add* to this dayВҰ216644. \add вүҲThat became a customВҰ216646 in YisraelВҰ216649вҖ”the words of that song are writtenВҰ216651 in a scroll of funeral songs\add*.
\p
\v 26 The record of all the other things done by Yoshiyah \add вүҲwhile he was king\add* andВҰ216656 his loyal commitment \add вүҲto following Yahweh's instructions\add*,
\v 27 including his actions from the beginning to the end \add of his reign\add*, was writtenВҰ216668 on the scrollВҰ216671 вҖҳThe kingsВҰ216672 of YisraelВҰ216674 andВҰ216664 YehudahвҖҷ.
\c 36
\s1 Yehudah's King Yehoahaz
\rem /s1 King Joahaz of Judah; Reign of Jehoahaz; The last kings of Judah; Jehoahaz Rules in Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Kgs 23:30-35)
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ216677 the peopleВҰ216678 of \add вүҲYehudah\add* tookВҰ216677 Yoshiyah's son YehoahazВҰ216683 andВҰ216677 made himВҰ216687 kingВҰ216687 inВҰ216691 YerushalemВҰ216691 to replace his fatherВҰ216690.
\rem /s1 Jehoahaz King of Judah
\v 2 YehoahazВҰ216698 was twenty-three when he becameВҰ216699 kingВҰ216699, and he reignedВҰ216702 from YerushalemВҰ216703 for \add only\add* three monthsВҰ216701
\v 3 \add before\add* Egypt'sВҰ216708 kingВҰ216706 deposedВҰ216705 himВҰ216705 and \add вүҲforced the country to pay\add* an \add annual\add* tribute of \add вүҲthirty kilograms\add* of goldВҰ216719, and \add вүҲthree tonnes\add* of silverВҰ216717.
\v 4 Egypt'sВҰ216724 KingВҰ216722 Neko took YehoahazВҰ216740 to Egypt, and thenВҰ216721 the king made his \add younger\add* brother Elyakim king over YehudahВҰ216731 and YerushalemВҰ216732, \add вүҲalthough\add* he changedВҰ216733 Elyakim's name to Yehoyakim.\x + \xo 36:4: \xt Jer 22:11-12.\x*
\s1 Yehudah's King Yehoyakim
\rem /s1 Jehoiakim King of Judah; Jehoiakim Rules in Judah; Reign and Captivity of Jehoiakim; King Jehoiakim of Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Kgs 23:36вҖ“24:7)
\p
\v 5 Yehoyakim was twenty-five when he becameВҰ216754 kingВҰ216754 and he reignedВҰ216758 from YerushalemВҰ216759 for eleven years. \add вүҲHe did many things that YahwehВҰ216763 had said were evilВҰ216761\add*.\x + \xo 36:5: \xt Jer 22:18-19; 26:1-6; 35:1-19.\x*
\v 6 Babylonia's KingВҰ216769 NebuchadnezzarВҰ216768 \add (Heb. Nevukadnetstsar)\add* attacked \add and captured Yehoyakim\add* and took him to BabylonВҰ216770 inВҰ216772 bronzeВҰ216772 chains,\x + \xo 36:6: \xt Jer 25:1-38; 36:1-32; 45:1-5; Dan 1:1-2.\x*
\v 7 along withВҰ216783 some items from Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add* that were taken to BabylonВҰ216781 andВҰ216776 placed inВҰ216783 \add @the king's\add* temple \add *there\add*.
\p
\v 8 The record of all the other things done by Yehoyakim \add вүҲwhile he was king\add* and the disgusting activities he did was writtenВҰ216796 on the scrollВҰ216799 вҖҳThe kingsВҰ216800 of YisraelВҰ216801 and YehudahвҖҷ, and hisВҰ216789 son Yehoyakin \add вүҲreplaced him as king\add*.
\s1 Yehudah's King Yehoyakin
\rem /s1 Reign and Captivity of Jehoiachin; Jehoiachin Rules in Judah; Jehoiachin King of Judah; King Jehoiachin of Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Kgs 24:8-17)
\p
\v 9 Yehoyakin was eighteenВҰ216811\f + \fr 36:9 \ft Using 2 Kings 24:8 to (hopefully) correct the Hebrew here which has вҖҳeightвҖҷ.\f* when he becameВҰ216814 kingВҰ216814, and he reignedВҰ216819 from YerushalemВҰ216820 for \add just\add* tenВҰ216817 daysВҰ216818. \add вүҲHe did many things that YahwehВҰ216824 had said were evilВҰ216822\add*.
\v 10 \add вүҲAt the beginning of the next year\add*, KingВҰ216829 NebuchadnezzarВҰ216830 sent \add soldiers\add* to bring him to BabylonВҰ216832, bringing valuable items from the \add вүҲtemple\add*, and he made his \add younger\add* brother Tsidkiyah king over YehudahВҰ216847 and YerushalemВҰ216848.\x + \xo 36:10: a \xt Jer 22:24-30; 24:1-10; 29:1-2; Eze 17:12; \xo b \xt Jer 37:1; Eze 17:13.\x*
\s1 Yehudah's king Tsidkiyah
\rem /s1 King Zedekiah of Judah; Reign of Zedekiah; Zedekiah Rules in Judah; Zedekiah King of Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Kgs 24:18-20; Jer. 52:1-3a)
\p
\v 11 TsidkiyahВҰ216856 was twenty-one when he becameВҰ216857 kingВҰ216857, and he reignedВҰ216861 from YerushalemВҰ216862 for eleven years.\x + \xo 36:11: \xt Jer 27:1-22; 28:1-17.\x*
\v 12 \add вүҲHe did many things that Yahweh had said were evilВҰ216865,\add* \add in fact,\add* he didn'tВҰ216869 \add even\add* humbleВҰ216870 himselfВҰ216870 when the prophetВҰ216873 Yermeyah \add (Jeremiah)\add* \add вүҲbrought him a message\add* from Yahweh.
\rem /s1 The Fall of Jerusalem
\rem /r (2 Kings 25.1-21; Jeremiah 52.3b-11)
\v 13 He \add вүҲhad become very stubborn and wouldn't\add* return to Yisrael's god YahwehВҰ216895, and he \add also\add* rebelledВҰ216880 againstВҰ216892 KingВҰ216878 NebuchadnezzarВҰ216879 who'd made him \add вүҲpromise inВҰ216878 front of GodВҰ216883\add* \add to be loyal\add*.\x + \xo 36:13: \xt Eze 17:15.\x*
\v 14 \add вүҲIn addition\add*, all the leadersВҰ216902 of the priestsВҰ216903 and the peopleВҰ216904 \add of Yehudah\add* \add вүҲbecame more and more unfaithfulВҰ216906 and doing disgusting things often done in other\add* nationsВҰ216913, then they defiled Yahweh's residence whichВҰ216919 he had consecratedВҰ216920 in YerushalemВҰ216921.
\rem /s1 The Fall of Jerusalem
\p
\v 15 \add вүҲSoВҰ216923\add* YahwehВҰ216924, the godВҰ216925 of theirВҰ216926 ancestorsВҰ216926, \add вүҲsentВҰ216923 many messages via his prophets\add* because he felt compassionВҰ216934 on his peopleВҰ216937, andВҰ216923 on his residence,
\v 16 \add вүҲbutВҰ216942\add* they mocked God'sВҰ216945 messengersВҰ216944 andВҰ216942 \add вүҲrejected\add* the messagesВҰ216947вҖ”ridiculing his prophetsВҰ216949 until YahwehВҰ216954 \add вүҲbecame so angry that he couldn't be stopped\add*.
\rem /s1 The Fall of Jerusalem
\v 17 \add вүҲSoВҰ216961\add* \add Yahweh\add* \add вүҲsent\add* the Chaldean kingВҰ216965 againstВҰ216962 them, and \add #they\add* \add вүҲran their young men through\add* withВҰ216970 the swordВҰ216970, \add even\add* inВҰ216970 the \add вүҲtemple\add*, and \add #they\add* didn'tВҰ216973 spare any of the young men or women, or \add even\add* those who were older or elderlyвҖ”\add @God\add* allowed \add @Nebuchadnezzar\add* to \add thoroughly\add* \add вүҲdefeat them\add*.\x + \xo 36:17: \xt Jer 21:1-10; 34:1-5.\x*
\v 18 ThenВҰ216985 he took \add вүҲeverything valuable\add*, big or smallВҰ216990, from God's temple as well as from the kingВҰ216995 andВҰ216985 his officialsВҰ216996.
\v 19 They \add вүҲset God's temple onВҰ217014 fireВҰ217014\add*, and tore down \add some of\add* the wall \add surrounding\add* YerushalemВҰ217009, burnt all its palacesВҰ217012, and destroyedВҰ217019 everything valuableВҰ217018.\x + \xo 36:19: \xt 1Ki 9:8.\x*
\v 20 \add вүҲAnyone else who was still alive\add* was taken to BabylonВҰ217029 where they becameВҰ217030 servantsВҰ217034 to \add @the king\add* and his children, untilВҰ217035 \add the time when\add* the Persians \add вүҲcame to power\add*.
\v 21 \add That\add* fulfilled God's messageВҰ217042 that Yirmeyah had \add previously proclaimed\add*, that the land would become desolateВҰ217057 \add to make up for\add* the Rest Days \add that had been ignored\add*вҖ”that took seventyВҰ217060 years. \x + \xo 36:21: \xt Jer 25:11; 29:10.\x*
\s1 Cyrus sends the exiles back to Yehudah
\rem /s1 Cyrus Commands the Jews to Return; Cyrus Proclaims Liberty for the Exiles; Cyrus Allows the Exiles to Return
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (Ezra 1:1-4)
\p
\v 22 During the first yearВҰ217064 that King Cyrus \add (Heb. Koresh)\add* reigned over PersiaВҰ217068, inВҰ217073 orderВҰ217069 to \add further\add* fulfilВҰ217069 what Yahweh had said via \add the prophet\add* Yirmeyah, Yahweh \add вүҲworked onВҰ217073\add* the spiritВҰ217079 of King Cyrus who then wrote this ruling \add and sentВҰ217084 messengers\add* to announce it throughout his kingdomВҰ217089:
\v 23 вҖңI, Persia'sВҰ217102 KingВҰ217101 CyrusВҰ217099, declare that Yahweh, the god of the heavensВҰ217111, has given me all these earthlyВҰ217106 kingdomsВҰ217105, and he's given me the job of buildingВҰ217116 a houseВҰ217119 for him in YerushalemВҰ217120 whichВҰ217121 is in YehudahВҰ217122. \add To help with that,\add* \add вүҲanyone who's from there is allowed to return, and may their god Yahweh be with them and help them\add*.\x + \xo 36:23: \xt Isa 44:28.\x*
